Harbor Hotel.name: Harbor Hotel

reviews.text: Location is so-so since it's far from the touristy area but great if you want a quiet place that overlooks the sea. Rooms are okay as well. Only problem is the CR doesn't have a divider between the shower and the rest of the CR and there's no bidet. Owner was awesome as hell tho very nice guy. Speaks good English and even offered to drop us off at our destination when he was on his way home.

Near dongmun market and a few museums but the neighborhood it is located in is pretty much dead. The rooms are clean and the size is standard but they turn off the air conditioning if they think you are using it too much. They turned mine off and it somehow malfunctioned and kept making noise and flashing a bright red light all night. I couldn't sleep as the room was now too hot but opening the window let in noise from the road. They said they'll fix it the next day but never did.
Cleaning under the beds could be improved. Everything else was good. Very decent breakfast.
Good!
Good sea view, clean room and nice service.  Breakfast is healthy!

Hotel The One.name: Hotel The One

reviews.text:
Very, very bad experience ⚠️⚠️⚠️⚠️⚠️⚠️
Those of you who can read this review immediately avoid lightning this hotel and Jeju Island this tourist destination ！！！！！！！！！！！
(Chinese people have serious discrimination + hotel theft is prevalent and difficult to compensate and pursue, + a hotel card can be used to open multiple rooms + scenic spots are monotonous and general + shopping prices are higher than buying back home)

Incident: Boys were entered into our hotel room without permission, and the bathroom was used (p1)
Handling situation: No compensation or solution has been received at present

August 22:
After communicating with the front desk, we entered the room with a man and used the bathroom. It took about 3 minutes for the front desk to emphasize that we could ask someone to clean the room tomorrow. (Their focus is on cleaning, not safety, and is changing the subject.)
I also communicated with the front desk that we needed to check the surveillance (they replied that no one had entered our room and did not let me check the surveillance together within about 30 minutes).
Then emphasize to us that there is only one key to a room, and only we can open the door to this room. (This answer is also very problematic, first of all, the common sense cleaning card can open the door of the room, their management or the front desk also has a special card can open the door of the room, the use of some technological means can also open the door of the room)
This response does not have any credibility. First of all, I did not see the monitoring record, and secondly, the front desk generally does not have the right to directly view the monitoring.

-- Then I chose to communicate with Ctrip to solve this problem.

August 23rd
The whole process is communicated by Ctrip and the hotel

My appeal: 1. Find a manager to solve this problem together. 2. I see the surveillance myself.

Manager problem: After the first communication, they said that they did not have a manager, and the manager went to work every Monday (just after we returned to China 👍). In the second communication, the girl at the front desk said that she was the on-duty manager (OK random manager, right?) and communicated with her if there was any problem.
2. Asked to view the monitoring but was refused, saying that the guest could not view the monitoring. If you need to view the surveillance, you need to call the police (but the police may not be able to view the surveillance) see p4.

-- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- --
At present, we have changed a hotel to live in, I looked at the Jeju Island hotel theft/Jeju Island hotel sudden intruder small red book notes, probably have the following conclusions.

1. Sudden break-ins in Jeju hotels are the norm, because many hotels have a card that can open other rooms in the same hotel. It is difficult to defend our rights ➕ to solve the problem.

2. Hotel theft is also common in Jeju Island, and the cleaning staff and the front desk are likely to be in the same gang. For details, see notes on # Jeju Hotel theft

3. Calling the police won't work unless you're American

-- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- -- --
Then I checked the relevant notes of the hotel's little Red book:
1. In the case of other people in the room, a man used the card to open the door of the room and almost broke in (fortunately, the door was plugged in p2)

2. There is a serious problem with hotel hygiene
Budget hotel. Staff service attitude really poor. Bed side no power point.  Windows are smaller than one posted in advertisements.  Renovation cheap finishing. Windows can hear noise from the street.

Rooms ok, lack of charging and power, glass doors to toilet may be of concern. No flush toilet paper mitigated a bit by bidet, but still really? Breakfast, most expensive and worst by far on this trip in Korea.

Rooms are a little bit small in size (for example, for 3 pax per room as shown in the photo) but it's clean and cozy. Other than that, it's a great place to stay. The staff are very accommodating and patient - asked for a chicken and beer place, staff even printed out a copy of a map to show us. Breakfast buffet spread is quite good, they even have extended tables in the lobby. Location is good - e.g. there's a nearby 24-hour laundry service, quite a few 24-hour convenience stores and even a park at the back.

I like that the room I booked was huge - a King sized and a single sized bed, with a super huge bathroom (rain shower) and automatic toilet system. The bed was comfortable and sheets were clean. I also liked it that they had their own basement carpark, as the parking here in the city is awfully crowded. However, the equipment in the hotel looks generally worn out. I was disappointed because of the lack of maintenance. Lots of wear and tear, frays, stains on lounge chairs. (Photo here is at the hotel lobby!!) Overall still a decent hotel if you are looking for a clean hotel, but expect nothing luxurious. I came in end March and was told that the Aircon is centrally controlled so there's only heating system now. There was no way for me to change it. I can only open the windows if I wanted cool air to come in (at the risk of having mosquitoes, which they provided insect repellent).

reviews.text: The room was nice and clean. However, whenever the maids would clean the rooms, they would leave the doors open which lead to many mosquitos getting in (and that wasn't pleasant). You can't leave the windows open at night cause of the local night park with rides across the street can get loud. If you close the windows, its pretty quiet.
Room is spacious, comes with a computer in your room. Location is great too. Pretty good for the price
so so

I used room 505 for one night on a business trip and this is a specific evaluation.

1. The floor has hair rolling around and is poorly cleaned.
When I wiped the floor with a wet tissue, I wondered if this was really a wet mop. When I walked around with my bare feet, it was slippery and sticky.
2. The bathroom mirror has severe water stains.
3. The set-top box works, but the TV remote control receiver is defective, so you have to use the physical buttons on the TV to turn it on and off.
4. It was a non-smoking room, but the smell of cigarette smoke gave me a headache.
5. Room condition with dust accumulated on top of TV and set-top box
6. Indoor shoes provided in hygienic condition with the bottoms mixed with dust.
I turned my slippers inside out and left the room to check the cleanliness of the owner.
7. I don’t use the sunflower shower because it has too much limescale.
(Even if you just soak the shower head in scale remover, the condition will be better than this.)

I received a review report from Yanolja and was disappointed.
I regret paying a few thousand won more and going to the Regent in front of the motel.

Amenities are not provided in the room, but toothbrushes, soap, and toothpaste are provided in front of the counter. Please bring them up.

However, the owner is very kind.

Considering the Jeju special price on weekdays (Jeju exchange rate)
I changed my mind and thought that if the price was this much (45,000 with a discount), I should forgive it.

Good price, good location, and clean♡
I always make reservations here when I come on a business trip♡

reviews.text: smells like fish... ac didnt work but good price and great view
Hard bed and an old building that's showing its age, but still a pretty nice stay in a great location.

Superb hotel close to everything (bus stop, restaurant, ferry to U-do island). Super fast wifi, huge comfortable room, bug beds and very nice bathroom with hot water. Everything is extra clean. I don't understand why some customers complain. Towels may be small but it is the norm in Korea and they are provided for free along with shampoo/shower gel/toothpaste. There might be a small in the lobby because of the fish restaurant but who cares? The room smells perfectly well and there is A/C and heating. In addition, the value for money is fabulous and the staff super nice. Everything was really perfect.

good stay with surprisingly large rooms. good distance for the sunrise hill and eateries in the area.

however, the fridge can take time to cool up and can get noisy while doing so.

the towels may not be adequate, you may want to bring your own.

WATCH THIS BEFORE YOU BOOK !!!!
The place was ok, the location was ok. However the staff (the old guy) has ruined our whole experience in jeju. We booked through agoda and has stated 5 person while booking. However when we wanted to check in, he asked us to pay a 'local charges' and said is because the room is for 3 and we have 5 person. In the tnc for agoda they didnt mentioned that we need to pay any extra on the spot. We showed him the statement while he refused to see and keep on telling us that he dont understand english and asked us to call agoda ourself to sort this out.
WORST EXPERIENCE OF STAY IN JEJU. Defenitely wont recommend this 'hotel'. There is much more better stay nearby that area.

reviews.text:
We booked our stay at M-Stay hotel and we wanted to park our car at their free garage. The parking guy let us in, but after a few minutes he changed his mind and started banging hard on the car and forced us away. I NEVER felted this discriminated in the world before! The reception did not want to do anything about it, only talk to the guy ( then we know they did not get it :-()
The rooms are noisy, but decent enough. I am guessing this is hotel is only meant for Koreans on budget.

Good location within seogwipo, within walking distance to a street with good nightlife including food and some music. Staff was nice and room was clean. But there really wasn't anything to rave about. Bathroom was nice but with only bare minimum toiletries and no bath. I would stay again if I had to, but would rather find a nice pension instead.

Great breakfast buffet for only 12,000. Ice cold air-conditioning, pool is nice but only open until 6pm. Lots of families were staying here, so the pool got a bit crowded with kids in the later afternoon. (It's only about 4 feet deep)

Close to the food district and night life. Short walking distance to the airport limousine bus and other bus lines that will take you to all the tourist attractions.

When booking this hotel it was seemingly an amazing deal for 250 Canadian dollars for 5 nights.  Rooftop pool, city centre, how could I go wrong.  But unfortunately it was too good to be true.

Rooftop pool was closed )which I can understand)  due to covid (though I feel closing an outdoor pool is either overkill or just an excuse for staff to not have to maintain/clean the pool).

The parking situation was very confusing and a headache.  When going to the parkade there was no one there to help or places to park.  After having to park far away and then haul our luggage to the hotel they then told us that their parking is offsite.  Would have been nice if they had a sign outside.

When arriving, we found the front desk staff very rude and cold.  We arrived about 30 mins early for check-in and ask if we could check in early and was met with a "no! Check in is at 3, you wait!".   Ok, Didn't have to be so snappy about it but fair enough.

So my wife and her family decided to wait in the lobby until it was 3 and drink some water (it was very hot outside and we were all very dehydrated).  In Korea you have to wear a mask everywhere but is allowed to pull your mask down for a moment to take a drink of your water.  Apparently that was a problem for the front desk staff.  Instead of walking over to ask us to not drink water inside she decided to yell at us all the way across the lobby so everyone else in the lobby could hear.  And was met with alot of people staring.  Pretty embarrasing - was infuriating as well.  Not a good way to kick off the first impressions of Jeju Island.

Later on in that trip, my wife had lost her card to the room so we went to go ask for a new one and it was 10 dollars!  I think this is the only hotel that would actually charge you for that.  Definitely a first for me.  Most hotels don't even care if you give the card back or not.

The rest of the trip every time we were coming out of the elevator I always felt the front desk staff was staring at us and felt very uncomfortable.

The room itself and the room service was amazing.  They always cleaned our room every day and did an excellent job.  Room was nice and spacious but could have used one of those usb charger hubs.  Also the location is really good.  All the good spots in seogwipo is within walking distance and has a 7-eleven below

Though I can't recommend this place.  Usually I can deal with it if it's a one off but I really feel the staff go out of their way to not be very nice (maybe because I was non-korean?) Oh well.  Not worth the money.  If I ever return to Jeju (which is doubtful) I will pay a little more and stay somewhere nicer.  Countless other options in that area
Hand towels. It's a 3.5-star hotel without real towels. I do not want to use 3-4 towels to dry after a shower. There are not any other sizes.

reviews.text: If you’re seeking a room around Jeju, this is not the exact place that you looking for. Please choose another better hotel. The hotel situation and everything is horrible like worse than a motel. Just don’t go, it's like haunted house!!!

I said it was good,

I had a trip to the mainland, so I looked for accommodation near the airport and made a reservation.

Recommended for accommodation near the airport~~

It's an old building, but it's cozy and quiet.

reviews.text: I had a nice and comfortable stay at this hotel. The Hotel has a very convenient placement and is easy to access from the Jeju Airport. The rooms are clean and warm also the reception staff was very helpful with any questions I had. I would definitely recommend this place.

I love this place! I was here only for a couple of days but I had such a good stay. The Hotel and especially the rooms were really nice. Everything was clean and the beds were comfortable to sleep in. The staff was also really friendly. I would definitely come here again and even stay for longer!

The men at reception who helped me to check in is really nice! He is so helpful and talkative. Through chatting with him during my 5-night stay here I learned many fascinating facts regarding on S.Korea and made my journey in Jeju even more enjoyable!:)
Nice spacious rooms, good amenities. Location is great with its proximity to the airport and close to many restaurants. It was the best hotel i stayed in on Jeju island.

This hotel is absolutely perfect; I've never had a better stay. The rooms are excellent; the downstairs public space is extremely convenient; the staff are professional, generous and open. The location is also good. Perfect!

reviews.text: Rooms good and price is good and location is better. But the thing is that the towels are too small only for men. Have to use 3 towels to dry my long hair haha..

Building generally feels old with chipped walls, especially the bathroom. That said, for the price I think the location is good near the airport. The building isn’t oceanfront though, so don’t expect ocean views. There is no hotel provided airport shuttle, so be prepared to hail a cab.
Super basic room which didn’t have air conditioning unless during summer periods. Good for the price and location though

Ok for a one night sleep.

Close to airport, but in no case by foot.

Definitely need to take a taxi. If you don't find one on Uber and you don't have the local app, ask someone from Nice to CU to help you.

Beautiful modern designed room, clean, but the bedding is not very comfy as the fabric is a bit rough. Next to the coast. Downside is there is no frequent bus to get to other locations. The reception working time is from 7am to 11pm

editorial_summary.overview: Streamlined rooms with city views in a contemporary hotel offering a bathhouse & a restaurant.

Astar Hotel.name: Astar Hotel

reviews.text:
This hotel is 10 minutes from the airport. There’s a CU store inside and two GS 25s a few blocks away.

The staff are exceptionally helpful and friendly.

Rooms are spacious (one Queen and a single bed in the room) and very clean. My bed was very comfortable.They provide lots of free drinking water daily. There’s a gym and a sauna available for an extra Won 10,000. The WIFI is amazing! 5 G.

It’s quiet and you can take a short taxi ride or walk to one of many of Jeju-si’s international restaurants from the Astar.

I’d happily stay here again.

The rooms are clean and the staff is friendly and also I enjoyed the breakfast but I think the rooms don't feel like a 4 star hotel and now that I know Jeju I'd also choose a different location as a tourist. It's a good hotel but was a bit under my expectations especially because I visited a 3 star hotel in korea that had much better rooms than this one.
Nice room, large and confortable bed, very helpful service. Nice buffet breakfast. Recommanded.
I would stay in this hotel in a heartbeat if I go back to Jeju. Just 10-15 min drive from Jeju Airport. Breakfast is amazing. Staff were accommodating.
Rooms are very clean, parking is free. Location is good.

reviews.text: The hotel rooms look quite old and worn, from carpet to furniture. The staff was helpful with answering questions, but during our check-in, we had to look/call a bit before someone came to the front desk and there was no bell for us to ring. Location is decent, as it's not too far from the open air market but still a bit of a walk from the waterfront.

Kind & cool staff...good location, the room located on back of main building was not recommended, if u want to look good window view and large room....that is almost same style as Toyoko Inn
Strolling around it, it good to visit Jeju central Catholic church for feel hisotry of Jeju. Opposites of the church entrance, it best place to release ur drunkn, hanover soup, Mipung Haejangguk

As an American, this hotel is horrible.
Starting with the rooms. The beds are just 2 spring boxes stacked on top of each other. No cushion. Very uncomfortable. The rooms and halls are filled with dirty old carpet. Nothing is upgraded. There are mosquitos in the hotel and rooms.
Also, we booked this hotel because it said that they had air conditioning. Upon entering the stuffy room, we called the front desk to tell them that the AC wasn’t working. They said they wouldn’t turn them on in the middle of the October heat. They control the AC. They told us to open the single window and offered us electric fans. We were left to sweat in our sleep for 3 nights. The front desk were nice and comfortable and definitely had their AC in the lobby.
The front desk/ customer service were the most unfriendliest and unhelpful during our stay in Korea.
We wanted the hotel to reserve a large taxi to accommodate 6 luggage bag, for the next morning. We explained that we needed a large, specifically. They told us to ask them the next morning. As nonresidents, we ourselves can’t reserve large taxis. The hotels have to.
When the next morning came. They told us the large taxis needed to be reserved the day before. So frustrating. They offered to order us 3 small taxis instead.

I wouldn’t recommend staying at the hotel for it being so old, refusal to allow the use of AC. Not listening for our request to reserve us a large taxi for the next day.

You couldn’t ask for more in terms of location coz it’s just a couple of meters away from the market, shopping street & other cafes. As for the rooms, it’s fair enough for the price & spacious for 3 & 4 beds with our big luggages

Good location and comfortable room at level 8

Near to bus stop

Provided towel, shower gel , soap, shampoo, mineral water but without toothpaste and toothbrush

Able to storage luggage at the lobby

reviews.text: The place Is so good, a lot people talk bad about It , but i dont think they are real travelers, i cant imagine them sleeping in the street or camping in any construction ,even in the beach. This place Is very good i recomended for people who  dont care if Is a old building, Is old yes , but Is clean, instalations good care, hot water, good wifi AND the mama boss Is very nice!!🙏🏼🥰

Hotel is very bad. Everywhere you can feel strong ugly sigarette smell. Beds are made up bad, thete are hair on the sheets. Ugly uncomfortable pillows. Furniture is very old and function not well. Towels were with the holes. It was impossible to open the window in the room. All is in bad condition

If you don’t wanna spend money much for accommodation. This hotel is great deal for you.
But I don’t recommend stay here in Summer. Because their air conditioner is poor and I don’t think it does works well.

They provide Free Wi-fi(It’s not special in korea)

Room condition...? Fair enough.

Staffs are very friendly and kindness.

Aweful. We arrived at 6pm just to see the staff in the middle of "cleaning". Didnt seem to be efficient at all, the floor was dirty with leftover of food, the room smelled cigarette, the curtain full of stains, the furnitures damaged, one light completely destroyed and falling from the ceiling, the flush of the toilet constantly running, the bathtub clogged...this hotel is just good if you want to shoot a horror movie.
But at least they have wifi
Dirty and very old. I checked out after one day even though I paid in advance for 2 days with no refund.

reviews.text: The room was good, BUT there's NO amenities, even toothbrush, toothpaste, hair brush no one, it's horrible just 2 bottle of water available on the refrigerator.. I expected a lot so that's why I didn't bring my personal belongings...BUT...ugh!! On my own opinion they actually done that so that their customer will buy in the convince store at the first floor,which is MAYBE the owner franchised that store. Terrible,ugh..

I have lived in motels with better service. There's no coffee or tea in the room, no toiletries provided, the comforter and curtains are torn. These are all ofcourse aesthetics and luxuries, but one would think a hotel of this stature would provide better.

more like 2.5-star hotel. stingy and lacks many things

odd how this property was able to earn 4-star grading.  it looks ok from outside being 17 stories high and all but lacks so many things inside.

sneaky marketing with room types.  they advertise deluxe double rooms with balcony are all "sold out" when in fact they are sold as 'regular' superior double; when you check in, you will be told all superior double rooms come with balcony and the truth is rooms are TINY because the balcony dimensions are factored into the room size.  i would recommend not booking their 'superior double'.  these double rooms are also facing tall building in the front and has NO view.  try the back side instead, it's got at least open view.

lacks many things:  no coffee in the room.  no sofa. no other usual complimentary amenities and so on; mostly for purchase.  this, not a deal breaker but not 4-star graded hotel's offerings either.

the most annoying thing is the sensored lighting by the entrance/bathroom.  it turns on every time you go to the bathroom.  (if you and your partner never go to bathroom in the middle of the night, u should be ok though.)  anyhow, asked the maintenance team to temporarily turn it off during my stay but they weren't able.

no a/c turned on in the hallway and inside the elevators stating it's not hot enough yet.  well it's end of june and bus turns on a/c and their restaurants turn on a/c.

housekeeping asked if it is ok not to clean the room and just exchange towels.  well...

breakfast was not worth paying for much.  in particular, the only type of eggs offered was scrambled but even that was  mixed in some cream sauce. (no other protein source.)  all else very simple like coffee, milk, rice, soup, and toast.  cheaper better alternatives just a few steps outside.
Hotel was good. Except the restroom was so poor ....can’t close the door all the time
Hotel is new when i stayed. Breakfast was horrible but the room was very spacious. Location was the best feature.

reviews.text: Nice location. Old but renovated hotel. Very Good environment. Clean room and provide daily requirements for stay such as towel and razer

Was slightly apprehensive reading some of the reviews to extent that I nearly cancelled. However staying there I found the location fantastic near dongmun market, black pork street, olive young, issac toast. The rooms were slightly small but functional. Staff could be more present. I preferred this to my other hotel in jeju
Fantastic location. Nostalgic japanese style Inn. For the price u pay, definitely worth it.

Beware that this hotel is much smaller, unprofessional, and more dingy than it appears in their photos. We were promised a room size of 23 square metres but estimated our room at around 15 square metres. There was barely space to walk around after opening one medium-large sized luggage. The room was slightly run down and was not fully clean.

Hotel is a lot more run down than expected. Stairs are unrenovated, unsafe, and fenced off. We were looking for extra towels and found spare towels, bottles, and other room laundry was thrown on on the floor in a dirty and dusty storage closet.

The hotel front desk is typically not staffed. Instead they have the person manning their cafe double up as hotel staff, which means it is hard to get help during cafe operating hours. Staff barely spoke English and did not seem happy to help.

Location was okay, with reasonable amenities and food around. Parking took some time to find, on a one-way street that required a big loop behind the hotel, but was not a big complaint.

Giving them 1 star for the dishonesty, false marketing, and undeserved high prices.
Hotel at great location to access all shopping area nearby.

reviews.text: Clean and straightforward rooms that offer essential amenities. However, note that there are no dining options available at the hotel, requiring guests to dine out for all meals.

Please don't stay over night here! It was one of the worst day ever. There was a super big cockroach crawling inside the room, smell of urine came from the sewage in the batroom. It's a very low-quality hotel, even though, they got me paid the similar cost compare to a nice hotel in downtown.
Came with SCT cycle tour, Clean rooms
Very kind hotel during bike riding with reasonable price.
You get what you pay for
Good

I have traveled a lot in Korea this is the first time I have come across such a dirty hotel, we stayed 3 nights we never met anyone working in the hotel. The room is dirty, there were even cockroaches in the bathroom and a dead cockroach at the entrance to our room. To avoid

There is a large E-Mart right in front and a GS convenience store.
Dongmun Market is about a 20-minute walk away.
The cost-effectiveness and location are good, and except for the fact that there is no elevator, the bed is nice and soft!
I definitely plan to visit again next time!!

Cheap is expensive.  I really want to save 10,000 won

I hated myself for staying here.

Living, living, sleeping in lodgings

I had vivid nightmares because of the atmosphere of that facility...

This is an inexpensive and cost-effective accommodation.
This is the perfect accommodation for single or two people.

Maro Hostel & Lounge.adr_address: 5 Donggwang-ro 21-gil, Ildo 2(i)-dong, Cheju, Jeju-do 63253, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Simple quarters in a warm, hip hostel with a shared kitchenette, a dining area & free DIY breakfast.

Maro Hostel & Lounge.formatted_address: 5 Donggwang-ro 21-gil, Ildo 2(i)-dong, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Maro Hostel & Lounge.name: Maro Hostel & Lounge

reviews.text: It's a little bit away from the main street, we had to Take the bus to the main street. The room is very good, small but very clean. And the price is very cheap, but quality is very good. I'm so impressed to the generous breakfast. They provide free eggs, ham, salad, toast, milk juice and cereal, its the generous hostel when I was in Jeju.
We had a great stay for 3 nights, host spoke good English and was able to assist us alot. Would highly recommend it to non korean speakers. Thanks again Su and Hubby.

Very nice service by the staff. Good location in the middle of Jeju city with quite a lot of convenience store, bakery and other shops nearby. Near to bus stop.
They provide free breakfast and a dedicated cooking tools for Muslims that are pork free.
Really nice hostel. Love lounge zone - it is great designed and have big library. you could get free breakfast. Rooms clean but we have some delay in changing bed linen
Very nice place, great price. The rooms are okay, the staff is very helpful and friendly. Very close to the Jeju Intercity bus terminal by bus.

We chose Sakura Hotel based on price and location. The room itself was clean and spacious. The hotel is a bit dated, but they did renovate the rooms fairly recently it seems. The elevator was smaller than average. It fits 4-6 people, and this was with me breathing on the person in front of me. The tv was a good size tv as well, which made for good late night tv watching. The bathroom was also clean and thankfully toilet paper could be flushed down the toilet. I found this to be an issue in some places in Jeju.
The location is close to many big grocery shopping centers. Air conditioning worked plenty fine and cooled our room nicely. They provided 2 mix coffee sticks of Maxim coffee with hot water boiler. The staff was friendly and allowed us to check in a little early as we arrived a bit early, initially to just drop off our bags.

A place to go for cost-effectiveness.
Although it is old, it is optimized for washing and sleeping.
The surrounding infrastructure is good

It is a place with good value for money.

It's quite clean and much cheaper than nearby hotels.
It's not a bad facility at a reasonable price. I recommend it.
Good location, cheap and clean

Pearl Tourist Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63136, Jeju-do, Cheju, 연동 277-2
Pearl Tourist Hotel.name: Pearl Tourist Hotel

reviews.text: Located a mere 0.7 km to Yeondong Choong-ang Church, this 3-star Pearl Tourist Hotel Jeju offers 24-hour front desk assistance, a hairdresser and a laundry ..
building is a little old but interior is still elegant and comfortable. very economical and close to city and plenty of restaurants in marugori 👌👌👌
Great hotel with breakfast and parking space if you need it. Great location. A lot of shops and restaurants around. Not far from airport.
Rooms sees spacious in pics but not very big. Also double bed  seems bit smaller than expected. I have taken 4 person room, but slippers and cups were for only two people
Good place to stay during Jeju holidays. Convenient location, good food (breakfast), pretty good rooms.

Top Island.adr_address: 47 Yongnam 1-gil, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do 63174, South Korea
Top Island.formatted_address: 47 Yongnam 1-gil, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Top Island.name: Top Island

reviews.text: Visited as an overnight stay between flights, there's plenty of food nearby but weather conditions were bad and so many stores closed early. Greeted warmly by a lovely lady at the front desk, whom had tried to call us earlier to confirm if we were arriving (no other hotels did this). We tried to order fried chicken but had many difficulties (no Korean number, etc.) so we asked the receptionist for help. He (night shift receptionist) humourously and kindly engaged with us, helping us get our orders through the app on his phone. Overall, service was excellent for a 2 star hotel. The room toilet had an old design but was warm and spacious. The table was small for 4 people, so we ate chicken while sat on the floor. Beds were clean and smelt fresh. Cozy place with their own self-service convenience store and free coffee and tea all at the reception area.
super
Nothing to complain

It's a good hotel. It's clean. I don't have laundry, but there's a self-laundry near the intersection, so it's okay. There's a convenience store and a restaurant nearby, but I couldn't experience it because I had a busy schedule... I could walk there while looking around from the airport, and it's near the cherry blossom street, so I was able to go to see it comfortably. Dongmun Market is about 1,6 to 1,8 km away, so you can easily get there by walking or taking a bus. If you're not good at exercising, it might be a bit difficult...

Cost-effective accommodation at Jeju Airport. I hesitated because the price was quite cheap (around 40,000 won. There are only a few places cheaper than this accommodation, including Mix Hotel), but in the end, I decided it was the best choice.

The advantage is
1. The accommodation is clean
Although it is an older accommodation, it is very neatly maintained.
Bedding is also clean.
2. There is a coffee machine and ice maker.
There is a coffee machine and ice maker with Starbucks coffee beans. I can't stress enough the need for an ice maker until midwinter arrives. I'm very satisfied.
3. There is a store on the first floor.
A store with prices that are not much different from nearby convenience stores. Also, there is a Hangang Ramen machine, so it's great for appeasing an hungry stomach. However, it is cheaper to buy alcoholic beverages at convenience store events.
4. The staff are friendly
The staff are friendly. Is this the most important part? Accommodation image changes

The downside is
1. There is not enough parking space
There is not enough parking space, so you have to park nearby or park in a public parking lot. However, with so many advantages, the disadvantages seem minor.

Willing to visit again. I think I'll be going again soon.
For those of you who are thinking about comparing it to Mi x Hotel, definitely choose Top Island.

Jeju Raon Hotel & Resort.adr_address: 127 Geumneungnam-ro, Hallim-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do 63015, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Refined property offering indoor pools, a spa & a restaurant, plus tennis & basketball courts.

Jeju Raon Hotel & Resort.formatted_address: 127 Geumneungnam-ro, Hallim-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Jeju Raon Hotel & Resort.name: Jeju Raon Hotel & Resort

reviews.text: Price of the hotel was way too good to be true for its location. This hotel is tired and needs a major update. Seems like the management is not interested in investing money to make the rooms look nice or offer good service as you will always find 1 front desk person at the desk who's busy checking in guests and playing other roles.  If you decide to stay at this hotel, I recommend signing up for breakfast buffet. Food is excellent, and the lady who looks after the hall is absolutely amazing 👏

It's difficult to rate all the areas of this hotel at once. I could give the stars for each facility and at the end it would be a 3 star average.
Bad experience at the swimming pool. Dog poop behind lounge chair at indoor swimming pool. It had been there some time but it was more improtant to stop us from swimming with no hat than cleaning the dog poop! There was no sign that a hat was required and they did not inform us a head covering was required to swim until we were already walking into the water. Another Korean guest helped translate and they blamed us because we don't speak Korean, yet a Korean/English speaker helped us at the desk when we paid and the cap was not mentioned! So we had to pay to rent swimming caps for our heads.
No breakfast included which should be for this kind of hotel and these prices.
Rooms spacious, nice but worn out (not updated for a long time)
Bathroom is the best :)
For the price there should have been included amenities, but there were none.
Great experience here. Very nice room, comfortable at a great rate when we stayed (Early March). 7/11 was open until 10pm and staff was friendly. Was perfect for what we wanted on our stay.

Nice hotel. Decent, spacious rooms and very friendly staff. Due to a mix up at check-in resulting from language difficulties they gave me free tickets to the pool, the Ma Park horse show, the zoo and gokarting which I thought was very generous. For this reason I couldn’t give any less than 5 stars. The free airport shuttle is very convenient as it’s about an hour away. You can walk to the beach in less than half an hour and it’s safe to do so. The breakfast was ok, but it’s quite Korean, no pastries. I would certainly recommend this hotel, especially if you want to play golf.

It's  a little shabby and out of the way, but it's ends up being good value for money if you're planning on exploring the neighborhood near Jeju Brewing Co.!  Wifi didn't work during my stay although I got a good signal.  Hotel staff were at a loss to solve my problem, likely due to my non-existent Korean and their limited English.  You'll have to bear this in mind if staying anywhere other than Jeju-shi or Jeju City.   English ability drops off quite a bit once you leave the city center.

Renaissance Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63176, Jeju-do, Cheju, 삼도1동 531
Renaissance Hotel.name: Renaissance Hotel

reviews.text: It seems to be that the hotel is already running out of business. They shutdown the electricity from 12 afternoon till 3 pm. There is no one in the reception for 24 hours. The bathroom has a funky smell the moment we arrive. There is no bidet, the towels provided are too small. We booked a toom for three and was provided by one pillow per person. I dnt recommend the hotel at all to anyone.
Excellent attention, the facade is what can be improved but! The interior is renovated and it is worth it :3

I won the room where the remote control is difficult to press.
When I asked to change it, they just told me to press hard.
I have a Netflix hotel account, but they say it's fully booked or won't work well on weekends haha...
Location is good.

I really like it here. Unlike the exterior that looks old, the interior has been completely remodeled and is very clean. And there is a huge TV. The floor was not carpeted, but made of flooring-like material. When I checked in, I was given a disposable toothbrush, toothpaste, and razor. It's a quick bus ride from the airport, and it's great for eating Hyotoe Meat Noodles for breakfast. The downside is that the amenities are not disposable, the slippers are reusable, and there don't seem to be many parking spaces. I don't think there's really anywhere that can come close to this price. It would be nice to just watch a movie on a big TV.

AEWOL STAY in Jeju.adr_address: South Korea, 63049, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Aewol-eup, Aewolhaean-ro, 708 KR
AEWOL STAY in Jeju.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Aewol-eup, Aewolhaean-ro, 708 KR
AEWOL STAY in Jeju.name: AEWOL STAY in Jeju

reviews.text:
Abundant parking. Hotel is right in front of the volcanic rock beach and within walking distance from several eateries and cafes.

Our family deluxe room had 2 bedrooms and 1 living room. Bottled water was provided. Our request for extra pillows was fulfilled. We declined room cleaning on the second day and the staff kindly left extra towels, replacement water and tissue handing on our door handle - - this was a pleasant surprise.

Feels like there was another woman in my room.  Fresh cup marks on my table and long hairs on my shower head. Amazing experience with so many mosquitoes....feels like sleeping in the Amazon... Good for you!

I'm from the US and currently on a family trip to Jeju. On our first day, we stayed at Aewol Stay. The manager was fantastic – they upgraded our room when they found out we had daughters. The room was impeccably clean and had everything we needed for a perfect family vacation. I absolutely loved our stay at Aewol, and the fact that there's a great Korean BBQ restaurant just a 2-minute walk away, along with a quiet gift shop, made it even better. If you're planning a visit to Jeju, I wholeheartedly recommend Aewol Stay!!!!! Two thumbs up 👍👍
Very clean hotel with very hospitable staff. It was a very fine accomodation for my family. We will stay again in the future👍
A good location, nice rooms and service and on-top of it all professional level facilities.

CJ Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63207, Jeju-do, Cheju, 이도2동 광양8길24
CJ Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 이도2동 광양8길24
CJ Hotel.name: CJ Hotel

reviews.text: I've been there a few times while traveling to Jeju, and it's clean and quiet for the price. The room has a balcony, probably because it was remodeled from a studio apartment. You can see Hallasan Mountain in the distance from the balcony, and there are many restaurants and movie theaters nearby, and public transportation is also convenient.

It was remodeled and clean, but the bathroom was very small. Bathing fee was 7,000 won. Credit card accepted.
It's so small it's frustrating
There is a men’s sauna in an inexpensive motel-like accommodation.
This place has a great view of the beach.
not too bad. No promotions at all.

Jeju Sky Resort.adr_address: 3794 Gwideok-ri, Hallim-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do 63024, South Korea
Jeju Sky Resort.formatted_address: 3794 Gwideok-ri, Hallim-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Jeju Sky Resort.name: Jeju Sky Resort

reviews.text: Rooms are comfortable and adequate, the rooms were quiet and clean. The rooms is nice and the staff are also very friendly and helpful.I thoroughly enjoyed my stay here.
Best accomodation. Nearest with tourist top spot

A slightly remote hotel with a large parking lot and some free bread and coffee on the first floor, which taste pretty good.

I booked a sea view room but it was so foggy that I couldn’t even see it. The bed was a little hard but I thought it was quite comfortable. There was mineral water in the refrigerator and the hot water was very stable. The floor was heated and cool. The most important thing is that it also has an attached adapter which is very considerate. Overall Very comfortable and cost-effective~
It's cheap, there are a lot of customers, and it's nice to take the bus along Ilju Road, but there's nothing around.

This is a cost-effective accommodation. Considering the price, I was very satisfied. There were two beds and the bathroom was clean. The palm trees outside the window looked cool and nice. There was no elevator, but it wasn't that inconvenient since it was a second floor room. I thought the parking lot was small compared to the number of rooms, but parking is possible without any inconvenience. It is located between Gwakji Beach and Hyeopjae. It's 7-8 minutes from Hyeopjae Beach. The location is good. The staff are also friendly.

Nice place, but quite a ways outside of town. The room was clean and WiFi was fast. The bus stop is only a 5 minute walk down the street.

Oddly, the card swipe on the door is crazy loud and alerts the whole floor you are entering your room.
The facilities are convenient and my room is spacious. More importantly, I love the sunset sea view from my window! I will never forget how beautiful it is for the rest of my life.
Nice ocean view at cheap price. Service are good but not soo good.. The rooms are neat amd hot floor is available just in case if you are visiting during winter..
Location is fine, ocean is just across the road but there are not many shops and restaurants in this area. Good for a budget stay. Room was clean and airy.

Waaaaah哇哇... I Can't say a word about this hotel and the owner oh my god ... he is really nice, kind and helpful ...let me tell you our situation.

Our flight was in the early morning and we booked for this hotel on harry because it's near to Jeju airport 4 km (8 minutes) by car, we slept and in 6:00 a.m we wanted to go to the airport buuuut there is No taxi ... And it was raining alot ..he called a taxi for us and treated us so good ... And room was an Ocean view 😍😍😍　i totally recommend this hotel

Cordelia Resort.adr_address: 941-1 Ojo-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63640, South Korea
Cordelia Resort.formatted_address: 941-1 Ojo-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Cordelia Resort.name: Cordelia Resort

reviews.text: A bit shabby but ok for the price they charge. It’s places like this that allow you to save some won when traveling around South Korea. If you’re not focused on facility quality but rather just a place to sleep and shower while running around all day, this will work great.

Dirty, smelly, uncomfortable pillows, heating did not work well, there were a lot of mosquitoes in the room even though we did not open a window, there was only one working outlet next to beds, dirty windows and mirrors. Definitely too expensive for such a low quality place
Not clean, ac does not work, pool is closed even though it is 40c outside. Room is dark and shabby. Not worth the money.
Very clean, very reasonably priced. The room had an excellent bathtub and the beds were comfortable. The pool was also very nice!

There are corona infected people found in Jeju Ireland. So we called this hotel to cancel our reservation. However the hotel manager didn't help us. they've charged full whole week amounts from us. it is not nice of their business. let others know if something happen before your trip, this hotel don't allow you to cancel your reservations. and they will charge full amounts. no negotiations and no half credit anything.

At noon Hotel.Ltd.adr_address: South Korea, 63124, Jeju-do, Cheju, 제주도 제주시 연동 292-30 제주도 제주시 은남1길 8호
At noon Hotel.Ltd.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 제주도 제주시 연동 292-30 제주도 제주시 은남1길 8호
At noon Hotel.Ltd.name: At noon Hotel.Ltd

reviews.text: Small rooms resembling a love hotel. Good for the price and it does the job. Be warned there is no desk in the rooms and the sink is next to the beds not in the bathroom. Didn't try the breakfast.
The reception can speak good English and helpful. The room is clean and stylish

First of all, the location is in downtown Jeju, so it's pretty good for going out for drinks, and it's close to the airport, so it's convenient. The rooms overall are not spacious, but are clean. I stayed for 2 nights for a business trip and was satisfied with it.

The room condition, facilities, and accessibility are good for the price. There are rooms with and without a terrace, so you can choose and reserve according to your preference.

When parking all day, you have to give your room number and leave your car keys, and there is plenty of parking space.

There are many places to eat nearby, so it's easy to walk to.

Marevo Beach Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63034, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Aewol-eup, Gwakji-ri, 23 1565-18
Marevo Beach Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Aewol-eup, Gwakji-ri, 23 1565-18
Marevo Beach Hotel.name: Marevo Beach Hotel

reviews.text:
Double room with sea-view. Pleasant friendly check in at 4pm. Room layout better than expected after reading negative reviews.

Room overlooks dilapidated park camping area and beach public car park. AC has no cooling mode which makes sleeping difficult. Reception refuses to hand over the AC remote control.

Opposite the hotel is the teenager operated Wasup Beach House Bar that blasts outside music to an empty street and zero patrons until midnight.

Hotel has no food offering except some pastries and cake options with plastic samples on display at reception.

Eh, the hotel had a kind of nice vibe, but a bit worn out in places.  A good view of the beach.  But the bed was horrible; the springs were poking through, wobbled all over, and I could barely sleep.  Definitely too pricey for that :(

Location is great.
Room is just OK
Stay here if you don't expect  nice hotel.
Nice view. Somewhat close to the beach.
Real beach hotel and a clean room.

Hotel W Shinjeju.adr_address: 42 Eunnam 4-gil, Cheju, Jeju-do 690-814, South Korea
Hotel W Shinjeju.name: Hotel W Shinjeju

reviews.text: Spacious and lots of restaurants around
clean and kind service, close to downtown
Nice and clean
good

Looking at the facilities alone, the hotel is said to be inferior to new motels.
However, it is located in the center of Nuwemaru Street, the center of Yeondong, so there is a geographical advantage when visiting this area.
The distance to the airport is also close.
The bed was uncomfortable and the room condition was so-so.
It was spacious and spacious, so I didn't feel stuffy, which was nice.
Except for the major hotels nearby, everything is the same.
In terms of cost-effectiveness, it still seems to be top-tier in the area.
Overall, the deterioration of nearby hotels is serious.

Design and the layout of the room is vintage and Korean style. Clean and well organized. Jacuzzi was a nice amenity. The pool was not accessible in the month of May. There are cafes, restaurants, and convenient stores in walking distance. Gentlemen at the front desk was not very helpful accommodating guest from abroad.

There is a spa jacuzzi for period reservations only, and I really liked the wood-toned interior and the cleanliness. Everything else was good, but the resort was located too far inside, so it was quite far to get to other places, so I had to use a call taxi or a rental car. It was a shame. Yes.

The pool water was murky, there were wasps, and the cooking utensils were dirty so I couldn't use them, but the overall rooms were clean, the beds were spacious, there were two TVs, and there was a jacuzzi, so it was great to watch TV. Still, it was a decent accommodation.
But it's a bit disappointing that the water isn't very clean.

24.6.6 It is located next to Jeju Airport and is easily accessible.
It's a partial ocean view, so it's great value for money. There's a bidet and the bed is good.

Cozy resort next to Jeju Airport
It is located in Eoyeong Village and has everything you need, including a walk around Yongduam Rock and Paul Basset. It is quiet and nice.

\uc774\ud638\ub9ac\uc870\ud2b8.formatted_address: 295-1 Iho 1(il)-dong, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
