reviews.text:
The owner is very kind.
The room was also ondol, so my back was very warm.
The owner is friendly and the facilities are good.
Too bad for the price. The name is a resort, but the content is like an inn.
Various rooms and facilities Parking lot
The owner is very kind.

Hotel Fine Jeju.adr_address: 87 Chilsimni-ro, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63596, South Korea
Hotel Fine Jeju.formatted_address: 87 Chilsimni-ro, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Hotel Fine Jeju.name: Hotel Fine Jeju

reviews.text: Great value for the price. The room was spacious and enjoyable. We had a faulty bathroom door and the staff was very nice and accommodating. We got a free upgrade which was very much appreciated. Recommend!!
The junior suite is very clean and spacious. It looks like a new hotel. The receptionist, Miss Jang, is very helpful and helped us to order food in during a heavy downpour :)

Great place!
Has clean rooms and comfortable beds!
Breakfast buffet is good too!
Good price!
Very clean and comfortable. Location is good. Staff is friendly. Breakfast ist absolute okay.
Was staying on level 8, the room is not very big. 2 mid size luggage cannot be open together. However, the room was sufficiently furnished. It was a comfortable stay

Aimi Jeju Beach Hotel.adr_address: 474 Johamhaean-ro, Cheju, 63333, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Down-to-earth hotel featuring free parking, a restaurant & a rooftop deck with sea views.

Aimi Jeju Beach Hotel.name: Aimi Jeju Beach Hotel

reviews.text: We overall had a good experience. The check-in and checkout was very smooth and we received good service when needed. Their parking is a 3 minute walk to the hotel, so be mindful if walking is an issue. They also don't provide laundry services so we had to walk a few minutes to a very good, but pricey (~ $10), laundry service. The rooms were clean and met our basic needs. They although went in our room when we put a do not disturb sign. Nothing was stolen but we wouldn't have expected them to go in.

Poor service front desk officer, never great customer never say thank you. He always not on his desk when we want to look for him (for check out enquiries and etc) book a seaview room but was assigned a room next to the cafe. The bathtub was facing the cafe and the curtain of the bathroom does not cover full. The bed was very uncomfortable. Why does it still counted as 4 stars hotel???? Will not recommend for this hotel in Jeju to anyone.

This hotel was AMAZING for a weekend getaway. The location is right on the beach, far enough away from the busy bars to be quiet, but close enough to walk to them if that is your thing. The room was small to be honest, but was clean. I wasn't in Jeju to stay in the hotel though. The restaurant had a breakfast buffet that was pretty good and an excellent value.

This hotel is at a great location! Right on the beach and on a strip of good restaurants. Room was a little dirty and there was no hot water so that was the only negatives. But it was so hot, it didn’t matter much to not have hot water and we would definitely recommend! The staff was very pleasant and there was free beer every night. There is also a nice hill nearby for hiking. One of the best places we stayed at in Jeju

(Family room for 6 people) there are not many charging stations around the room. The bathroom floor is always wet. The room is clean, some furniture stuffs are old and need repair. This hotel has free beer from 6pm -10pm and the beer was really good. Worth the money!!!

Location was very good, the room was very clean. But the sound isolation is a little bit weak. Those leaving early in the morning wake up the whole building 😅 I am exaggerating, but I could hear the whole talk on the room next to mine. Apart from that, the bed was very comfy and toiletries were good quality too.

Floor not very well swept when I arrived. No kettle. No bath towels. Only hand towels. On the plus side,  wooden trellised wall hooks. Arrangement of single and double beds is good. Has a lift. Near to convenience and eating places. Near to laundry. General cleanliness acceptable.

It's a decent place to stay in Jeju for a lower cost but the service was a bit lacking. Front end employee is gone quite often from the front, and no early check ins allowed even though we were only there 15 minutes early was a bit disappointing.
Simple hotel with very good amenities. The staff changes your towels every day.
Yes very nice place to stay

Hostel Lyndon.adr_address: 278 Seogwang-ro, Ido 2(i)-dong, Cheju, Jeju-do 63207, South Korea
Hostel Lyndon.formatted_address: 278 Seogwang-ro, Ido 2(i)-dong, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Hostel Lyndon.name: Hostel Lyndon

reviews.text: Terrible bunk mattress was no.1 problem. All the 4 mattress in my bunk bed room kept making uncomfortable sound all night which made people in the room wake continuaslly.  Also, staff here speak loud in the hallway.  Facial towel is not provided enough so if you are late to ask towel as soon as you check in, nobody cares if you get towel. You have to ask towel and hair blower. Nobody cares about you because the staff is like customer not manager. Plus the basic thing, Room and bathroom floor was dirty nothing was neat and tidy here.

Lovely quest house, feels like home. Daily movie nights and also you can get snacks at the hostel too. Friendly youtful staff who speaks english. I was a bit confused at first because I didin't read info given in KakaoTalk (translate it from korean).

This hotel has the nice vibe. The staffs are friendly and helpful, on the top of that They speak English well. And they have utensil for Muslim only, so don't be afraid your food will mixed with non-halal food. The room and common room are nice. I will definitely book it again. #muslimfriendlyhostel #jejuisland

Can be say no breakfast at all..  they claimed that bf is at 8 until 9am only. the staff take out the bread and a bottle of orange juice at 8am and 10min later it all finish. If u ask for more thier staff will stand by ur side and make sure u only take 1 pc only.
On my third day of staying there while im cooking my instant noodle. The staff keep coming to the kitchen  with a bad face ( hellloo maron u stated  that u provide a kitchen that can be use) why the staff keep busy in the kitchen eat here and there.. let the guest have their on space la..
I felt cheated by lyndon hostel i booked 2 queen room for 3nights stay.  On the website stated that there will a "HALAL untensil" but when i ask the staff the " make a drama" like oh really.. no such thing..

No kettle in the room so need to go downstair to get a drink or hot water..
My 1st room is oky.. but the 2nd room is WITHOUT A TV.. can u imagine A hotel room without a tv. So poor service .

Also No bath towel provided.
Only a small face towel, and you must request from the staff

Overall is all bad. Espcially the staff is busying wih thier on agenda. In the kitchen all drawer is label with a "for staff.." for staff.. here and the all fot staff..
Then u should closed down and open hostel for ur staff only.
I mixed well with other guess ..and they feel the same too. They seem surprising that no breakfast after 8.59am.  The staff already standing next to you to take the PLAIN SANDWICH BREAD and put into the " STAFF DRAWER" ..
This is the worst hotel in this entire world.
Im taking your hotel room..not your sharing dorm.
And im buying my own bread and eggs for my other 3 family member.

Cozy and Comfy place. There won't be nice window views. But for the prices and service they provide it's a heaven for budget travelers.  Guest house, Private rooms and Hostel are the options. Breakfast can be prepared yourself using the kitchen facilities.

Urban Island.adr_address: South Korea, 63124, Jeju-do, Cheju, 연동 292-27

editorial_summary.overview: Warmly furnished rooms in an informal hotel offering a cafe & complimentary Wi-Fi.

Urban Island.name: Urban Island

reviews.text:
Budget hotel. Room was okay for the price.  Total for 3 nights was the cost for 1 night in other hotels we saw. There was a piece of trash when we entered the room (lint remover sheet). Must’ve dropped by the housekeeping. The door doesn’t close properly if not pushed so keep in mind!

Lots of restaurants near the hotel. There’s bus stop in front too. Good location.

TV had Netflix, Youtube, but DisneyPlus cannot be opened. They don’t have bath towels, only hand towels. There was “Towels” in the amenities listed in Agoda sure but not the large ones. So better to bring your own. Shampoo, conditioner, shower gel, hand soap, and toothpaste, hair blower are available. Light in the bathroom has a timer so it turns off even when you’re still inside. The trash cans inside the room and bathroom are small. Didn’t like the robes. It was itchy when I tried to wear it.

Staff are okay. Sometimes there’s no staff in the front desk so you have to wait a while if you need something. They can speak basic English.
Nice, comfortable rooms, good service (better have your personal towel, cuz their re very small)
Good rooms, nice location, friendly staff
Nice single room for 50€ per night with breakfast, which is only ok
Good location with  cozy ambience

Charlie Hotel.adr_address: 128 Seosa-ro, Cheju, Jeju-do 63183, South Korea
Charlie Hotel.name: Charlie Hotel

reviews.text:
This centrally located budget hotel in Jeju City offers a pleasant and convenient stay. I highly value this hotel for its simplicity, cleanliness, and the friendly nature of its staff.

The room is well-equipped with all the essentials for a budget-friendly and business-oriented stay, all at an affordable price.

Additionally, its proximity to various city attractions and a mere 10-minute drive from the airport adds to its convenience.

There is a wide selection of restaurants and convenient stores in the vicinity, making it even more convenient for guests. Choose this hotel for a budget-friendly stay that provides excellent value for your money."

Average hotel, only advantage I felt is price is less.
The location is okay not good, this is a bit far and there are no good restaurants nearby
Rooms and bathroom are big in size.
But overall old, no view from the room.  Reception is available till late night.
Smoking smell was coming in the corridors.
A water cooler is available in the reception area.

Consider as last option, better to check other options first.

Very nice hotel. Big spacious rooms, netflix TVs, fridge, big bathrooms and plenty of hot water.

Enjoyed our stay here and its a short walk from the Jeju bus terminal too which is useful to get around the island.

Pleasant stay, very conveniently located.

The staff is really really kind and will help you if you need anything. Plus the location is really great, there's a lot of bus around which goes to the airport and everywhere around Jeju-do. There's some restaurants really good around and it's near the beach. Unfortunately the room smells a little weird and if you go out of you room a little bit late it will not be cleaned.

But I recommend it :)
I stayed in a room for 2 people, with 1 bathroom with both a bathtub and a shower.  The room is quite large, comfortable, convenient, located near the center,

\uac00\uae4c\uc774\uc5d0\ud30c\ub3c4\uc1.adr_address: 1972-1 Oedo 2(i)-dong, Cheju, Jeju-do 63068, South Korea
\uac00\uae4c\uc774\uc5d0\ud30c\ub3c4\uc1.name: 가까이에파도소리

reviews.text: Property is located just on the edge of a beautiful shoreline. Peaceful and serene surroundings. The place is a little run down and best described as managed in a sparsely manner. No housekeeping services and no full time staff at the reception counter.

I took the most expensive room and had one room.
The waves rolling in the sea in front of the pension were dynamic.

The location is so deceptive. The sea is right in front of the room and there is nothing blocking the view, so the view is great. It's a shame that the cleaning was a bit unkempt, the bedding was old, and there was no elevator, but the view made up for it. The layout had a strong studio feel, so it was a house I wanted to live in for a month, cleaning the bathroom with bleach and buying bedding. There are hardly any convenience stores or shopping malls nearby, so it's a good idea to prepare what you need in advance.

There are no nearby amenities, but considering that Jeju Island itself is a place where you can travel by car, it is really good value for money. are you okay. You can't get a room like this for this price.

It was nice because it was an accommodation where you could see the waves right in front of Cheolseok.
It's old and lacks facilities, but I think it's a good place to take a break.

Golden Tulip Hotel Jeju Seongsan.adr_address: 329-1 Goseong-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63641, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Chic rooms in a modern hotel offering a restaurant & sea views, plus a rooftop deck with a pool.

Golden Tulip Hotel Jeju Seongsan.formatted_address: 329-1 Goseong-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Golden Tulip Hotel Jeju Seongsan.name: Golden Tulip Hotel Jeju Seongsan

reviews.text: The tandem bike  in the entrance is not for rent - a classic, yet failed attempt to misuse one of humanity's most util inventions as a decorative prop. With most machinery already spending most of their time stored away in dark cupboards or garages, I am deeply dissapointed that after multiple attempts to use the bike (as its purpose dictates), I had to find out that this tool, too, will remain unused until the end of time. Otherwise the hotel was good 👍

Hotel with a good location to visit Udo Island. The room is functional, highlighting the bathroom that seemed renovated. The mattress needs a renovation. The roof top with the pool is very nice to take a bath.

Decent bargain! Very nice breakfast with a good selection. Located just off the road to the Seongsan tourist beach area. A few bus stops away. Walkable - about half hour to 40 mins. The room is small, with a shower. Very nice heated toilet!
Good location to access many attractions in Sungsan. Not bad but dont expect too much.
"Compact yet nicely renovated rooms. Convenient location with easy access to Sunrise Mountain, nearby convenience stores, and a range of dining options."

Cutie Pie Hotel.adr_address: 610 Aewolhaean-ro, Cheju, Jeju-do 63047, South Korea
Cutie Pie Hotel.name: Cutie Pie Hotel

reviews.author_name: Garry Lew Your Estate Advisory Realtor
reviews.text:
🇰🇷 Visited 07/12/2023 chilling winter Thursday evening. The following sharing are based on our unbiased personal opinion and experience

This is our first night stay after a hectic over 12 hours of traveling and flight ✈️ to reach Jeju island. We checked into the hotel around 6pm local time. It's a hotel situated along the coast.

The hotel has no lift 🛗 and that's the first encounter we had with 03 huge luggage 🧳 to lift up the flight of stairs. In the end we unpacked some of the essentials for showering and left the luggage back in the car.

The rooms are huge with 2x single bed and 1 x queen size bed. Room was pretty normal but the design was dated. It has all the essentials like fridge, TV, hair dryer and a huge balcony leading out to the sea.

Overall a 4 ⭐⭐⭐⭐ for the room size, location, view.
Not so much of services over here and the lack of lift 🛗

This hotel is awesome!
Location wise is better than great!
Facing directly to the ocean, next to the hotel has a famous BBQ black pork that you cannot missed it.

If you taking bus to the city is about 15 to 20 mins walking distance to the main road. Still ok under the cooling weather.

The hotel lobby is a cafe and you can order coffee to drink and cakes to eat. Next to it is a convenient stall and as you walk down the road there were many other restaurants for you to explore!!

A lot of photo scenery infront of this hotel, no regrets to stay there and I should have stay in this hotel all of my Jeju trip if I can!

Their toilet comes with bidet and hair dryer! Only down side is they don’t provide large towel!! And there is now lift to the other floor!! With large luggage you have to carry up!

Overall!! 5 stars and I will recommend and even stay there again!!!

Amazing location in the small town of Jeju Island of Aewol. Surprisingly, it's next to two highly recommended restaurants with high ratings (black pork BBQ and seafood sashimi just west of the hotel. The rooms are okay, you get a free drink one per room per day. Definitely the best location to enjoy the sunrise and sunset.

Even before I went, I found a place with a great view. This place is so pretty. Other than the inconvenience of carrying luggage because there is no elevator, it is a very pretty and comfortable place. The surroundings are pretty and there are restaurants nearby. I wanted to see the seabed biting, but the weather was bad so I couldn't see it.  It's quiet, peaceful, and has a great view. The cafe on the first floor also receives a 10% discount.

Great value for money, right in front of the sea
1st floor cafe very good

Jeju Pacific Hotel.adr_address: 20 Seosa-ro, 용담1동 Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Jeju Pacific Hotel.formatted_address: 20 Seosa-ro, 용담1동 Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Jeju Pacific Hotel.name: Jeju Pacific Hotel

reviews.text:
I came to Korea on vacation! I came with a some tour package, but I didn't expect much at all. However, although this hotel is old Building but it was quite clean and I was quite satisfied with the service due to the friendly crew!!
So I’m leaving a review of this hotel!!  "Jeju Pacific Hotel" staff, thank you very much!!  Thanks to you all, I am very satisfied!! I'am going back to United States very soon!!
I will remember!
you guys are very Professional~
two thumbs up
God bless you all ~~!!

The staff were very nice, and were English speaking so that was a plus point for me. My room was upgraded and it was a nice big room which made my stay better. The hotel staff were friendly and able to guide me on tourist spots to visit as well as the best way to get around Jeju. Would definitely recommend!

Very good hotel. Nice and large rooms, beds comfortable (all with one big and one small bed). Facilities are clean and good. Breakfast is so nice with the chef cooking fried eggs, seaweed soup, json soup... Friendly staffs.

The hotel quite good to stay few days
Room big enough
Breakfast look okay
Room service good
Facilities in room not new
Good and clean.

Hill Hotel Jeju.adr_address: South Korea, 63067, Cheju, 애월읍 하소로 507
Hill Hotel Jeju.name: Hill Hotel Jeju

reviews.text:
The restaurant owner was very friendly.
The menu was varied and delicious.
The price is reasonable, so you can get a meal without burden.
There's a dog next to it, so it's a good place to see if you like dogs.

The restaurant menu is diverse and delicious.
And the restaurant owner is very friendly.
It's nice to be able to get one meal without any hassle.
The owner must be an artist. The exterior was ordinary, but the interior was clean and comfortable like most hotels. The room was also warm and nice. It seems to be getting better.
Good luck! Under construction! It also smelled like horse manure. The room is spacious and clean. Good for sleeping with kids. The surroundings are cozy. Motel level

When I think of Aewol, I think it’s the beach ㅜㅜ
I thought this was what a distant sea view meant.
However, the room and bathroom are spacious and clean.
It would be better to think of it as a motel rather than a hotel.

\ud638\ud154 \uc568\ub9ac\uc2a4 \uc564 \.adr_address: South Korea, 63133, Cheju, KR특별자치도 제주시 연동 연동12길 4

editorial_summary.overview: Relaxed rooms & suites in an understated hotel featuring 2 bars, parking & Wi-Fi.

\ud638\ud154 \uc568\ub9ac\uc2a4 \uc564 \.formatted_address: South Korea, Cheju, KR특별자치도 제주시 연동 연동12길 4
\ud638\ud154 \uc568\ub9ac\uc2a4 \uc564 \.name: 호텔 앨리스 앤 트렁크

reviews.text:
Convenient location with friendly staff.
Despite they arent good at speaking English, they try their best to google translate it.
Not much amenities serving in the hotel but basic ones.
Spacious and comfy bedrooms.

The receptionist is very friendly and helped us to call taxi when we requested. Kudos to the receptionist on  24 Nov 2023. The room is clean and the shampoos smell great! Complimentary water bottles too.

Nice decorated affordable hotel with great facilities to work remotely. Good wifi, no problems with zoom-calls. There’s an office-like airconditioned studio with desks&chairs and a coffee machine. Spacious rooms with nice amenities. Located close to the city center of Jeju, so you’ll find many restaurants and bars by walking distance. We were able to park the rental car right outside of the hotel. The car park isn’t very big, but big enough for low season traveling.

A couple of things that could be improved. Staff is nice and helpful. However, they speak limited English and gave up very quick when a question about the wifi was asked. There are no breakfast options at the hotel. You’ll be able to get a cup of coffee, which was nice. There was a certain smell in our room that I didn’t like. Not sewage smell; more like a bad morning breath smell. The rest of the hotel smelt very sweet and flowery, so coming from the hall to the room was a bit weird.

The hotel rooms have no AC. When we first went in our room, it was 28 degrees and  very stuffy despite outdoors being around 18 degrees. Reception told us there is no AC and to open the windows. We had to leave the room it was so hot. At night we left the windows open all night to keep the temperature low, but it meant we could hear all the street noise. 2 stars off for no AC. otherwise hotel served it's purposes.

Chose this hotel just because of the proximity to Mt. Hallasan. Nice spacious room, but the bathroom is very inconveniently designed. No place to put your toiletries, the sink is tiny.
Dusty walls…

Line Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63213, Jeju-do, Cheju, 이도2동 1169-8

editorial_summary.overview: Casual hotel featuring simply furnished rooms, some with futons & heated floors, plus an eatery.

Line Hotel.name: Line Hotel

reviews.text: Rooms were spacious, clean, and comfortable. Decently convenient location. Fantastic value.
Budget clean hotel in Jeju city, not far from the main street. No breakfast available. Staff was nice. The view from the room overlooking the sea was pleasant.
Clean and spacious room. Clean bathroom. No bath tub. Cheap price. Standard room in weekdays is only $45 per night. I don't know price of weekend. Breakfast is available on $ 4.5
Great location and good value
Pong dep

Ebenezer Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63333, Cheju, KR특별자치도 제주시 조천읍 함덕리 1269-19번지 골든튤립제주함덕호텔
Ebenezer Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Cheju, KR특별자치도 제주시 조천읍 함덕리 1269-19번지 골든튤립제주함덕호텔
Ebenezer Hotel.name: Ebenezer Hotel

reviews.text: Located along the coast in a touristy town, surrounded by food, amenities, and attractions. If you get an ocean fronting room the view is great for the price, but the rooms are no-frills, and the bed, is hard.
Incredible cemetery view instead of mountain view. Not gonna lie I’m not a big fan of seeing coffins and tombs wake up everyday lmao💀

Fabulous ocean views. Sound proofing is not the best - especially when the room next door is having a private party until 1am.

Its a noisey hotel and you can hear all the door slams, cupboard bangs.

AC temperature is set during winter/spring and so cannot cool the room for sleeping.

As commented previously, the mattresses are very hard. So if you have back problems book elsewhere as all the room mattresses seem the same (after we transfered rooms the bed was the same).

Reception polite and friendly. I was amazed when they checked us in early. Which has never been the case in our 3 weeks moving around Korean accomodations.

Bed was well-worn but better than those provided in barracks. Only one key card was provided, even if you check-in as a couple. Staff had to be “coaxed” to help us book a taxi to the airport (we can’t speak/read Korean).

The view and close vicinity to the beach and various café / restaurants made up for it.

Prime location, however we had a very bad experience checking in. We arrived here around 12pm, waited for 3 hours, since they had strict rule of check-in only after 3. Everyone was waiting in the lobby on this horrible raining day. We’ve travelled extensively around the world, never been to any hotel so rigid with their rule especially when the weather was so poor. We went up just about 5 minutes before 3pm to ask if they are ready for Check-in, they refused. We were the first up to the desk, however by the time we finished our enquiry, there’s a big queue, the receptionist just sent us to the back of the line and receive local clients first. Is this how the local bully overseas customers?! Unbelievable. The room is ok, relative clean, only one chair is covered by some chocolate thing on the side, but missing towels, it was very hard to communicate with the staff, as they hardly speak English! Also, the Samsung aircon is funny, when it reaches the set temperature, it turns off automatically, and then it goes back on making big noise again when the temperature changes. No quiet sleeping setting. Disappointing with the brand choice. Oh, they don’t provide toothpaste or brush like others, so bring your own. Jeju-do is sadly not set up for international tourists, not just the language issue, the levels of professional service and courtesy are very not impressed. The view of the beach is not bad, but the beach is quite small, not as portrayed online.

Ebenezer Hotel.vicinity: KR특별자치도 제주시 조천읍 함덕리 1269-19번지 골든튤립제주함덕호텔, Cheju

Ventimo Hotel.adr_address: 14 Yeonsam-ro, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do 63118, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Airy quarters, some with kitchens & sea views, in a casual hotel offering a rooftop garden.

Ventimo Hotel.formatted_address: 14 Yeonsam-ro, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Ventimo Hotel.name: Ventimo Hotel

reviews.text:
This is a good small-sized hotel that is relatively new.
Pros:
•Clean modern rooms
•English speaking/helpful staff
•2 bedroom suites are reasonably priced with 2 separate bathrooms and toilets.
•Freshly laundered towels and toiletries are provided
•Near the airport and Lotte Car rental.
•Free delicious sandwiches for breakfast.
•Free coffee making facilities at the lobby
Con:
•Limited parking
•Bedrooms are a bit small. We’d to place our luggage outside the bedroom- at the living area

Amazing hotel with a valet who parks your car. The value for money is very good. We stayed for 1 night and they gave you for breakfast some sandwiches which are good too.
The staff is also very kind.
A Netflix account is provided in the room.

On the early morning of April 25, 2024, I checked in and everything was fine except for the check-in attendant. She did not provide any information about the facilities, sandwich service, or the door password. She simply asked if I had a car and handed me the check-in paper.

However, other aspects of my stay were positive. The bath water was hot enough, and the staff, especially the gentleman who worked on the early morning of April 30, were friendly. He even asked if I wanted a sandwich to take with me to the airport, despite it being 5:30 am. The room was clean and spacious enough for solo and couple travelers, and the location was just a 5-minute drive from the airport.

It’s ok. Seems all rooms in Jeju are smallish and 3 star standard. I would call it near and cute. Location was great. Many shops within walking distance. Their valet will park your car for you for free as space is limited. Nice coffee machine at the reception area. Really plus facility is the FREE washers and dryers. So so useful. View was very nice too. I would return

Great hotel! Room size is not the biggest but it is clean and the service provided by the hotel staff are great. There is a convenience store located right downstairs and valet parking is also provided. Also, the hotel provides complimentary breakfast! Would stay again.

Ramada by Wyndham Jeju City Hall.adr_address: South Korea, 690-022, Jeju-do, Cheju, 중앙로 304

editorial_summary.overview: Warm rooms in a contemporary hotel featuring a relaxed international restaurant & a gym.

Ramada by Wyndham Jeju City Hall.name: Ramada by Wyndham Jeju City Hall

reviews.text:
Room:large and clean
Laundry: 10fl total 9,000w to wash and dry
Breakfast: a bit tired from 3rd day.
Carpark: hotel guest free
Beside hotel got 7/11,
Opposite hotel got 24hrs Korea restaurant and several of Cafe.

This hotel is conveniently located in the heart of Jeju City and close to the airport.
There is free parking for the hotel guests (or maybe more like valet parking since you do have to hand over your car for the valets to park the car).

Check in and check out was smooth.

Now onto the rooms. I got a twin room. It was super large. Enough to do cartwheels (if I was so inclined, which I did not.)
The beds were nice and firm. The bathroom was also large, and I must say the hair products that was provided really did wonders for my hair. My hair never looked so shiny after the wash (but I sidetrack).

You can request for a bathrobe from the front desk if you need one, otherwise it won't be provided in the rooms. Actual slippers, and not the disposable kind is provided which is mighty thoughtful, since most hotels only provide disposable ones which if it gets wet, can be so icky.

The laundry room is also a lifesaver after having spent days without washing my clothes. Supposedly the laundry room is open from 9a to 9pm, but I don't think they actually enforce those rules. If you don't have detergent, it's ok. You can buy detergent and dryer sheet for 1k won. All washing machine, dryer and packets can be purchased with credit card. Super convenient.

If you are hungry during dinner, the hotel restaurant turns into BGC chicken outlet in the evenings. Or you can head to 7-11 or Holly's located right beside the hotel.

The only downside to the hotel is that when entering and exiting the parking garage, it can be quite dangerous, since its such a narrow lane that comes in both directions.
Clean, comfortable rooms with amenities. Close to 7-11, cafe and other eateries. Bus stop is just in front of the hotel. No smoking area provided.

Rooms are very nice, service is polite on the surface, but there is a huge difference between how the hotel staff treat their domestic Korean hotel guests and the way they treat their international guests. The breakfast served is not exactly top of the line, which is expected from a three star hotel, but their Coffee which should meet a basic minimum standard falls far short of expectations. Their disgusting machine coffee is so below par, it's a wonder anyone can even consume it. There are also no tea or non-coffee options unless you count concentrated juices. The worst part of my stay was too much noise on my floor by people slamming their doors loudly and disturbing the peace for several hours past midnight until 2am in the morning. Really unpleasant stay at this hotel, will not be visiting again. The only reason I'm giving them a two star review instead of a one star review is because of the excellent quality of their rooms. It's the only thing keeping them afloat.

My experience with the parking facilities at the hotel was extremely disappointing. Despite available space, we were denied parking, leaving us to wonder if this was a form of discrimination towards foreigners.

However, the check-in and check-out process was seamless. Situated in the heart of the northern city center, the hotel's location is highly convenient.

Although the staff insisted on parking at another location, we encountered issues with the car park gantry, resulting in a lengthy queue of up to 20 minutes. The walk from this alternative parking area to the hotel takes approximately 5 minutes, so be prepared for the winter wind and rain if directed there.

On a positive note, the hotel offers washing machine facilities. However, it was puzzling that they restricted usage to certain times. Considering the machines are located at the top of the building, noise pollution should not have been a significant concern.

Despite these challenges, the hotel's convenient location and smooth check-in/out process somewhat offset the parking woes.

I-Jin Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63136, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, 연동 306-14 KR

editorial_summary.overview: Relaxed quarters, some with balconies, in a straightforward hotel offering a casual restaurant.

I-Jin Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, 연동 306-14 KR
I-Jin Hotel.name: I-Jin Hotel

reviews.text: Very nice location especially if you have a car (it also has free parking area). We really appreciated the fact that there was daily cleaning of the room. In the dislikes the fact that from time to time there was a kinda bad smell of mud..

Really enjoyed my stay here! Highly recommended. Good price for 2 pax. Room is of a good size, there is space to open our luggages. Bathroom feels spacious and clean.

Service is 10/10! I told them we were feeling cold in our room and they brought us a radiator/heater. I also borrowed a clothes steamer from their reception. Kettle is clean. There is free parking across the hotel too. Although there is no view from the room, but at least I can open my window for some fresh air.

Room is very quiet despite being just beside the lift. I had a really good sleep :)

We stayed 2 nights with 2 double beds for a family of 4. The room is clean but a bit narrow. The toilet was huge and the water pressure was good. BF comes with bread, porridge, rice, fruit, coffee and juices. Convenience stores are near and it's near bus stops. Service is good. Check in and out was very quick. The only complaint is that there are no money exchange shops nearby.

We booked the suite. Price was very reasonable. The room was quite spacious with a bedroom and a living room. Also there was 2 T&B with one having a jacuzzi. The room has a wrap around veranda. Very spacious and a great view of Jeju Cityscape.

Location-wise, there was a number of restos around but if you want more choices you'll need to walk for more than 5 or 6 blocks.

Service was good and staff were very helpful. We left very early and front desk staff was kind enough to book our taxi for us.

Overall, a great stay.

The hotel was nice. We managed to park on the unpaved parking accross the street, but coming in the evening were never sure if there will be a place for us. Didn't try the garage as we read it is small and usually full.
For me the only downside was the breakfast. Strange choice of food and I ended up walking out on the second day and coming back after I bought some outside food. It was served from 7:30-9:30, and soon after 8:30 there was barely any food left. The lady working there wasn't very pleasant and was always eating at the table instead of taking care of the buffet, which we found unbelievable. People who were still eating close to 9:30 (not taking food, there wasn't any anyway, just eating still) were scolded by her, even though the restaurant/cafe wasn't about to close
Double bed room is not spacious but mattress was so comfy enough to have good rest at night (very calm) , bathroom facilitates was new and overall my rate is great!
Very  clean  room  and  good  service. Nice   morning   breakfast    is available for  additional price.
Good hotel, but no restaurant service.

Ok ok hotel...
The breakfast is just normal..
Walking distance to samyang beach...
Near to black sands. Good hotel food. Room was okay.

HOTEL NANTA.adr_address: South Korea, 63242, Cheju, KR특별자치도 제주시 선돌목동길 56-26

editorial_summary.overview: Upmarket hotel offering a buffet restaurant, a gym & a lobby lounge, plus event space.

HOTEL NANTA.formatted_address: South Korea, Cheju, KR특별자치도 제주시 선돌목동길 56-26
HOTEL NANTA.name: HOTEL NANTA

reviews.text:
The service here is really disappointing. I came here with my 7 Yr son. When we enter the hotel, they saw my son and I are carrying luggages, nobody came and help.

My son was excited when he saw the private pool outside the room. He jumped in straight away. When I was getting him ready to shower, noticed that there wasn't any toiletries provided. I wanted to go to down to buy the toiletries, realized that they only gave me 1 room card. I am stuck as my son needs the light in the room where he was inside the toilet.

Managed to get to get all these things settled. Then realized that their fridge wasn't cold at all where we bought 2 packets of milk earlier on. Tried to call the receptionist, they couldn't understand us.

It is really very disappointing as I don't think it is the way to preserve the environment where there is a working fridge, but not cold (not serving it purpose), have a convenient store downstairs selling all the disposable toiletries. Isn't it creating more waste for the environment?

For the short traveller like that, we won't bring home the remaining toiletries. I would suggest providing those big bottle toiletries for guests usage. And also ensure all the appliances work and serve its function properly rather than trying to cut cost!

Btw, they actually set the air con to a
certain temperature. When they misunderstood us on the fridge issue, they lowered our air-con temperature to 18C instead 😢 then now it is perpetually 18C

The rooms are good for cheap hotel . If I want better rooms get an expensive hotel. Even tho the hotel is 4 stars they don’t give shampoo and body wash in the bathroom . But u can get it from gs25 for 6500 won . The gs25 is in the 1 floor . There’s 7 floors . Trust me if u didn’t find resturant order and fried shrimp from room service it’s very yummy !!

In line with their green policy, single item usage such as Shaver, toothbrush, bodywash and shampoo is not provided.

Pros
- Good location as nearby to Gwaneumsa Trail to hike Hallasan
- beside the Nanta Show
- across the jeju planetarium
- has GS25 convenient store on-site
- gym
- slightly secluded
- friendly and helpful staff albeit language barrier
- free parking
- spacious room with good view
- smart WC

Cons
- did not notice swimming pool or spa
- abit far from most things
- limited complimentary beverage options. Did not have creamer and sugar for coffee.
- pillow was tooooo flat. Had to stack two together, but was still to low to sleep comfortably.

Rooms are big. Minimal amenities provided. Due to recent push by govt for sustainability, shampoo, shower gel, toothbrush etc is not provided. Bottles of water will be given every day and towels changed as well. Good value for money so please don’t expect anything more than cleanliness and essentials in the room.

The location is convenient for climbing Hallasan. Gwaneumsa trail is just 10mins away by car and the parking lot is big. We parked there, took a cab over to Seongpanak which is about 20mins away and started the hike from there.

Excellent location but the hotel is old and in need of urgent upgrade . Breakfast is very good value and it has good facilities. The rooms are very spacious and clean. Overall very good value for money but must renovate.

Golden Beach.adr_address: 2342 Yongdam 3(sam)-dong, Cheju, Jeju-do 63114, South Korea
Golden Beach.name: Golden Beach

reviews.text: Great rooms, with view of the ocean - but this place is almost directly under a flight path... fortunately, the planes stop at night.

The building looks old, so don't expect much, but the room is warm.
It's clean and the price isn't too expensive.
A pension of that size with a beach view would charge more even on weekdays than in a typical area, even if it's not the peak season. It's cheap, but it's not the same as a hotel with good facilities.
It's a place I really like. I highly recommend it. For reference, I used room 301 on the left for the first time.
Before that, only the second floor on the right from the building entrance was used, so the view on the left would not be good.
thinking is wrong

For a pension, cleaning and hygiene are maintained well.
It is located on Yongdam Coastal Road, so it has good accessibility to the airport. It is convenient as there are many restaurants nearby.

Although the weather was windy and cloudy, it was a wonderful experience at the water garden and a useful time to gain various knowledge about Jeju stones. This is a place that requires a full day to see it all!

Although the facilities are excellent or nothing special to boast about, the owner's consistency and low cost are very big advantages.

Moreover, the food village near Yongduam is close and the surrounding conditions are excellent.

It's also good to go to Aewol or Hallim.
It is also a great pleasure to watch the sunset while drinking a glass of soju at a nearby restaurant at night.

Sea&Hotel.adr_address: 15-1 Naedo-dong, Cheju, Jeju-do 63074, South Korea
Sea&Hotel.name: Sea&Hotel

reviews.text:
Terrible hotel service. Worst customer service I ever had. Asking to replace toilet seat cause it is too soft and too small for toilet bowl.  It  keeps dropping inside the bowl when we sit on it. Customer service said nothing wrong with the toilet seat and deny to replace a working one. Bed sheets and pillows are old  and dirty looking.  Mattress is super hard.
Not recommend this hotel at all.
Clean, has a buffet on bottom floor( I didn't try), they are friendly. It's a decent room better than motel 6. We had a small balcony. If you had a room facing the shore you would see the ocean

The room was awful and had holes in the wall. The bed felt as if you were laying on bricks. I even paid extra for the continental breakfast and there were flies over all of the food 15 minuetes after breakfast started. To avoid the flies I got the cereal and the milk was sour. This is the worst hotel stay I ever had. DO NOT STAY HERE!

Good breakfast for foreigners.
I think position is great for call taxi 🫡
Local area... If you want to stay, it is ok. No cups or amenities. You should bring what you need.

Boutique Hotel Villa de aewol.adr_address: 516-7 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do 63047, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Unpretentious hotel featuring sea views & an outdoor pool, as well as a restaurant.

Boutique Hotel Villa de aewol.formatted_address: 516-7 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Boutique Hotel Villa de aewol.name: Boutique Hotel Villa de aewol

reviews.text:
Terrible. There’s no couch, no big towels, a bit dirty and dusty.

We had to request towels. They brought us 4 for 7 people.

The bathroom sink doesn’t drain well.

We came into the bathroom and there were body hairs on the toilet and poop splash back on the back of the toilet seat. I asked them to clean the toilet and literally the hair was still there after they “cleaned”.

There’s a bed in the living room. There’s no couch or anything. Bare bones amenities.

The pool look nice and the view is nice but the price is not worth those.

One of the rooms has no closet. There are no lamps or bed lighting. The place looks nice from the outside but inside is rough.

I would rather stay at an Airbnb for half the price or a different hotel.

It was clean.  The bed was comfortable.  Breakfast was included.  The breakfast was good ... typical Korean food.  Lots of selection of Korean food. The price was reasonable

However I found it plain weird.  It looks like someone stole all the furniture and replaced it with a few pieces from Alice on Wonderland.

We stayed in a 2 bedroom suite.  There were only enough cups etc for 2 people.  There was a hot stove but there was a sign not to use it.  The couch and 1chair in the loving room were uncomfortable. We asked if we could get an extra chair but were told there weren't any extras.

There was one small common closet for everyone to use.  It only had a few mismatched hangers that came from various retail stores.  Neither bedroom had a closet or dresser so we had to keep our clothes in our suitcases.

They didn't clean our room the first night and when we called to complain and ask for clean towels they gave us a hard time.   They did eventually bring us clean towels.

There were no chairs on the balconies so we couldn't sit outside.

The bathrooms are roomy with lots of amenities.

The grounds are clean and plain.  The hallways are very dark at night.

You definitely need a car if you stay here.

Ok for an overnight stay but I wouldn't recommend for an extended stay.

booked by agoda. requested bed guide for children, and received confirmation but they are not prepared and even do not have them. room is not really clean and old. even price is not cheap comparing othet hotel. will not visit again. never.

best days in my life 😍my honeymoon 😍💖
November 2013 💖
Nice place, great service staff.

Dyneoceano Hotel.adr_address: 394 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do 63046, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Upscale hotel offering a rooftop pool, 4 restaurants & a cozy bar, plus sea views.

Dyneoceano Hotel.formatted_address: 394 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Dyneoceano Hotel.name: Dyneoceano Hotel

reviews.text:
We stayed 3 nights in a huge third floor king bed ocean view room with a window front jacuzzi. By and large the service was excellent, the staff very friendly and helpful, and the room clean. However, there were a few details in the bathroom and the room that make me think they may have skimped on refurbishment. The caulking around the sink is gone in some places and in others moldy. There is a slight odor but that's unavoidable as all of the other seaside places at least in the States seem to have one from the humidity. The bedding is great but the mattress itself is older, very hard and you can feel every single spring. Thankfully we were so tired from our daily outings that we still slept ok. Our room was one with a little seating area and the bed was not raised like in some of the pics, so maybe it's not one of the completely updated rooms.

The rooftop pool is super clean and fun. It's not truly an infinity pool as there is a plastic fence blocking the ocean view from the pool a bit.

The site itself is great, a few walkable businesses including black pork bbq, pasta, a gift store and even a Starbucks nearby. The walkable pier right in front is great. It's a bonus that they have a Twosome Place Cafe on the hotel main floor.
We wish we had been able to book a couples massage but even after several calls, leaving our number twice and physically going down to speak in person to try to book it, we were unable to get in touch with anyone.
Overall a great stay.

We stayed 5 nights at the family ocean suite and it had been a fabulous experience. Rooms are indeed refurbished and the sea view is stunning indeed. So far the negative reviews that the rooms are not clean and smelly are unfounded during our stay.

For the price of Sgd $300 for a huge 2-bedroom suite, there is nothing more we can ask for.

The coastal walk right in front of the hotel is a wonderful experience. We ate at the restaurants around the hotel and the food was great. The black pork BBQ restaurant and the seafood restaurant are top-notch in quality. This is a hotel that we will return to if we are to come to Jeju again.

We stayed for a night at the suite as part of our road trip around Jeju.
This suite has a huge master bedroom with a big spa bath overlooking the ocean as well as an ensuite bathroom at the other corner.
The other bedroom, which was much smaller, has two single beds and an attached bathroom as well.
Great views from the suite.
There are restaurants and cafes within walking distance.
Unfortunately we only stayed for a night and did not have the opportunity to walk along the trails along the ocean that are just across the road from the hotel.

Location was decent. A little far from the city areas but was nice and easy to get to by car. But the room wasn't as advertised and service was like talking to an npc. The 1st room we got didn't have its wifi working nor was the phone working until we went to front desk to ask. The room was advertise for 5 people with 2 singles, a queen bed and a couch. But the couch was a regular couch without any pull outs or blankets. Asking for an extra blanket also costed us 20000 won per night and they failed to deliver until we asked a second time, but double charged us for it. The second room we book has an included pool. But was also not as advertised. It was listed as a room for 5 with a sofa bed and both pool and hottub. We were given a room with only a pool and a regular couch. Plus we again had to pay 20000won for blankets since we got the room with 5 people in mind.

We are lucky to spot this newly furnished hotel at very fair prices. Spacious room with more spacious bath tub, electronic toilet, view of the sea from the window, conformable beds. Close to convenient store and middle of famous spots. Cannot ask more for a holiday stay.

Sea Stay Hotel.adr_address: 1105-1 Gonae-ri, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Sea Stay Hotel.formatted_address: 1105-1 Gonae-ri, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Sea Stay Hotel.name: Sea Stay Hotel

reviews.text:
Real facts.
Stayed 1 night
Weired noise coming from the hallway like someone was consistently walking up and down.
No double lock
There is no main entrance security like a swipe card
Anyone can walk straight to your door
No door peek hole
The ground floor is accessable from the street via balcony
Ac doesn't work
Flush the toilet, the whole place shakes
Random plumbing bubbling noise when other floor uses water

Would give zero stars if I could. The place is red flag. 100%, these love motels would have spy cams. Go elsewhere

The view was great! You can see sunset and night view was great too. You can hear the waves and has unobstructed very clean view. The owner was very polite and the room and bedding was crisp clean. You need to pay 5,000 won to use outdoor bath and it was worth it. Very relaxing with view. There was no hair dryer or iron i wasn’t sure i had to ask for it. Overall very satisfactory.

Nice, small hotel with a good view of the ocean from the rooms. There's a lot of lava rocks on the shore so it's just for view and not for swimming. The view was interesting and peaceful.

There's a hot tub by the terrace which we used and it was relaxing to hear the waves while soaked in hot water.

The room was clean and huge. You can connect your Netflix account too. The bed was comfortable, we had a peaceful sleep.

There's a mini kitchen and utensils are provided. You  can only make ramyeon and use the microwave, other than that, cooking is not allowed/possible. There's plenty of restaurants nearby and there's also a convenience store.
Excellent value for money. We had the family suite and it had a full view of the sea and we had our own balcony.
Quiet place and have a nice view. Got GS 25 in front of the hotel. We bought instant rice and heat in the microwave provided in the room. Basic cooking amenities also provided in the room.

Just went there over a week ago with my family and loved every bit of it.  It was raining but didn't stop us from using their big swimming pool as the weather was hot.  Friendly staffs, very accommodating, and the theme is geared towards children who love super heros from US, Korea, and Japan.  Soon as you walk into the their lobby you will see TV screens playing many animes and cartoons with models all around.  Even when you get to your floor you will be see models of children heros in a glass storage as you walk to your room.  I got a suite so our rooms were very clean with kitchen, fridge, and two bedrooms.

Next to the swimming pool, there is a small indoor trampoline, arcade and huge statue of Iron Man you can take a picture with.  It was awesome for my kid.

This place was a good location for us as we didn't travel much beside heading to the ocean side and the Jeju Aquarium.
We will definitely be back when we visit Jeju next time.

Nice and clean, people  could  be friendlier.
What a paradise  for the baby she loved every thing  about the place. She would  wake up and she will be ready to go downstairs to play.
Down side is she didn't  want to go out at all.

This is a great hotel if you have kids, like under 10 years old.  Tons of stuff for them to do. Rooms are fine, but you can tell they are just letting kids and frustrated drunk fathers punch holes in walls.  I do like that the repairs are low budget. "I see that your kid kicked a hole in the wall, make him color a picture and spackle it on there and we can call it even"

Seriously though this place caters to families.  Also if you don't speak Korean, find this place on naver ahead of time. Waze gets you lost and our taxi driver couldn't find it.

The resort is conveniently located next to the road but there is no good view.
facilities that are good for children, such as swimming pools, playgrounds, mini train and trampoline.
Good place for children.

Tamna Stay Hotel.adr_address: 번지, 2732 하귀2리 애월읍 제주시 제주특별자치도 63050, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Cozy rooms & suites with ocean views in a polished lodging with 2 pools, a cafe & a restaurant.

Tamna Stay Hotel.formatted_address: 번지, 2732 하귀2리 애월읍 제주시 제주특별자치도 South Korea
Tamna Stay Hotel.name: Tamna Stay Hotel

reviews.text: Amazing sea-view with morning sun! Check for opening of swinning pool in summer before booking! Laid-back vibe of seaside town, walking distance to coin laundry, and the beautiful Moonwhale Cafe! Family room was huge. Lighting and ventilation can be improved though. Overall a good stay!
I was visiting a restaurant nearby and could not get a taxi for very long. The receptionists very kindly helped us. Such wonderful service! So grateful!!

재방문 했어요!
담에도 또 여기로 예약하려구요!

Recommend. (I was a return guest!)
Attentive staffs.
Neat and clean rooms with a great sea view
Good location (Not that far from Jeju airport)
Enough parking space
Room’s condition is actually good that i had expected. Yup so good for sightseeing view in the room to ocean!
No air con during winter so had to open the window. Couldnt sleep very well because of that but otherwise a great stay

Dyne Resort.adr_address: 400-9 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do 63046, South Korea
Dyne Resort.formatted_address: 400-9 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Dyne Resort.name: Dyne Resort

reviews.text:
A decent resort, but by no means outstanding. The rooms were ok but not well maintained or furnished. Not enough electric outlets (only three accessible). Towels and sheets of poor quality. No crib for babies. No dressers or wardrobes to store items. A serious lack of parking - guard that parking spot tightly.

The pool was poorly maintained and in need of serious renovation (looks like a cheap holdover from the 70s full of bugs a leaves). There is another rooftop hotel on the roof, but you have to pay an excessive amount and reserve a spot there.

Food options there are good. I liked the BBQ restaurant and the free live music is a nice touch (although I'm not a fan of Korean oldies). The western restaurant at the hotel was surprisingly good as well. The chef there really does western food well.

The staff was generally pleasant there. An older maintenance guy who spoke English even kindly helped carry my bags up 2 flights of stairs, even though that wasn't his job. Greatly appreciated his assistance while juggling a baby in my arms.

Environment and location is good. Ocean view with many food options nearby. Not too far from airport, but far enough you're away from the city. I just wish there was a nice sandy beach nearby for swimming like Galki Beach. But Galki beach is only a 30 minute drive so not so bad.
Pretty decent resort with comfy room settings located nearby seashore with lotta coffee shops and restaurants around. Most important of all, the price is affordable~

Great accommodations! The room is beautiful. The rooftop saltwater infinity pool temp is perfect and the ocean view from the pool is spectacular! Breakfast buffet has lots of Korean and American style choices. We're loving our stay so far.

Located in a good shopping street
There is no English tags for the food but you can find them in Korean and another language. The staff are friendly and they try to help by using a translator. My friend found a hair in her dish.
Suchi was varied.
Rooms are ok but the shower head is spoiled.

Aewol Oceanstay.adr_address: 412 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do 63046, South Korea
Aewol Oceanstay.formatted_address: 412 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Aewol Oceanstay.name: Aewol Oceanstay

reviews.text: Very clean rooms with a great little efficiency kitchen and basic pots, plates, spoons, and chopsticks. The rooms bleed some noise so if you have rowdy neighbors you will know. Besides this minor thing really enjoyed my stay.

Bedding and facility management seem to be very good.
The owner was very kind and nice

It is located in front of the beach
There is a convenience store right next to it.
The room is not that big
The bathroom on the terrace is okay too.
Pension in front of the beach~~ I like it in a way~

Standford Hotel & Resort.adr_address: 406 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do 63046, South Korea
Standford Hotel & Resort.formatted_address: 406 Aewolhaean-ro, Aewol-eup, 특별자치도, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Standford Hotel & Resort.name: Standford Hotel & Resort

reviews.text: Staff were nonchalant to our complaints. Gave us a room with non-adjustable 30°C air conditioned on our first night. It was so hot, we opened the windows to let the cooler air in. Mosquitoes then feasted on us the whole night, itching till 3 days later. Woked up at 9am to drilling maintainance right outside our door. Are we on holiday or a construction site? We requested the air-con to be fixed but when we came back at night, temp was still the same. Had to packed and changed room in the middle of the night. No explanation given on what happened to our original room. Room amenities were the only positive feedback on the stay. Overall, for this price range is better to stay at Dain Oceano Hotel.

You can see the sea in the distance,
The rooms are nice and quiet too.
I didn't go in to the swimming pool because it rained, but it was nice.
Good value for money. It's a shame that the pool opens in May, but the rooms are very spacious.
I had a very comfortable rest. The room is spacious and the sea view is nice ^^
The rooms are spacious and there is ample parking space. Breakfast is also delicious.

Log Park Hotel.adr_address: 303 Dochidol-gil, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do 63035, South Korea
Log Park Hotel.formatted_address: 303 Dochidol-gil, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
Log Park Hotel.name: Log Park Hotel

reviews.text:
Pretty big complex of accommodation with ranch which u can feed alpaca.
Also can buy variety of alpaca hair stuff.
Heatting system Working well, but the bathroom is pretty cold.
Stayed well for 3days without interruption.

Loved the place rustic feeling. The cabin is very accommodating to 4 of us. And so many power outlets. Got places to stroll around and see the horses. Beautiful place to be for winding down.  Recommended!

We drove in after 9pm, the drive was a bit nervous for us as first time visit, both to the country and Hotel. As I notified the Hotel beforehand of the late check in, the friendly staff waited for us dutifully, I walked into the reception and he greet me promptly. As we arrived at the Log House, it's all ready for us, lights up, heated up... The kids just love it once they entered, we would so welcome! Thank you!
Quiet and clean. Very well priced. 1 apartment is big enough to accommodate a family of up to 6 pax. Private tranport is required as accommodation is quite inaccessible by public transport.

The Log Park Hotel is a fantastic place for a weekend in the countryside. I really enjoyed staying at Log Park. The area was peaceful, offered amazing views of the mountains, and the staff was extremely friendly and helpful. This place is a great place if you want to stay local and spend time around the area. I don’t recommend it if you are traveling around Jeju and only need a place to sleep

If you bring your children along they will have a fun time running around and playing with the wildlife. We were met by two alpacas when we first pulled up to check in to our cabin. there is also a small pet farm colocated with the Log Park. We woke up early for a morning walk to watch the farmer feed the pigs, deer, goats, and chickens. Kids will love it.

There are also other amnesties that make this place enjoyable. There is a campfire every night until 2200. The owners have equipment available if you want to BBQ. They have food, water, and beer available in the main Log Cabin for purchase.

Great place. I would love to come here with a group of friends for the weekend.

Grabel Hotel.adr_address: 7316 Iljuseo-ro, Cheju, Jeju-do 690-191, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Understated quarters, some with sea views, in a laid-back hotel offering dining & a rooftop pool.

Grabel Hotel.name: Grabel Hotel

reviews.text:
Good view ocean from the swimming pool.
They have done the necessary to give us two rooms next doors with our kids, the view of the ocean was very nice (downside of it all sea views are facing main road also).
Overall it is a very nice rate between price and quality.
Great service. Safe, clean, big and comfortable rooms equipped with all the necessary facilities (except disposables). Heated pool was very relaxing.

Thia hotel is not well located. The pool and rooftop is not as beautiful as the pictures. There is no beach next to it. The service is ok even though they did not want me to go by the swimming pool after my checkout whereas my plane was in the afternoon.

Hotel doesn't have wash cloths. No iron in room. Carpet is dirty and wasn't vacuumed. The Breakfast buffet was descent. They offered salmon which was really good. Staff was friendly. Descent view of the ocean but no beach nearby. Roof top pool was nice. I give it a 3 out of 5. But the price was good.
I would not recommend to foreign visitors to use the standard of service at a 4-star hotel.

Huesik Hotel Sydney.adr_address: South Korea, 63050, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Aewol-eup, Aewolhaean-ro, 943 시드니호텔
Huesik Hotel Sydney.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Aewol-eup, Aewolhaean-ro, 943 시드니호텔
Huesik Hotel Sydney.name: Huesik Hotel Sydney

reviews.text: We stayed in the AirB&B property that the hotel owns. It is right on the water with a rooftop that looks over the ocean. Property was right up to the ocean, right on the rocks so the nice sound of waves was heard all day which was nice. Room was very large and broken into two parts. Bedroom and kitchen. Both rooms were large enough for big groups. Great place to stay but a little out of the way from most of the tourist locations. Great find.

Positives: great view, many Cafe, restaurants and convenient stores near by, kind staff , comfy bed

Negatives: room service could improve,  they didn't make our bed during the stay or wipe down any surfaces, bathroom mirror obviously hasn't been cleaned in many stays, or just not well. if you like an extra pillow Bring your own, there was 2 on the bed but when we requested more then refuses. Only one set of toothbrush, shower slippers and glass was provided even though we booked for 2 adults.
They also did a renovation on our room in the middle of our stay

Over all,  you get what you pay for.  Good for young travelers

Location is good but we did not get the same room as what we booked. Also the condition of the washroom with faulty locks is inconvenient as the door cannot be closed. Thankfully it was only for a one night stay, so it was bearable. Slept and left the next morning. There is a half used tooth paste tube in the toilet. Really unsure if that is provided for guest or it was a left over. Highly recommend a bbq place though just down the street from the hotel.
Has a great ocean view.  The room is nice and clean.  Clean sheets.  Kind staff.  Four out of five stars.

pretty neat, you can see a great view of the ocean, there are parking lots so if you have rented a vehicle, you can store it here, but the lots are kinda not enough for every room to have one lot. but overall, it's good

Olle Resort.adr_address: South Korea, 63047, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Aewol-eup, Buryongsu-gil, 33 KR
Olle Resort.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Aewol-eup, Buryongsu-gil, 33 KR
Olle Resort.name: Olle Resort

reviews.text: Room does not have air conditioning.  Called front desk and they just argued that it works.  Asked for another room.  Do not come here.

The beds are very comfortable and the hotel is very quiet. My favorite thing about this hotel is that it's walking distance (300 yards) to good resteraunts. It's also across the road from an ocean-side hiking trail.

Breakfast was delicious. The staff were friendly, helpful and spoke English. You can make your own pottery in the Ceramics house. We did get a chance to use the Spa. Our room had four beds, a stove top, microwave, fridge, washing machine, dishes and a grill on the private patio. The bathroom has a Jacuzzi large enough for four people.  The view of the ocean and mountains is Amazing from Suite 502. Bring your own robe, they are not provided. Toothbrush, toothpaste, body wash, shampoo, shaving cream, razor, Q-tips and bath sponge. We received one free room service item and other discount coupons. There's a small bar in the BBQ restaurant, a coffee shop, mini convenience store, children play area outside, library, pool table, large sitting area where breakfast is served. I would come to this resort again but next time bring the kids.

A lovely friendly resort, tucked into a quiet part of the island. We went off season so the pool and spa were not operational, but there was a great Thai massage place close by.
Not easily accessible by public transport but fine by car and taxi.

It is one of the worst experiences of my life staying here.

reviews.text:
OMG some of the BEST bread I've had! I Food was crazy good...

Located in the podohotel area, it was our favorite place to have breakfast, during our trip to JEJU. Although small (something normal in JEJU) it has a beautiful view and a cozy living room with natural lighting. The super fast and attentive service.
I literally saved one just to enjoy on the plane ride. Freshly baked, loved and displayed so magically. Thank you for a great morning and yummy memories.

Friendly manager(SangHoon Baek), great service!!! Thx!!!

This hotel was just what we needed during our trip to Jeju Island. Firstly,  it's expensive (we didn't need the expensive price) and it will be difficult to justify this price. Visiting here will depend on why you are going to Jeju. For us, it was to unwind, spend some quality family time together and just be. This hotel was perfect for that. The hotel itself is a work of art. It is part of the Spinx golf resort. I believe that is is currently operated by the SK group.  Due to the elevation,  it is one of the unlucky courses for weather. There is more fog and poor weather days than many of the courses on the island, but when the weather is clear, OMG it's a beautiful course. Back to the hotel: The room we has was so spacious,  that we dreamt of creating a summer cottage to similar specs as our hotel room, because it was so perfect for us. The food at the hotel is first rate, be it Korean or western.  In the odd chance that you have a picky eater in the family, McDonald's is a 10 to 15 min drive away! In fact, aside from the main city, most places worth visiting are 10 to 15 min away. It's also  wonderfully serene there at all hours of the day.
We were able to drive and visit various places that we had hand picked to eat at without any traffic worry (must have a rental 🚗 car).
Downsides:
There are not many downsides to this resort hotel, but I will list what I found off. Pool: There is an indoor and outdoor pool located 3 min down the road by car. The land is that large! 3 min is NOT walking distance.  It's at another building called the annex. All of the facilities are fine, but having the pool so far away makes things difficult to organize family visits. Spa? It would be nice if there was a spa or more space for activities for those among the group who are not golfers,  or perhaps to cater to 1 adult and a couple of children should there be an avid golfer in the family and that person would want the other family members to enjoy more while he or she golfs up a storm. (Not me... just sayen)

It'd called the Podo hotel because the shape from above resembles a bunch of grapes. I wonder if that was exactly what was intended. I wonder if they were trying to create a bunch of modern-day Jeju Island houses and the result ended up looking like a bunch of grapes? You decide.  Either way it's cool.

The hotel itself is quite an impressive combination of modern-day and artistic expression.

I would visit again for all the same reasons we did the first time.

Suite room is very huge with lots of sinks so you don't forget washing your hands. 7/5 would wash my hands again. You can have a dinner course near a golf field with a nice open view. Lots of pieces of meat are served which all taste savory and melt in your mouth.
Must go here, for sure. Usually everything is good but maybe skip the Chinese fusion
expensive. good sight view but loud because of outside road construction

reviews.text: Pet-allowed rooms can be a bit smelly, but at least it is a resort that allows pets inside their rooms. 😁

It is 30 minutes away from the airport and is located in a mid-mountainous area, so it is 4 to 5 degrees lower than Jeju city and there is a cool breeze, so I was able to enjoy golf even under the heat wave warning. The course was well maintained and the fast green speeds doubled the fun of golf, and the sunset scenery was fantastic.

reviews.text: Wonderful hotel at a good price. Rooms have air-conditioning and floor heating. All Amenities. Good shower facilities with rain shower. Sunset view over the sea from every room. Free all day breakfast of toast with strawberry jam, Starbucks blend coffee. Ramen n other beverages available for purchase. Very friendly service. I slept really well and all ready for the day's Olle. Thank you.

the furnishing isn't tip top quality nor brand new. but they keep it clean and the room is very alright size for 1 person.
the staff is very approachable. there is a small area to put luggage it says theres cctv. sea view is quite spectacular.

is very well located as just along the road, turn in

Initially booked 1 night, then stayed an additional 2 more nights. 2 of the biggest reasons I stayed here again and enjoyed my stay has to do with the value proposition of the hotel and the bathroom. After having uncomfortably stayed at another hotel which required toilet paper to be disposed of in a waste bin rather than flushed down the toilet, I truly appreciated the luxury of flushing toilet paper down a toilet. I feel as though this could be an important detail for some, as it was for me.

The hotel also offers a nice large 24-hour dining area to eat brought in food. They also sell some snacks, drinks, and ramen if you have some hunger pangs at night. The hotel provides free toast, jam, and a great coffee brewing machine which makes a good morning coffee. They have filtered water for ice as well, which I appreciated as I enjoy iced coffee.

Room was tidy and comfortable. They also have available a dehydrator or a spin dryer in the lobby to help dry off clothes that you hand washed. They also have a nice computer to use if you need quick access to the internet, free to use.

I would definitely recommend this hotel, considering the price and area as well. Nearby is a great pasta restaurant called “Pesto”, which I visited twice during my stay. Also, there is a nearby 7-Eleven convenience store, which is about a 7 minute walk along the beautiful coast.

There is a local bus stop literally across the street from the hotel. The 202 bus, which is a frequently used bus, stops here at 용운동 (Yong Oon Dong). Hotel shows a little mini map of the nearby restaurants and places of interest as a nice reminder. They provide free amenities like toothbrushes, shaving razors, etc.  You really couldn’t ask for anything more from a hotel. I recommend staying on the higher floors as the big ceiling to floor windows are great and you have a little more privacy the higher up you are.
Very good experience. Clean bedding and a bang for your buck! Great service and care. The staff are very friendly and willing to accommodate to your needs.

reviews.text:
Very nice, large hotel with friendly staff. The hotel is not the newest but is classy nonetheless. There’s a few external restaurants and a 7/11 next door.

The pool is a bit small for the hotel size but nice otherwise. Exterior of the building could use some maintenance.

Our experience was wonderful in every way. We booked last minute due to an unexpected issue with our original lodging and were delighted by the turn of events that landed us here. The staff went above and beyond to accommodate us. They were friendly and helpful. The building is beautiful and well maintained. The gardens are lovely and peaceful. All the services we used exceeded our expectations. Would definitely recommend and hope to stay again.

Lotte Hotel Seogwipo Jeju is nestled in a breathtaking location, offering stunning panoramic views of the ocean that make for a truly serene and luxurious experience. The resort’s imposing structure stands out against the scenic backdrop of Jeju Island, and the ocean views from the balcony are simply mesmerizing, providing a perfect spot to unwind and soak in the natural beauty.

The architecture of the hotel is nothing short of beautiful, combining modern elegance with subtle traditional influences, creating a grand and welcoming atmosphere. The large outdoor heated pool is a standout feature, perfect for a relaxing dip while enjoying the fresh sea breeze. For those seeking a bit of excitement, the resort’s casino offers a lavish and entertaining experience.

However, the experience is somewhat marred by the service, particularly at breakfast. The staff, though professional, could benefit from being more courteous, especially towards guests who arrive close to the 10:30 am closing time. The strict policy of not allowing guests to take any food from the buffet counters after the cut-off time, despite the food still being on display, felt unnecessarily rigid and, frankly, rude.

Additionally, while the hotel boasts several dining options, the variety could be expanded, particularly with more vegetarian options, to cater to a wider range of guests. Another downside is the lack of complimentary toiletries in the bathrooms, such as toothpaste, toothbrush, and a comb, which need to be ordered from housekeeping at an extra charge—a surprising omission for a hotel of this caliber.

Overall, while the resort offers a visually stunning and relaxing stay, there are areas, particularly in service and amenities, that could be improved. Based on my experience, I would give Lotte Hotel Seogwipo Jeju 3 out of 5 stars.

Comfortable, even though alone but can feel comfortable and satisfying, and good service, highly recommended..... 👍👍

Lotte Hotel in Jeju is the best hotel in my life. I went with my mom and child, and from the swimming pool to the accommodation and breakfast, there was nothing lacking.
