reviews.text:
Gloucester Jeju Hotel offers a pleasant and comfortable stay in Jeju. The hotel is well-maintained, featuring clean and neat rooms that ensure a relaxing experience. Its prime location near an outdoor shopping area provides guests with easy access to various shops and boutiques, making it convenient for those looking to explore and shop. Additionally, the vicinity boasts a variety of restaurants, offering numerous dining options to suit different tastes.

One downside, however, is the hotel's breakfast, which is quite mediocre. While it provides the basic necessities, it might not meet the expectations of those looking for a more varied or high-quality breakfast experience. Despite this, Gloucester Jeju Hotel remains a solid choice for travelers due to its cleanliness, excellent location, and overall value. It's a great option for those who prioritize convenience and comfort during their stay in Jeju.
The location is good , room is good too. They will change your sheets everyday. It just the corridor smell off. Need to change the floor carpet.

very poor service! the receptionsts in the desk provides no service at all, leaving luggage is a mess, just theguest help them selves without any security (randommly in the lobby conqer). The receptionist always busy at staring at the PCs, not sure what are their job duties, not serving the guest. No greetings at all, no 'thanks', 'can I help you'. We booked the room only for late flight today, suggest avoding it 100% for other guests.

Staffs were friendly and nice. Close to airport. Room was spacious and clean.

No USB chargers as most hotels would have and no bedside plugs as advertised. Really poor communication from the hotel:

First instance: I was awoken in shock early morning due to a deafening drilling noise that sounded like it was coming from the room next door. We had to call reception to confirm that this was scheduled construction as we were not notified previously. They did answer quickly and confirm this. However, we did not know about this the night before as mentioned. You would think that if there was construction work taking place the hotel would notify the guest beforehand. The loud drilling was ongoing even until we left the hotel at 11am.

Second instance: The hotel has free unreserved parking (in the car park underneath the hotel and in a public garage around the corner). The con (unreserved parking) strongly outweighs the pro (free). When we were heading into the car park under the hotel, the parking attendant told us to park underground. We followed his instructions as he guided us downstairs to B2 (garage floors: B1-B3). After we parked our car, the attendant said we were okay to leave. The carpark was under renovations and we also saw another car coming into our floor to park so we didn't question the attendant.
The next morning when we tried to get our car to leave, we were told by the workers that we cannot move our car out at all until 9pm. We went to reception and they said the same thing and that we needed to move our car before 11am. Before this point, not once were we advised that we had to move our car before 11am - there were no notices in the hotel/car park nor was this mentioned during check in. The parking attendant that let us in also did not say anything regarding this. This caused us to delay our planned itinerary. The hotel staff were helpful and I could see that they were trying their best to resolve this for us. They kindly hired a taxi for us until 7pm - we had to cut our itinerary short as it was 2pm already by the time the taxi arrived.
We went to get our car at 9pm to move it to the free garage to avoid this from happening again and the workers there told us that we can't get our car until 11pm even though we were told 9pm earlier on. We went to reception to confirm that we can get our car tomorrow as long as it's before 11am - they said yes and I specifically mentioned that our car was in B2. Come next morning and we get a phone call at 7:24am telling us to move our car as they are starting construction. 7:24am = 11am?

As mentioned by the other negative reviews, this hotel has really poor communication. Not once was this mentioned on any of the notices as pictured.

Parking spaces tight. Room was warm because the aircon doesn't work due to change of season. Had to open the window but ended up getting feasted on by mosquitoes, my child got at least 10 bites.
Toilet was very noisy and the sensor light was very annoying. Toilet glass door felt dangerous because it is heavy and kept swinging. Was really worried my child's toe would get caught. Breakfast was lackluster, non-appetizing and expensive.
Restaurant looks run down, coffee was disgusting.
Service and English speaking skills are non-existent. On my check out, my child touched the railing and the service staff snapped at him "no touch no touch". Worst stay of my 1 week trip in Jeju.

It's good. The view is good and you can have a barbecue. It only costs 20,000 won. The staff was so friendly that I thought it was the owner. It was even better because it was clean. I fell asleep looking forward to the ocean view in the morning.

The view is nice and the rooms are clean.
The bathroom was spacious and clean, so I was able to spend my time comfortably.

Don't book the cheapest room.
The ocean view room is okay, but the cheapest room can be an embarrassing experience.
The wind in front of the sea is very strong, but the room is really warm, so I took a good rest even though it was hot~~

The room is worse than a motel.
The room is humid and narrow.
What about the hotel... Anyway, I really regretted choosing the wrong accommodation.

reviews.text:
The city needs to perform a MAJOR health inspection...tremendous lack of concern for cleanliness and sanitation.  Rooms also have not been fumigated for pests.  I got infected with bed bugs and mosquito bites on the first out of the three night stay and reported it immediately to the front desk lady.  She did not seem to care and only switched our rooms for the sake of keeping us quiet.  Even new room has some cookies on the floor course not ours..bugs screen door not working both rooms..Showed absolutely no sign of remorse; no apologies for our troubles.  Bathrooms were moldy and infested with mosquitoes, No plumbing bathtub also. Most utensils are unusable, Ruined our vacation. Would give them minus star if I could..Folks, if you're planning a vacation to beautiful Jeju Island,
please reconsider staying at Tovice Condominium and avoid at ALL COSTS!!!
It's great value for money... The rooms are clean, and it's located on Aewol Coffee Street and the beach, so it's great for taking a walk. I'm planning to make another reservation next time.

A condo with nothing good about it except the location and price
I can't watch TV because more than half of the channels are laggy.
The facilities are so outdated that even the codes do not work well.
Moreover, the boiler cannot be turned on and off at will.
There is no separate sauna at night.
Of course, if you ask me what you expect from this price, I have nothing to say.
It is divided into two condominiums, the old building and the new building, but the new building seems to have been remodeled quite recently.
If you are the kind of person who just wants to sleep, it may be okay because the price and location are good, but if not, it is better for your mental health to pay more and sleep somewhere better.

1. The bathroom near the bed was okay, but the bathroom near the entrance didn't have a good exhaust fan, and I got atopic dermatitis all over my body when I used the shower.
2. There is a fishy smell in the sink. How to use it...
3. Even though I turned to the left to use hot water in the shower room near the entrance, only lukewarm water came out.
4. Blue screens often appeared on TV programs. (There wasn't much to see.)
5. Be careful with the handles of closets and dressers, as they are worn out and may cause injuries to the hands of young children and the elderly.
6. The only advantage is the view, and the view was worth seeing.
7. Everyone said that the new building was remodeled, but it seems like only the front was remodeled, and the building in the back felt like it hadn't been remodeled at all, so I felt like I was visiting a grandmother's deck in the countryside. Please be careful as the feeling and appearance in the photo and in reality are different.
The rest are full of shortcomings.

It's a very old facility and the cleanliness is poor~ When I was checking in, another customer had booked for 2 nights but stayed only 1 night and checked out because it was dirty, so I was worried, but guess what.... ㅠ
The bathroom smells bad and the refrigerator isn't cleaned.
I don't even want to use a towel...
The bedding makes my body itchy~
The older female desk clerk is cold!!
The two management staff responsible for separating waste were very friendly.
This is a place I never want to go again!!~

soon

html_attributions: 炭炭與亞尼克 Tantan und Yannick

reviews.text: It was my first time in the Jeju so I really like the hotel view, surroundings, and the rooms. The hotel service was also good. It has reasonable price compare to other 5 star hotels. They provide breakfast buffet system only when you pay for it. I really like the breakfast buffet. The hotel area was quite large and it had a swimming pool too. The hotel is situated near the beach area so you can spent good time at beach. The hotel has a separate inside bar plus restaurant where you can have your meal if you do not want to go outside however it was quite expensive.

Great hotel with a nice location and fairly big rooms. The service was friendly but the automated check-in check-out system is a complete waste of time and makes the first contact with the hotel not so pleasant (let humans do human jobs). The receptionist must anyway help you to check-in so what is the point?
The prices, like everywhere on the island, are expensive, for both the rooms and the room service.
The breakfast buffet is OK with a great choice of food to please everyone.
As some mentioned, it is not a 5 stars hotel, rather a 4 stars.

The hotel is indeed in the midst of many 5 star hotels. The location is nice and the price is reasonable, however the hotel is in no way shape or form a 5 star hotel. I would say it’s 3.5 star hotel. Lots of renovation needs to happen. Carpets are old and has stains. Needs to be replaced. Walls are not finished properly. The surrounding hotels are definitely all 5 stars, esp Parnas and sila.

I stayed here in a double room in the month of September, 2016 with one other guest. I did not have any of the extra amenities, including the meal packages, so this is simply a review of the room.

Arriving in the room, it was clean and organized, with all the proper amenities, and some additional ones that normally aren't included with hotels of this caliber. It also has a very ample balcony, sizing up to the rest of the somewhat spacious room. It was very comfortable, but it did come with some issues.

For one, the air conditioning was essentially nonexistent at night. With the heavy and thick bed sheets, the other guest and I were quickly waking up covered in sweat. The following morning, we approached the front desk where we asked them, in Korean, if there was an issue with the air conditioning in that room or floor, when we were informed that it was normal and to instead open the balcony door and use that for ventilation. We were then offered a fan in case things got any worse, which wouldn't have helped much in a room of this size.

Secondly, a minor issue for me but an issue nonetheless: after the first night, we had our room cleaned. Everything was as good and organized as when we first checked in, but now there were quite a number insects that I had to take care of myself. A hotel of this supposed quality shouldn't be having pest issues.

Now, I will add that the staff and service was your typical friendly Korean variety. At one point, we had forgotten to turn off our "Do Not Disturb" status, but luckily the hotel called to see if we still wanted the room clean, which was really nice of them. Parking was not too difficult, as we always found available spots near the sides of the hotel.

Were it not for the air conditioning issues and the insects, I would have given this location five stars. It is in a great location for a decent price.

The staff was very friendly and cordial, the breakfast buffet was fantastic, the rooms were exactly what I was looking for. It is a little farther from the beach than I would like, but it is a fantastic location for those who like to run in the morning (like me). I was able to run to all the local attractions without issue and traffic in the area was minimal. It is also next door to a casino.

Great hotel central seogwipo.  Parking is free but the garage is a bit tight.

Good prices for what you get

Bathroom was high quality
Nice hotel. Feels upscale. Everything works. Nice little gym. Little balcony but no table or chairs are provided. I recommend going to the market only 450m away for nice cheap food.

As of July 2023, a great hotel, with ocean view. Not too unreasonably priced, and very clean. Staff were all helpful and friendly. They have a nice little lobby where you can get a variety of coffees or drinks. Careful in the parking garage though, it’s very crowded and very narrow especially early morning or later at night. Definitely want to be careful going in and out. There is also a convenience store right next door and a laundromat if you’re staying a while and need to wash some clothes. Overall enjoyed the stay here and was able to explore many nearby places. Would definitely recommend.

I loved this hotel. 😍The service was amazing, the people are really welcoming and friendly. I really liked the breakfast and we had a wonderful room with a fantastic view, definitely if I come back I would love to come back to the same hotel! Thank you for all the attentions

Hotel Rest Seogwipo.adr_address: 17 Jungang-ro 71beon-gil, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63592, South Korea
Hotel Rest Seogwipo.name: Hotel Rest Seogwipo

reviews.text:
Nice hotel. The front desk is at the second flour and there is the owner who attents the guests. He didn't speak English but was friendly and helped us promptly when the airco didn't work and I wanted an extra pillow. There are like 10 very very tight parking spaces down at the entrance but they are almost always full. At the reception desk we received a map which indicates 3 other free parking areas nearby. Sometimes you need to drive through them a couple of times because there is quite a parking problem in the area, there are so many cars. But eventually we would always find a spot within 15min or so. The parking lots are close to the hotel.
The rooms are nice, well equipped. We didn't make use of the breakfast (is at floor 2 as well).

The location is good as well. Seogwipo is quite a weird town and I wouldn't really be able to define one area as the city centre; shops and restaurants are all across the city.

Affordable and in a good area with lots of restaurants around. The rooms are a bit janky though. Some of them smell like cigarettes even though there's no smoking. The toilet in my room leaks each time you flush and the walls are super thin. There's also only one elevator.

They will email you a link that shows your room number and room key combination. This honestly feels super unsafe as there's no authentication to view it as long as you know the URL. And it shows both the room number and key code... Just be careful opening it up anywhere in public.

You Should read this before staying here and decide for yourself.
My Disappointing Stay at Hotel Rest Seogwipo

Firstly, the food handling practices at Hotel Rest Seogwipo were quite alarming. I discovered that the manager transferred food from his own bowl to a guests plate without disclosing that it was second-hand food. This lack of transparency and disregard for basic food safety regulations left me feeling uneasy and concerned about potential health risks.

Furthermore, the noise disturbances caused by the cleaning staff were highly disruptive. Despite it being 8:00 in the morning, the staff were shouting and making excessive noise outside the hotel rooms. This greatly impacted my ability to relax and enjoy my stay, as I expected a peaceful and quiet environment.

Cleanliness standards at Hotel Rest Seogwipo were also lacking. Requiring guests to wash their own plates and cups after breakfast raised concerns about the cleanliness of these items. It is important for a hotel to ensure proper sanitation practices, and by shifting the responsibility onto guests, the hotel seemed to prioritise convenience over maintaining a high level of cleanliness.

Lastly, I was disappointed to discover that Hotel Rest Seogwipo charged additional fees for replacement sheets and pillows. I believe that essential amenities such as these should be provided without extra charges, as they are fundamental to a comfortable stay. This policy left me feeling inconvenienced and gave the impression that the hotel was trying to cut corners at the expense of guest satisfaction.

Overall, my experience at Hotel Rest Seogwipo was far from satisfactory. The issues with food handling, noise disturbances, cleanliness standards, and additional charges for amenities left a negative impression. I hope that the management addresses these concerns promptly to ensure a more pleasant and enjoyable experience for future guests.

Good affordable price. Convenient location. Comfortable stay. The biggest downside is the room walls are thin. Able to hear ur neighbours talking very clearly, doors opening and closing. It has been keeping us up the whole night ..
The counter staffs are friendly and helpful. Free parking at hotel. Roof top has 360 nice view of Seogwipo city.

We booked this last minute because our original accommodation was inaccessible due to a typhoon. The pool was fun and everything was clean. The view was amazing and I'm thankful that we had somewhere to stay in an emergency!

However, I wouldn't stay here again. There was such an odd smell coming from the bathroom and it really permeated through everything in our suitcases. Other reviews have mentioned this as well. Maybe it's the sewer?

We rented a pullvilla which has a private spa and swimming pool, it was fantastic! The room condition was very neat and clean with 2 bathrooms. It seems like there were many celebrities who went here as well :) I highly recommend it!

The sunrise view over Seongsan Ilchulbong from the hotel was absolutely breathtaking. The location of the hotel is on the coastal road that you can find many interesting small local restaurants. However, getting to them will require a bit of walking. We had a rental car, so it was a very enjoyable experience staying there.
Clean and spacious rooms. We could see Seongsan Ilchulbong & the ocean straight from our balcony! Only downside was the small shower area, as they squeezed in a huge bath tub in a small washroom.
Love the hotel cleanliness and size of room. Higher price if you opt for a room with jacuzzi bath tub. Staff are polite and efficient. Hotel is in front of the beach

reviews.text: Hotel that needs urgent renovation of the rooms. The bathroom, although functional, has a bathtub with a curtain and no overhead shower. The pool has too many rules and the security guards do not let you swim safely, despite knowing how to swim very well. The garden and its views are very beautiful.

Don't bother going to the outdated gym. It's a joke and they will overcharge you!

I paid for 2 days to get a quick work out in and they had the audacity to accuse me of not paying for a third day! If you are a foreigner the gym attendants are not accommodating. I have never in my life left an establishment without paying.

Don't come to this hotel if you want to be treated with respect. Absolute garbage. KAL of you are reading this, be better.

This hotel is in a good central location. The gardens are beautiful and so well maintained. I could have spent the entire trip there.

The rooms and the hotel itself are a bit dated but didn’t seem old. Everything was clean, well maintained and everything you would expect.

The Palor Suite was extremely spacious and the bed comfortable but it was the views that were phenomenal. We could see the squid catches out every night while overlooking the garden.

The staff are experienced, friendly and always willing to help.

I was a bit sad the the pool didn’t have water in it as it was not the right season for outdoor pools.

Overall, would definitely come back.

The hotel is furnished with comprehensive amenities designed to ensure the safety and well-being of guests. The reception staff exhibited exceptional kindness and attentiveness, particularly in assisting me with directions. My room underwent thorough cleaning, and despite its compact size, it was equipped with all the essential items required for a comfortable stay. The rate charged for the accommodation was exceptionally reasonable, considering the outstanding level of service provided. I express my gratitude for the excellent service. Thank you.
This is not a 4 stars hotel. The place has not been updated in over 30 years. Carpet is dirty and everything is outdated. Don’t trust the pictures they have on their sites. See the attached

reviews.text: Lovely location and staff. The accommodation and breakfast was delicious. Our room smelled of smoke which was impossible to get rid of it we still enjoyed our stay here.
Lovely place to stay. Rooms are spacious and clean. Location is quite strategic to travel around the island when you are driving. Has nearby restaurants by car.
Peaceful and quiet place to reax and recharge yourself. The swimming pool is not big but comfortable enough for a family after a long day of sightseeing. A great place for a big family trip.

Five out of five !

Design- well designed, very practical and spacious. Very large. Famaly can easily stay for month.

The room is well equipped- gas and electricity stove, oven, fridge, rice cooker and even a wine bar. Nevertheless they could do with more utensils.

Service- very kind and friendly.

Location - you must have a car if you wish to travel around. Anyhow you better have a car in Jeju.

Stayed 3 nights at Atrium.

wi-fi didn't work on 1st floor. Also signal strength of SKT 5G was very poor on 1st floor. Can't complain anything else!

reviews.text: It was really nice to have 3 bathrooms, 3 rooms, 2 TVs, and a large vanity with a nice view, but... the toilet was leaking, and when I came to wash up in the evening, there were money bugs in the bathtub... Even when I went out on the veranda, I made sure to check the screen. The noise is loud. I don't know if it's the house next door or the house above. It's their fault, but the thumping sound is loud. It's a shame that the nearby convenience store is a bit far away. But the cat was cute haha.

This condo-type accommodation is convenient for families to use. There are no amenities in the complex, but within a short walk (10 minutes~), you can find Starbucks, convenience store, Yeomiji Botanical Garden, Yachting Center, and Sailing Delicacies. As Jungmun is spacious and well-equipped with facilities, I would like to visit again next time when comparing prices.

Family suite. I am satisfied with the spaciousness of the 3 rooms, 4 beds, and 3 bathrooms.
The kids were surprised to see a large spider in the main room and a large spider come out of the bathroom. Quarantine is unsatisfactory.

Good for multiple people to stay
Lots of rooms and bathrooms
Convenient parking in front of the building
Convenience store location within the complex
Toothbrush and toothpaste are not provided.

Brown Suites Jeju Hotel & Resort.adr_address: 94 Goseongojo-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63639, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Unassuming hotel featuring an indoor pool & modern rooms, plus a rooftop terrace with sea views.

Brown Suites Jeju Hotel & Resort.name: Brown Suites Jeju Hotel & Resort

reviews.text: Cannot recommend. Only if you are on a budget and want a bigger room. It looks very run down, cheap construction. The shower and sink had so many water stains, I don't think they are cleaned properly. The location is also not ideal.

The ocean views are fabulous and also kindful reception service. The room is tidy and pretty big. reasonable price, enough parking spots. strongly recommend. Unfortunately, they don't provide breakfasts and swimming pool services at the moment but staff will show the local restaurants list which are famous shops nearby.

We had a very nice stay here. The rooms are big and clean. The hotel has a great view of the bay and the volcano that we wanted to be close to. There are lots of great places to eat nearby and beach is walking distance. The staff is very friendly and helpful and suggested great places for us to try and we went and had great food.
The hotel itself doesn’t offer breakfast or pool services due to Covid but other than that it’s been a great experience staying here.

The room was clean and a nice size. It would have been nice to have heated floors (because we travelled in winter), but it seems this isn't common for hotels in Jeju. The bathroom sink tap is very strange and sometimes it wouldn't turn off properly, so we didn't have hot water for a shower because we had left the hot water tap running while we went out 😅 it was our fault of course, but the sink tap is very annoying. Don't eat at the hotel's recommended black pork restaurant! It was not good...

We wanted to hike up sunrise peak to see the sunrise but the staff told us the ticketing booth doesn’t open until later so we are grateful that they saved us from waking up early and getting a taxi in vain.

The view from the hotel room itself was great to see the sunrise.
The glass was filthy but you can just crack open the window to see the view.

There’s a small convenience mart at the basement that is unmanned at certain hours.
The swimming pool seems to be permanently closed.

The hotel might be 3 stars but the service was 5 stars.

There seems to be only 1 staff at the counter who spoke English but we managed fine.

High recommend 🙏

Good points:
1. Location is convenient if you drive
2. The room is spacious, clean and well maintained

Area of improvement
1. Insufficient staff running the business
2. Staff treated local better than foreigners
3. Staff has condescending attitude when I request for help.

5. Must sure you bring umbrella as they only either broken umbrella or limited. The staff will ask you to buy umbrella from eMart when it is raining. Who will bring sufficient umbrella overseas!!
Jejueco has an extremely helpful host Victor and his staff are all exceptional. Loved the rooms, very spacious and cozy. Would love to go back.
Lovely views of forest & ocean. Nice hot tub on balcony. Breakfast simple but good. Friendly people.

reviews.text:
Love this place, thr view is wonderful that you don't want to leave the room. I've book the loft room which located on a third floor walk up. The room is spacious, clean, bedding is very comfortable. I love that there's hot/cold drinking water machine inside the room. Plenty of amenities for whatever you need. There's also a convenient store on site in case you need anything else. Plenty of parking space with ev charger on site.

The staff are very helpful and can speak English. I would recommend this place if you want a quiet location with superb views. An easy driving distance to many restaurants and attractions.

There is a fog right in front of the accommodation, so it’s perfect for swimming.
Even the reserved octopus ramen is delicious.
Great view, great cleanliness, disappointing soundproofing
There isn't much food around, and you need to bring cleansing and shower towels. It's in front of the beach so there's a sunset view. great

The room is like a duplex studio. However, the view outside the window is nice and you can see the wind turbines far away. I thought I could see the sunset from the room, but the day I stayed was overcast and cloudy, so I couldn't see it. It rained early in the morning so I took some great photos.

Hotel The Grang Seogwipo.adr_address: South Korea, 63592, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, 16, Jungjeong-ro, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, Republic of Korea 제주특별자치도 서귀포시 중정로 16 (서귀동, 호텔더그랑서귀포
Hotel The Grang Seogwipo.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, 16, Jungjeong-ro, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, Republic of Korea 제주특별자치도 서귀포시 중정로 16 (서귀동, 호텔더그랑서귀포
Hotel The Grang Seogwipo.name: Hotel The Grang Seogwipo

reviews.text:
I would have loved to give 10 ⭐️if I could! The team running this entire hotel appears to be only these 3 people, Jay, Bruce and Becky and that’s mind blowing. Jay and his team are superbly friendly, and we had our car handled by Bruce well as well.

And what do you know, at the lift lobby, there was a quote that is very philosophical and thought provoking!! 😄

It was a very comfortable stay and the location is prime as we could get to the nearby market and food street easily, and there’s an excellent cake shop (Tina’s cake) nearby as well.

Would love to stay there again if we revisit jeju island!

Best hotel I stayed in Korea.
Jay and Bruce were very service oriented,  prompt, and friendly.

Every time I reach the hotel or need the car, they will attend to me immediately.

Nice and cheap bf.
The only issue is that the toilet might flood as the draining system is slow. Otherwise, 5 stars!

I checked in late, and a young lady named Becky greeted warmly.  She has a friendly laugh that makes us happy.  There is no hassle with valet parking, and the cleanliness and quietness of the rooms are also the best.  It was hot and humid as the rain continued, but the air conditioner worked well, so we're able to stay comfortably.

Best hotel in Korea! (Better than lotte hotel which I've stayed previously in Seoul). Special thanks to Jay and team for making our stay so memorable. Jay is very attentive and caring towards us and make sure we were well taken care of.

He is well versed in English and mandarin so communication is no problem. He answers to all our queries and ensure that we get our transport that we require in advance.

Rooms are pretty new, pillows are thick and bed is firm enough for my liking. There are also restaurants and market walking distance from this hotel. Come here and try for yourself!

I stayed 3 nights with my family in October 2023. Jay warmly welcome us, we were celebrating my dad's birthday and he provided us nice rooms and delicious breakfast. He kindly explained to us how to adjust the room temperature and where are the locations of the hotel facilities. The staff were all very sincere, kind, friendly. One one they even packed a bento lunch for us. This is the best hotel I have stayed in Korea during my 2 visits there. If I am back at Jeju I will definately stay at this hotel again. I actually thought I wrote a review, but it seems i missed out.

Hotel The Grang Seogwipo.vicinity: 16, Jungjeong-ro, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, Republic of Korea 제주특별자치도 서귀포시 중정로 16 (서귀동, 호텔더그랑서귀포, 특별자치도, Seogwipo

reviews.text: Best hotel to stay. Affordable price, location close to main attractions. Mini mart just in front of hotel.
Clean rooms, lovely staff and amazing restaurant in walking distance
Not bad
Clean cosy
I often use the Sunrise Seongsan branch, so this time I visited the Seopjiko branch. I think the Seongsan branch was better in all aspects, including cleanliness and bedding location.

reviews.text: A place where you can enjoy the services available at the pension... There is even a washing machine, so it is convenient to use.

Good value accommodation.
There is a private heated pool so it's great for families to enjoy.
Parking is a bit inconvenient.
Location is good
I had a really nice vacation. Very satisfied. Everything is ready. I definitely want to go again.

Room is nice and clean.
Because of the distance between the parking lot and the accommodation.
Everything is good except taking a carrier on the stone road.
I think it would be the best choice for families with children.

Haerian Hotel.adr_address: 2167-16 Jungmun-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63545, South Korea
Haerian Hotel.name: Haerian Hotel

reviews.text: It looks quite grand and have nice ambience. The staff there are very helpful and friendly. It's very convenient, as there's shops, restaurants and attractions nearby. Would like to stay here again😁
Comfortable and clean room and excellent price

I usually use the Benikea Hotel across the street, but this time I used this hotel to try a different place. This hotel is not actually a hotel, but rather the entrance reminds me of an old motel... and the room reminds me of a condo. Especially here, there is a washing machine in every room. Looking around the room, I think this place was probably made to be rented out as a studio rather than a hotel.  Therefore, it is a highly recommended accommodation for long-term guests.

The owner is kind and always
Please keep it clean and keep things simple in your room.
It's great because it can be cooked.
There is a supermarket right in front
Also, the price is good and cost-effective.
I love it so much

It is a condo-type room, spacious and comfortable, and quiet despite being located in the Jungmun complex.
There are many convenience stores and marts nearby with a variety of food options.
It's easy to eat according to your taste, it's close to the pharmacy, Saekdal Beach, and thanks to the friendly owner, I had a great vacation^^
A place I want to come back to~

Jeju Shinhwa World Landing Resort.adr_address: South Korea, 63521, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, Andeok-myeon, Sinhwayeoksa-ro, 304번길 38 KR
Jeju Shinhwa World Landing Resort.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, Andeok-myeon, Sinhwayeoksa-ro, 304번길 38 KR
Jeju Shinhwa World Landing Resort.name: Jeju Shinhwa World Landing Resort

reviews.text:
Stayed there for 2 nights and overall, was quite disappointing.
1. Free Shinhwa Theme Park vouchers were provided by the front desk did not explain what the vouchers were for
2. Front desk directed us to the wrong level
3. Front desk did not explain that toothbrush and toothpaste are not provided
4. Aircon in the hotel is centralised (I.e. you can’t adjust the temperature at all. You can only on/off it)
5. Hotel does not loan you any utensils and expects you to purchase from the convenience store (which is actually not that near to where we are staying)
6. Location is not the best
7. Do not provide additional water other than the usual 1 bottle/day/guest

If you are not going to the Theme Park in the hotel, suggest to stay somewhere else instead given the price.

One of the worst hotel I have ever stayed in my entire life, the room has very strong stinky smells, the bed sheet is absolutely filthy,bathroom has fungus, if you are staying this hotel swimming pool is not allowed to use, the manager in the check in counter is very rude,we had to check out early as we can not spend another night in this hotel , it was a disaster! Not to recommend to anyone!

Good things:
1. The hotel is besides the theme park and shopping mall, a free 3-ride theme park voucher is given per guest.
2. Considering no.1, the hotel room rate is quite reasonable.

Bad things:
1. The room sound isolation is not good, there is always noise coming from the next room.
2. Drinking Water is not free, 2000 won per bottle.
3. Service is not really good, maybe due to high volume of guests compared to workers to serve the guests.

Upscale, friendly service, and clean.  Breakfast buffet entrance can get a little backed up, but the food is pretty good (with a menu that caters to Korean, western, and Chinese palates).

Only downside is - for whatever reason, the Jeju Island government makes hotels turn off air conditioning on 10/1.  So, you'll have to leave the window open overnight, because the temps can still hit 70°F in October here.
It's five star property, huge  space, lots of activities and things to do.
