\uc81c\uc8fc\uc2e0\ub77c\ud638\ud154\uc2.formatted_address: 75 Jungmungwangwang-ro 72beon-gil, Saekdal-dong, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
\uc81c\uc8fc\uc2e0\ub77c\ud638\ud154\uc2.name: 제주신라호텔수영장

reviews.text: Adult pool only. no more kid
Traditional but crowded

There is a separate adult pool, so families and couples can have fun. The general pool is connected indoors and outdoors, so you can enjoy a warm swim even in winter. It seems better than other hotels nearby.

The good thing is that since children are not allowed, the atmosphere is quiet, and even if the weather is windy and cold, the water temperature in the pool is warm, and the hot spring pool massages your waist and back with a strong stream of water.. Good!!

The Jjamppong and fried chicken eaten in the zippered tent were also great.
Jjambbong with whole abalone, 2~3 shrimp, kaibashi... 100% satisfied.
I especially liked the fact that there was a hot air fan in the tent.
There are two beach chairs in front of the tent towards the pool,,, and the staff guided me as to which beach chairs to use.
I am having a great time thanks to the excellent facilities and friendly staff...

Bathrobes in the pool are provided only in winter, and basic swimsuits and goggles can be rented at the locker front for convenience. Unlimited towels are provided and there is also a kick board, which is perfect for beginners in swimming.  Beach chairs are free in the kids pool, so it's hard to get a seat, but you actually don't have time to sit on the beach chairs. Before the coronavirus, you could eat on beach chairs, but these days you can only eat at the poolside bar... Since indoor chairs are often empty, it seems better to eat indoors. Couples can use the adult pool relatively comfortably, and I highly recommend Chadol Jjamppong! Adding rice is a must!

Jeju Shinhwa World Marriott Resort.adr_address: South Korea, 63522, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, 38 Sinhwayeoksa-Ro 304beon-Gil Andeok-Myeon,Seogwipo-Si

editorial_summary.overview: Relaxed rooms in a polished hotel offering a gym, a spa & a restaurant, plus indoor & outdoor pools.

Jeju Shinhwa World Marriott Resort.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, 38 Sinhwayeoksa-Ro 304beon-Gil Andeok-Myeon,Seogwipo-Si
Jeju Shinhwa World Marriott Resort.name: Jeju Shinhwa World Marriott Resort

reviews.text: This hotel is Marriot comfort. The room is large, comfortable and very quiet. The pool is very nice and you can choose between outside or inside. The entire complex is for the guest's enjoyment. You have many restaurants to choose from and a casino. Highly recommended if you are in the area and need a break

Loved our time. Very clean and welcoming. Everyone was friendly and helped anytime we asked. The breakfast buffet was like no other we have experienced in Korea. Taxi from airport about $40. Stayed May 24-27, 2024. The only downfall was that the entire waterpark was not open. Will return.

진짜 재밌음. Absolutely amazing, I went there with friends and it was a time of my life. The rooms were absolutely luxurious for the condos. Feels like a paradise community with everything you need, a mall, convenience stores, a bowling alley, etc. Although, the waterpark and theme park could use more scarier and extreme rides and maybe to be a bit larger. I wish it was closer to the city though for the attractions. Definitely an amazing experience for tourists that want to enjoy the city of 제주도.

Pros:
Large, clean, bright rooms
High-quality breakfast

Cons:
Thin walls (noise can easily travel between rooms)
Overcrowded breakfast area

Overall:
This hotel is okay for a business trip, but I would not recommend it for a leisure stay. The rooms are functional but not very inviting, and the breakfast situation can be quite chaotic.

Additional details:
The rooms themselves are not very soundproof.
The breakfast buffet offers a wide variety of high-quality food, but the breakfast room is often overcrowded.

Recommendation:
If you are looking for a comfortable and relaxing place to stay, I would recommend looking elsewhere. However, if you are simply looking for a clean and functional place to stay for a business trip, this hotel may be a good option for you.

This resort has very nice rooms. Amazing employees, very kind and very helpful. Asking to take out bags up to our room and seeing if they could help us with anything else. The sky pool was incredibly relaxing with a beautiful view. The 3 rides we rode at the theme park were a lot more enjoyable than we initially thought they would be. They surprised us in a good way. A majority of the water park rides seemed to be closed such as the big family tube ride, lazy river, kids area, and tube slide by the family tube slide area.

What I wasn’t happy about was how many rules there were. We were not allowed to have drinks near the pool. Not allowed to have a beer can in the casino but could have it in a cup. One if the days at the sky pool it was raining pretty hard, the employees took the umbrellas down whilst the rainstorm was currently happening and when I asked if we could keep it up to keep our stuff dry, I was told no but when there was lightning within 5 nm money was told to get out of the water not wore umbrellas taken down. We couldn’t have a disposable cup inside Häagen-Dazs from Häagen-Dazs when the place was not busy. There was us and another group/family at the tables near us. We got asked to leave the store with it. You can’t drink a beer you got at Store A and bring it to Store B. Not inclusive of other company’s also on the restart. Almost like it’s a competition. Meanwhile, at other resorts usually if you buy it anywhere on the resort it is welcome because you got it on the resort grounds.

Maybe this place is better when it’s in season rather than out. I wasn’t mad just disappointed in how some things were done.

Seogwipo JS Hotel.adr_address: 51 Gimjeongmunhwa-ro, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63566, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Understated rooms in a refined hotel featuring a restaurant, an indoor pool & a sauna, plus a gym.

Seogwipo JS Hotel.name: Seogwipo JS Hotel

reviews.text: The staff are nice and kind. The room and facilities are also good. I got an ocean view. There is a garden and swimming pool at the rooftop. But during my visit, the swimming pool is closed. I think it was because the weather is still chilly. Overall, I had a great stay

A really nice budget hotel close to the World Cup Stadium. The hotel isn’t close to Downtown Seogpiwo but not far (10 mins ride on the bus). It’s clean and quiet. The staff is also helpful and friendly. They have many green campaigns to make you want to help use less water and save the earth which I personally really enjoy. If you like a quiet place and don’t mind staying far from Downtown, this hotel is a great choice.

I’m not sure who wrote the other reviews but they misrepresent the nice hotel. The hotel was great for our 3 days over New Years. Our room was spacious, had nice amenities in our room like tea and coffee, fridge with bottled waters, a balcony, and nice bathroom toiletries. For an incredible price of less than $65 a night, could not find something like this in the US in such a beautiful location.

Room are new and cosy. But if you’re driving SUV/MPV, there isn’t any parking lots for such size of vehicles within the hotel. You will be directed to an open public carpark which is 200-300m away, up a slope. This carpark can be full as well. Staffs can’t really speak English so not east to communicate.

Room is clean, but it's facing another building at such near proximity it made me feel so claustrophobic. Open the window to a wall at your face.
Hotel staff could not communicate well in English and we had a hard time trying to get our messages across.
Otherwise, location is great as it's near the tourist attractions by car, there's a 7-11 next to the hotel lobby and it's opp a huge emart which is a short 5 mins walk away.

Jeju Lemon Balm Stay.adr_address: 1673-1 Goseong-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63641, South Korea
Jeju Lemon Balm Stay.formatted_address: 1673-1 Goseong-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Jeju Lemon Balm Stay.name: Jeju Lemon Balm Stay

reviews.text:
Old but well-maintained rooms, exotic landscaping and lighting. Even at a reasonable price.

Great accommodation with no reason not to come back again

When I woke up in the morning and went out to the terrace, I was very happy to see Seongsan Ilchulbong. It seemed like a lot of attention was paid to the surrounding scenery. Because I went in late in the evening and left early in the morning, I was very disappointed that I couldn't spend much time. The accommodation was also clean.

This is a place where the owner has put a lot of work into it.
There is a garden filled with the scent of rosemary, so it would be great to have a barbecue there! If you pack raw fish at the raw fish center near Seongsan Port and buy meat at Nonghyup next to Starbucks, you can have a much better meal than eating at a restaurant!
Spend your vacation in a quiet and secluded place!

Although the landscaping is good, I could not rest properly due to the noise. It is not a completely independent house, but is attached to the room next door, so the noise from the nearby rooms is transmitted intact, so I often wake up from the pounding noise and vibration from early in the morning. Part of it is walking around on the wooden deck connected to the front of the room.

A cute puppy welcomes me lol
The accommodation is very clean and nice, but it would have been better if the weather had been good. It's a pity.
The accommodation itself is highly recommended.

WE Hotel Jeju.adr_address: 453-95 1100-ro, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63554, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Polished rooms with mountain or sea views in an upscale hotel offering elegant dining, plus a spa.

WE Hotel Jeju.name: WE Hotel Jeju

reviews.text: A wonderful relaxing break. We stayed 5 days. Forest walks, sauna, swimming pools. They also include complimentary classes (aqua relaxing, Crystal bowl, forest tour etc). Food (breakfast, lunch, dinner) is excellent. Shuttle bus available into Jungmun, but you will need transport / taxi to visit other locations. Overall, thoroughly recommended for a relaxing time.

From the moment I arrived, the staff was being exceptionally kind and attentive. The hotel itself looks really luxurious. One of the highlights of my stay was the incredible swimming pool and the green peaceful surroundings. It really is a place where you can relax perfectly. We had six nights, but I wish we stayed longer. I highly recommend staying at WE hotel and I will definitely be returning in the future.

Went for a Girls Trip and had an amazing time. Make sure you try the Aqua Therapy.
The staff was great! Room service is available. I wish I could have stayed longer. I will definitely be going back!

We couldn't help but feel that our stay here did not match our expectations. The setting is incredible and staff are really friendly but there were a few downfalls. It is marketed as a health and wellness resort but being family friendly, there are often many children playing loudly in the pool so it is not a relaxing experience. I feel this could be improved by introducing adult-only hours of use. We were booked for a health service only to be told the next day when we arrived for it that there was no one who could do it and they wouldn't return for a month- I feel they should have known that the day before at the booking time, we rescheduled our day around this appointment. The hotel boasts 2 restaurants, a cafe and room service but all 4 have the same limited menu. Perhaps the worst part though was paying 26,000 won for 2 coffees...
Aside from these things we were very grateful for the staff who were patient with our language barrier and always friendly and attentive. They definitely deserve 5 stars.

great place to stay if you want to have a good rest. spacious, tranquil, and with lots of amenities. beautiful and well maintained rooms, common areas and surroundings. their private forest is like a huge, well-kept garden. love the heated pools - so enjoyable in winter. staff are well trained. concierge is very helpful in providing tips on where to go. lots of good restaurants nearby and at Jungmun area. likely to stay here again.

edit: i returned in Summer and the place was packed! still enjoyed my stay very much, although it was not possible to park near to the hotel.

Hotel The Born Jeju.adr_address: 18 Saekdal-ro, 특별자치도 Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63534, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Down-to-earth hotel featuring 2 restaurants & a cafe, plus a fitness center & breakfast.

Hotel The Born Jeju.formatted_address: 18 Saekdal-ro, 특별자치도 Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Hotel The Born Jeju.name: Hotel The Born Jeju

reviews.text: I have been trying to contact the hotel to cancel the a reservation for last few days but couldn't reach them. I sent 4 inquiry through hotel's website and sent them 3 emails but no response at all. I guess I have to make a international call to cancel the reservation.  Worst customer service !!  If someone from hotel see this post, please check hotel's email !!!!!
Good service mind staff reasonable price for neat room with good bathroom and so many good deals coming along!
Bang for the buck? Exactly right. Room condition, amenities, buffet restaurant, many coupons for the restaurants around the hotel. Parking lot is a little crowded.
This is my favourite place for beef brisket on Jeju. It is Korean BBQ so you cook it yourself on a brazier at your table. Nice fresh vegetables and soups too!

This hotel is very clean and has reasonable price. The cafe and cafeteria in this hotel also serve well foods and coffees. I think foreign people like it. It is similar with the standard international 3 star hotels.

M_STAY Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63595, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, Taepyeong-ro 353beon-gil, 18-1

editorial_summary.overview: Understated rooms & suites, some offering sea views, in a relaxed hotel offering a spa & dining.

M_STAY Hotel.name: M_STAY Hotel

reviews.text:
Nice hotel to discover Jeju.

+
The hotel is idealy situated, near shops and restaurants.
Rooms are large and confortable, we had also a nice view on the sea.
Breakfast is copious and relatively diverse.

-
The carpet in the room is really old, stained and spotted. Same in the breakfast room.
Overall, we can feel the hotel is old and would require a small refresh.
just good to lodge for business stay. the breakfast is nice as for the present status because of the price.
Just ok, no tea and coffee ĺ but 1 free breakfast for 2day stay
Good location and clean room
Lovely hotel. I will recommend

Sunny Day Jeju Pension.adr_address: 131 Daepo-ro, Daepo-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63544, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Relaxed rooms featuring kitchenettes & balconies in a low-key hotel with parking & a BBQ area.

Sunny Day Jeju Pension.formatted_address: 131 Daepo-ro, Daepo-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Sunny Day Jeju Pension.name: Sunny Day Jeju Pension

reviews.text: nice boss, nice room, very big and clean, just different from the modern hotel.
Nice view!!!

It's such a great place to stay that I regret arriving late at night and leaving after only sleeping. I have never left before check-out time, but perhaps because I slept well, I woke up in a good mood in the morning. For a much cheaper price than a hotel, the room was cozy and really clean. There were plenty of towels, a large bottle of water in the refrigerator, and the lighting was good. I had a quick chat with the owner before leaving, and he said that the accommodation was built using imported wood from Finland, and that the doors and windows were also imported from France. For some reason, as I entered the entrance, I could smell a lot of wood, and it was really nice. The charm of a tree house is, of course, the smell of wood! The well-groomed lawn, stone path, and stone steps were beautiful, and I was healed while looking at the garden, which was tastefully maintained with palm trees and various plants. Next time, I want to bring my family and take a walk and chat on the garden bench. They also run a tangerine field in the back. I'd like to check it out next time. Because of the coronavirus, I can only go to Jeju Island, but it seems like I went on a trip abroad. I am happy because I found a good place to stay and was able to relieve the stress of the day and start the next day in a good mood. I'm using it well. Thank you, boss. take care of yourself.

Should I explain that the owner is proud of the accommodation and is comfortable on the eyes? Since there was nothing special nearby, I wondered if I could see the stars, but I couldn't because the weather was bad. If you're ordering delivery food, I recommend Oppa Chicken and Soy Sauce Melting Chicken. It's spicy but delicious.

The view is great and the cleanliness and maintenance are very good for the price. The bed was a bit disappointing and the floor was creaky due to the nature of the log cabin. I tried to be as careful as possible, but I had no choice but to hear some of my noise from downstairs, and I think the noise from downstairs may have come up.

Breeze Bay Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63643, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, Seongsan-eup, Seongsandeungyong-ro, 42

editorial_summary.overview: Unfussy rooms & suites, some with bay views, in a casual hotel offering breakfast & parking.

Breeze Bay Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, Seongsan-eup, Seongsandeungyong-ro, 42
Breeze Bay Hotel.name: Breeze Bay Hotel

reviews.text:
No frills hotel, big clean room, but the TV console is bent with the weight of the TV. The toilet is bare and simple.

Biggest plus is view of the sea.

Biggest grouse is towel. We booked a room for 4 but they only gave us mini face towel. When we asked, the staff only gave 2 big towel each day.

Travelled with a group of friends and booked the Premier Quadruple room. Very rare to find a hotel with 4 single beds. Stayed for 1 night and overall was a great experience. No toiletries except for towels, shampoo, body wash, conditioner were provided. Hence, you have to prepare your own. Parking lots were available during our stay. Convenient store was located just beside the hotel.
Great hotel, lobby is quite no-frills but hotel room is very clean and well-maintained. Rooms also have an amazing view of the bay. Overall a quiet but very peaceful area to visit.

Location was great had a beautiful ocean view and could see the sunset. Beds were clean and the bathroom was nice. Breakfast was average but it was good enough to where we ate there every morning. Walking distance to many places.
They charged extra towel fee even though their room is worn out. I wish it would be helpful for their renovation for their uncozy room ;(

Jeju Ocean Blue Hotel.adr_address: 2538 Daepo-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 697-320, South Korea
Jeju Ocean Blue Hotel.name: Jeju Ocean Blue Hotel

reviews.text: The gentleman at the front desk was extremely kind and helpful. He even called the restaurant I wanted to go to beforehand and told them my vegan diet options. Rooms are clean, affordable, and very well located if you're attending an event at the ICC.

This is a good place for solo/pair travellers on a budget. The room is clean, sufficiently big for 1/2 person, heater is working great. Location wise there are limited food options within walking distance, but a
Ocean view room, unpredictable cleaning service, rooms to be renovated.

Rooms have good ventilation, and all necessary acessaries. Staff is really nice to the customers. One can approach to two popular water falls, and the airport easily through bus number 600. A good sea side walking track, and cliffs 500m away.  Restaurants and convenience stores are a bit far away.

Amazing small hotel in South of Jeju. The owner is one amazing friendly Woman, who does everything to make her guests happy. The rooms have Sea view and a nice hiking trail (Jeju olle) is just 5 minutes away. The ICC is 5 minutes by foot away. The rooms are clean and Modern. There's water, coffee and tea provided in the room every day. Loved it. Best hotel

CO-OP City Hotel Seongsan.adr_address: South Korea, 63643, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, Seongsan-eup, Seongsan-ri, 250 KR

editorial_summary.overview: Colorful quarters in a relaxed hotel offering a restaurant & a pub, plus a rooftop terrace.

CO-OP City Hotel Seongsan.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, Seongsan-eup, Seongsan-ri, 250 KR
CO-OP City Hotel Seongsan.name: CO-OP City Hotel Seongsan

reviews.text:
Great location. Small rooms, but good prices.

Overall a good hotel if you just want to use it to sleep and be close to all the fun stuff.

Hotel is lousy. 1) Lobby has a cheap perfume fragrance like a sleasy hotel 2) website says hv washing machine but they disabled the dryer function, dumb! 3) towels hv a terrible stink 4) overhead aircon gives us a headache next morning 5) barking dog next door syarts barking its head off at 530am 6) feather pillows were thin and useless 7) hotel has no adaptors, no humidifiers at all 8) view nothg to pay extra for..same view standinf at lobby 9) 7-11 cl9ses btw 10am and 530pm.
Great service and perfect for somewhere cheap and easy to stay. Close to a number of beaches and local landmarks.

Was greeted by amazing sunset view right at the entrance of the hotel when we arrive. Think they may have upgraded our room to one with beautiful borderless ocean view. Hotel building exterior looks old when we were driving towards it but lobby and room look very modern and bright. Parking is available at level 1 if ground floor is full. Entrance and exit of the level 1 parking lot looks a bit dangerous as it is single lane slope for cars coming from both directions but thankfully we did not encounter any cars coming in opposite directions when we drive in and out. Room is spacious and comfortable. There is self service laundry room but we did not use as it is a simple household standard washer cum dryer machine. All in all, it did surpass our expectations.

Great location, helpful staff, comfortable rooms.

Really good view from the rooftop bar too.

YAKMAEUL (BLACK YAK).adr_address: 162 Saekdaljungang-ro, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 697-130, South Korea
YAKMAEUL (BLACK YAK).name: YAKMAEUL (BLACK YAK)

reviews.text: Luxurious & private resort!!

I went on a 3-day, 2-night trip to Yak Village full suite.
It was great to be able to rest in a comfortable accommodation after traveling to Jeju and travel again with pleasure the next day.
I was happy to be able to take a refreshing swim in the pool after returning from my trip.
Parents also return home delighted with the luxurious facilities and atmosphere.
I think the walking trail is also nice, but I'm so sad that I couldn't go there, so I'd like to visit again if I have the chance next time.

I stayed with my family for 3 days and 2 nights :)
It’s such a beautiful accommodation!

I stayed in a full suite room.
The kids loved that the heated pool was open 24 hours a day.
The outdoor pool was also great.

I was able to barbecue too.
I couldn't help but be intoxicated by the atmosphere on the deck next to the pool.

Compared to other pool villas, even if it is a pool villa, lukewarm water fee is charged separately.
Rather, it felt cheap.
Satisfaction was very high :)

Breakfast was also clean.
Drink coffee at the parrot cafe
Take a good rest!
Next time, I want to use the camping site too.
It was emotional.

The accommodation was a separate building, beautiful and well-maintained, and the swimming pool was quiet and clean, which was nice.
The location was in Saekdal-dong, Jungmun and transportation was good.

We stayed 2 nights in a full suite and 1 night in a living suite for a family trip^^
It was great to play with the kids as it was a full villa.
You can play in the water with your family privately in the pool suite, and then move to the living suite and play in the central public swimming pool for three nights. 🙂
It got a little chilly at night, so I warmed up in the jacuzzi after swimming.
Even though they said it was full, the surrounding area was very quiet and there weren't many people at the swimming pool, so it was better~~
Because it's a place to play in the water, there were plenty of towels and a jacuzzi, so it was nice to be able to warm up after swimming.
It's nice to take a walk around the area, and the Dudo Restaurant and Seoul Parrot Cafe inside are very delicious, spacious, and clean.

Basic cooking was also possible in the kitchen.
It was long from the entrance to the inside of the house, so it was good for the kids to run and play. There were three bathrooms, and there were solid shampoos, treatments, and body bars, so I used them very well.

The bedding was clean and comfortable, and the mattress was wide and not high, so I slept well without falling off even when I rolled around on the bed. The heating and cooling system works well.

I had a great time and slept well.
I had planned to go sightseeing, but the kids wanted to stay at the hotel ^^;; hahaha.
I recommend a fun, quiet, and comfortable stay with children!!!
I will visit again when I come to Jeju!!

Terrace Hill.adr_address: South Korea, 63311, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Wolpyeong-dong, 965-2 KR
Terrace Hill.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, Wolpyeong-dong, 965-2 KR
Terrace Hill.name: Terrace Hill

reviews.text: I would give 1000 stars if possible. This property is spacious, clean and close to the city and attractions. The owner and his wife are really good persons. My brother slipped due to slippery surface (snow) and broke his arm, I brought him to hospital but getting refused of any services because we don't have insurance. The owner and his wife drove us again to the same hospital and manage to get my brother treated, and even insisted to pay for the hospital bill. I have no words to describe how helpful they are, this review won't do any justice to both of them. I definitely recommend this property to anyone.
Awesome lodging in Jeju! Recommended for family esp! Spacious and clean! Daebak for the dryer which dries our winter clothes so fast!

Place is very well kept and clean and has everything a family needs for an extended stay. Close to jeju city and pretty much everything else given that jeju is not that big anyway. I would recommend this place for families with pets
It was a good place to stay. Bus stop was convenient to use. The place is centrally located. If you don't have a car, this is a good place to stay and use the bus.
We stayed at 2nd floor with family. This apartment no lift.

Hanwha Resort Jeju.adr_address: South Korea, 63345, Jeju-do, Cheju, Bonggae-dong, Myeongnim-ro, 575-107 제주특별자치도

editorial_summary.overview: Tranquil island hotel with straightforward suites, plus a restaurant, a bar & a spa.

Hanwha Resort Jeju.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, Bonggae-dong, Myeongnim-ro, 575-107 제주특별자치도
Hanwha Resort Jeju.name: Hanwha Resort Jeju

reviews.text:
We used this mainly just as a “base” when visiting and exploring Jeju. The unit was spacious, clean and modern (ours was 2 bedroom) with 2 showers and toilets. With a family it would’ve been nicer to have a larger fridge with freezer box rather than the tiny minibar one but that’s a minor point.

The unit had a sofa, coffee table, dining table with 4 chairs, 2 TVs, kitchenette with microwave, hob, kettle and basic crockery and cutlery.

Nice on-site mini-market selling a wide range of snacks and drinks and other essentials. We used the launderette which was handy and well equipped.

It’s a big resort and easy to get lost wandering around the various corridors. Familiarise yourself with the layout beforehand.

We’d definitely stay here again!

Price reasonable located in silent place but it's not really close to downtown the city of Jeju which is the only thing. Others are good. But not far. You can check it. The food is good. There is a lake in the back of the building. You can take a walk. Pretty fresh feeling you enjoy.

I spent the weekend with my family in this resort, the facilities are good although they lack a bit of remodeling, the place we stayed had two rooms, a large room that includes kitchen, a bathroom with tub, we had enough bedspreads, and there were also kitchen utensils such as ceramic plates and cups, chopsticks, forks, spoons, and knives. The television has different channels to watch and there is also a menu to order food (chicken, pizza, raw fish Korean style) from the room.  Before sleeping, you can go down to the L floor and enjoy musical performances by artists at the beer bar. To one side is the playground, to play you have to carry cash because it does not accept a card. I spent my time singing in the karaoke machine until 1 am. It’s super cool because it is a personal area and you do not have interruptions, there are no people who look at you or listen to you. The next day, I went to the buffet and it is from 7 to 10 am, there is a variety of Korean and foreign food, there are desserts such as waffles, breads, tiramisu pastries, cereals and juices of orange, apple, tomato, among others. The check out is at 11 am. Before leaving, my sister rode the bicycle and my brother and I played soccer in the parking lot since it is large enough. I would go back to this place without a doubt.

It is located in a very quiet place. Very close to the Jeolmul forrest and 4.3 memorial. Rooms need to be renovated. Staffs are friendly.
It is okay to stay but not good for the price you pay.

We went there about 3 years ago for high school excursion and I couldn't even think about writing review of what we had there because of anger. So as I said, 3 years ago we were high school students. When we got there, inside of the room, it was terrible as hell cuz people in room was 10 and pillows, there were only 4. What would you do if you were in that situation? Of course calling for more pillows and you know what person in front ignored even some of us actually went down for that god damn pillows. And other thing, person stayed a story above us smoked in veranda and that cigar ash came right through our room. Also that claim was ignored lol. So if you are planning on visiting this resort and you are student, please don't go, don't waste your time and money on that

The Best Jeju Seongsan Hotel.adr_address: 26 Dongnyuam-ro, Seongsan-eup, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63640, South Korea
The Best Jeju Seongsan Hotel.formatted_address: 26 Dongnyuam-ro, Seongsan-eup, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
The Best Jeju Seongsan Hotel.name: The Best Jeju Seongsan Hotel

reviews.text: Overall good. Convenient store at lobby is ideal. Didn’t bother about the location since we rented car in Jeju. Simple breakfast to fill stomach.
Breakfast is 12,000 won for adult. Pretty decent. Pool is extra charge 10,000. Very good view. Close to restaurants.
Great service, very welcoming staff. Breakfast was good for the price, but staff made it worth while. Kitchen and wait staff were very professional and helpful. Overall, worth the money.
Best Jeju Seongsan is not located here. It is at the Ramada Encore Jeju Seongsan site.
nice place for vacation and taste Korean food.  Top root swimming pool is the BEST location to see the whole view.

Nine boutique hotel.adr_address: 647-1 Seogwi-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63596, South Korea
Nine boutique hotel.name: Nine boutique hotel

reviews.text: Let's start with the good points first. We booked the penthouse at the top sixth floor and it was spacious, well-equipped with toys for my child, a water dispenser, microwave and not forgetting a breathtaking, spectacular view of the sea and mountains. What sets this hotel apart from the rest is its rigid policy pertaining to breakfast. The only window where food is served is 8am to 9am, the kitchen closes at 9am punctually and accommodation is made only if one implored hard enough. This is not a kid-friendly accommodation so young families who are keen to still stay here should be cognizant of what they signed up for through my personal experience. On my first morning, I had to plead loud and hard before the staff relented and allowed me to bring a sunny side to my room because I missed the window by a few minutes. As a grown up, it's fine if I do not eat. But I would really find it disdainful if my toddler is deprived of food just because I am not able to make it in time. Eventually, they permitted me to bring a miserly fried egg to my room to feed my child. On the second morning, my husband was dressing my toddler and as most parents can resonate, is not an easy nor smooth process. Seeing we cannot make it in time to be physically present for our breakfast, I headed down once again to request for some food to be taken up to the room for my kid's meal. This time, I was told every person has to come down personally. My child just pooped, my husband is showering my kid. It was 8.36am. Are we supposed to rush like hell and be all stressed up just to ensure my kid is fed? For God's sake, we are on holiday. I was told by the staff our holiday here has no business with them. Then hello, why run a business in the hospitality industry if making your foreign visitors comfortable is not your goal? Or are these folks only interested in the lucrativeness of the business that they would rather trade their customers' happiness for money? Is my request really unreasonable as a mother? Plus, it's served to me instead of buffet style so why is your team worried or fearful about serving me one or two fried eggs to the room? You are afraid the green plate would not be returned, or be stolen? If making money is more important than being hospitable, please, please, I highly suggest you consider to pivot and do something else instead of you cannot practise the simple principle of "give and take"!  Perhaps none of the staff are parents, epitomised by their inability to resonate with my situation. Money is not an issue, sure we can always head out to purchase some food for my child. This is not the main crux of my nasty encounter, though. It reflects palpably the appalling void of flexibility and compassion, and how much they are willing to go to demonstrate they care. This place makes a groundbreaking impression in my memory as one that is mercilessly strict, void of charity and unwilling to make concessions unless the plaintiff exhibits sufficient desperation. I highly suggest you either seriously reflect about lengthening the breakfast window till 10am or fold your business. The green plate that you care about so dearly, exponentially more than a child's hunger and welfare, is left at your front desk near your computer. Good day.
Incompetent staff. We asked to book a taxi for the airport early in the morning but we never had it and were left alone in our situation. They do not speak English well enough. Nice room however.
Convenient parking, cheap price, good lighting, large indoor square footage. If you come to Seogwipo, you can consider staying here.

Very friendly and good facilities. There's plenty of parking and it's nice.
I would like to stay more nights, but there are no rooms available so I have to move.
Good value mid-range hotel

Libentia Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63010 Jeju-do Jeju-si Villa & Hotel 리벤시아, 월령리 254-1, 한림읍
Libentia Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do Jeju-si Villa & Hotel 리벤시아, 월령리 254-1, 한림읍
Libentia Hotel.name: Libentia Hotel

reviews.text:
A newly built resort-like hotel tucked away along the coast of Hallim, Jeju Island.  Excellent value in every way.

New Chef by the name of Kim Soo Hong ( Luke) came to our table and personally explained how he prepared the evening meal. When Chef Kim learned of our dietary restrictions ( no dairy, no sodium), he went out of his way to prepare a full breakfast for us which was divine. We couldn't be happier.

A highlight of this hotel is the beautiful pool on the roof deck. The pool temperature was absolutely perfect when we went for a morning swim.  Pool deck -- an ideal place to enjoy sunset.

From the hotel manager, Choi Jin Soo to the front desk clerk, every staff member was kind, and accommodating.

Suggestion for the hotel --  need to create a place to hang bathrobes and towels.  By the way, we were surprised that there were no elevators. However, the staff was very gracious in offering to carry our bags to the second floor.
Hotel and villas are lovly people are real nice who work there

This is a review of a 4-day, 3-night stay in Villa D...
1. Vehicles are not allowed in the villa building.
2. There is no mirror in the bathroom
3.Shoes get dirty when it rains
4. When staying in a villa, luggage is transported by car.
5. There were a lot of construction vehicles due to remodeling work on the date of stay.
6. I plan to make another reservation after remodeling.
7. There is a convenience store meat restaurant just 3km to the right of the villa’s main gate.
8. What the owner said about providing breakfast after remodeling
Room condition and amenities are good. And it's okay because there's a rooftop pool. There are not many amenities nearby, but there is a place where you can eat or drink within a short walk.

This is where I stayed for one night, and the hotel also had welcome wine. It seems like they run both a pool villa and a hotel. There are no photos of the surroundings or the room, but it was a pretty neat place. However, it was a little disappointing that there were no convenience facilities nearby.

Libentia Hotel.vicinity: Villa & Hotel 리벤시아, 월령리 254-1, 한림읍, Jeju-si

Spring and Fall Resort.adr_address: 2660 Haemajihaean-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63638, South Korea
Spring and Fall Resort.formatted_address: 2660 Haemajihaean-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Spring and Fall Resort.name: Spring and Fall Resort

reviews.text: Helpful staff. But I was not informed of the indoor pool though it was raining heavy and the staff could see I was with a child non of them mentioned the indoor child's pool. However, I would like stay here again because of its location and to be frank it has some good facilities. Inside the room, there are pots and pans, and even a rice cooker. We never used them, but for a longer visit those items would be very useful especially if you are traveling on a budget. They also serve breakfast, looking from the photos they had on display, the food seems tasty. Recommend for the kids as they have an indoor playground!!! A+

Ocean view, outdoor pool. Clean rooms, however they only make up the rooms every three days. Fresh towels provided by hanging on your room door. Voucher provided to get wayer at a nearby convenience store. They don't put the water in the room for you. Rooms have a partial kitchen and some cookware. There are theme rooms for children available. Excellent place for parent's with young children.

The place is really beautiful. But with a big rain the balcony was flooded...at first they said we could put towels to avoid water. After that they changed our room. Also so many unsaid rules about bbq use. Rooms are big and clean. It has a lil dining room where u can cook small things.
It was a great fortune to know this place. Comfortable and high-quality services made the trip to Jeju more enjoyable.

very gooood!! my babies were so happy..
and breakfast was good considering price. just 10$. we wanna visit next time..

Hidden Cliff Hotel & Nature.adr_address: 542 Yeraehaean-ro, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63536, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: High-end, tranquil resort offering dining, a spa & a rooftop bar, plus a heated infinity pool.

Hidden Cliff Hotel & Nature.formatted_address: 542 Yeraehaean-ro, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Hidden Cliff Hotel & Nature.name: Hidden Cliff Hotel & Nature

reviews.text: We've had a great time at this hotel. A special thanks to Mrs Lee and Mr An who have been very helpful throughout our stay, with very good understanding of our issues and communicating in english. Thanks to them we had 0 concerns during our stay.

Hidden Cliff is sort of very famous for its infinity pool and quiet surroundings. Breakfast buffet wasn't that good even though sort of it is cheap. Nothing much to eat. Room condition was good enough. However, I rented EV car and there was no charging station which was very inconvenient. It was 2022!!!

1. AC barely works during the day (min temp 23C), turns off completely at night; attempting to sleep is a miserable experience

2. Shampoo and soap are bolted to the shower wall, so you can’t use them in the bathtub because you can’t move them.

3. Outlets in the room turn off power when removing the room key. I was surprised with having none of my devices charged when I returned to my room.

4. poor restaurant service

5. only two elevators serving almost 300 rooms across 7 floors; be prepared to waste time waiting for the elevator

Hard to agree that it's a five star hotel. The facilities are new and fancy, but their attention to detail is far less than one would expect from five stars. Personally, the pool seemed like a filming site; every one was taking photos rather than relaxing, which made me a little annoyed.

We’ve had a really nice five night stay here at Hidden Cliff. Very clean, great service, off the beaten path. Pool is wonderfully warm even in the chilly air, the hike into the ravine is peaceful, breakfast buffet is incredibly expensive but worth trying once. Otherwise there is a McDonald’s about two minutes drive away. South Bounder Brewery is about a minute walk away and there are two convenience stores about two minutes walk away. just a really wonderful stay.

Phoenix island ocean star resort.adr_address: 169, Seopjikoji-ro, Seongsan-eup Korea, 서귀포시 제주특별자치도 63643, South Korea
Phoenix island ocean star resort.formatted_address: 169, Seopjikoji-ro, Seongsan-eup Korea, 서귀포시 제주특별자치도 South Korea
Phoenix island ocean star resort.name: Phoenix island ocean star resort

reviews.text: Too many details to share. Bottom line, this building once was amazing but that was decades ago. it is falling apart. Aside from looking like an abandoned building, nothing was clean anywhere on the property. The lobby was filthy, the hallways were filthy, the elevators were filthy, the dishes, bed and slippers in the room were all filthy. Someone should buy this property and restore it to it's glory. Until then, stay next door at the Phoenix Island Resort.

Save your money and look for other place to stay. This was not a cheap option for me.

I was attracted to the reviews I red few years ago -  "The grandeur and beauty of Seongsan Ilchulbong, is a privilege that can only be enjoyed by guests staying at Phoenix Island Ocean star."

Now? This place is going down. Like you've never seen. I think government have to sieze the whole property and renovate it just to show people that we care about tourist. This was purely the worst experience in my life.

During my recent stay at the Phoenix Island Ocean Star Resort in South Korea, we encountered some issues. Despite being promised three beds, we only found two, along with a mat for the floor. The couch also did not convert into a bed as advertised. Additionally, there were only three cups, four pillows, and no extra blankets, just a sheet. When we asked the resort for assistance, they directed us to contact the host. While the resort provided extra cups and pillows after we contacted the host, they were unable to offer any additional bedding.

The outside looks like something out of a post apocalyptic movie. Very unkept and old. I got the feeling it was a failed business venture that they are just trying to squeeze a few bucks outa it. But the rooms were big and clean. The bathroom has a heated bidet, tho most of the functions did not work and some of the buttons where broken even. The A/C was problematic to say the least. They would not get cold and kept shutting off. Host finally offered to send someone to look at it on the 3rd day, but we were leaving the next day so didn't even bother with it. There isn't a dryer for clothes anywhere in sight. So be ready to go elsewhere to dry your clothes or be prepared to have them smell sour. I got a very good deal at $275 from March 31st-April 4th.

The rooms were big and clean and the view was amazing. And I feel like we got what we paid for. If you're looking for a budget place to stay with a good view and are willing to deal with the bad stuff then it's worth the money.

Scary.
Thats the keyword here. It looks like a Zombie Aopocolypse.

Wallpaper is stapled to the walls. A random raft in the hallways. Danger and caution tape in the "lobby" (if you can even call it that. There seems to be no signs of life inside the hotel except the poor boy who has to work at this asbestos farm. Windows are musty/grimy/I don't even know. Weeds and shrubs are taking over the first 2 floors. Exterior is FILTHY.

Inside the room:
No big towels. No hand towels inside bathrooms. They didn't refill the toilet paper before giving us the room. Kitchen but no silverware to be seen. The balcony next door is SHATRERED. You see my videos. Looks like the hunger games. Also, the hotel room door has a deadbolt that WONT LOCK. It's simply screwed in place or something. And the bedrooms have doors and NO LOCKS. I am so so afraid here. I dont care if it's cheap. Is it worth you life??

I feel like im going to contract something. I'm afraid to breathe or touch this furniature.

I want to gtfo asap tomorrow. F this place.

Donnaeko Pension.adr_address: 28 Donnaeko-ro 67beon-gil, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 697-060, South Korea
Donnaeko Pension.name: Donnaeko Pension

reviews.text:
It's quiet and good for rest.
The room has a spacious kitchen, and they are happy to prepare barbecue in the barbecue area.
Bottled water is not provided, so you must bring your own.

I found this out while looking for a place to stay to go to Hallasan the next day.
It is located away from the downtown area, so the surroundings are quiet.
There are no separate supermarkets or convenience stores nearby, so you have to buy it in advance.
The price is cheap and the owner is very friendly.
It's not clean. The floor is stained.
The blanket is also damp. Towel is also a widower? It smells
I don't know anything else, but the most disappointing thing is that the bedding is damp.

A budget-friendly pension. This is the pension where we stayed for climbing Hallasan Mountain. It is close to Hallasan Mountain, so it is convenient to travel around, and the summit of Hallasan Mountain can be seen from the pension. Although the interior is not sophisticated, it is clean overall and there is no inconvenience in using it. The owner is friendly, but the downside is that the soundproofing is not very good. Still, the next time I go to Hallasan, this is a place I want to stay again.

After spending the day, I was very satisfied with the facility itself. There are children's play equipment and rocking chairs in the pool, and the room is clean and spacious, which is nice. A few shortcomings I felt were that it was a bit difficult to get to in the city center. Stop with the sea too. Because it is near Hallasan Mountain, there are few people. There are almost no cars coming into the pension. So it's quiet, so that might be an advantage. lol

It was very quiet and I rested comfortably before leaving. ^^
Thankfully, the heating worked well so I stayed warm. If you wake up in the morning, I highly recommend taking a walk in the nearby Mandarin Duck Valley👍

Jeju Aerospace Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63521, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, Andeok-myeon, Nokchabunjae-ro, 216 KR

editorial_summary.overview: Contemporary hotel offering a buffet restaurant & event space, plus a business center.

Jeju Aerospace Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, Andeok-myeon, Nokchabunjae-ro, 216 KR
Jeju Aerospace Hotel.name: Jeju Aerospace Hotel

reviews.text: Hotel is very well maintained. Room is clean and spacious except for a funny smell. Bed is medium firm perfect to our liking. The environment is serene and peaceful but felt abit outskirt due to the long winding road. They have two carparks. There's a hot & cold water dispenser on every level and CU store beside the reception. The place met all our needs and we had a very comfortable rest.

The room is very spacious and there’s a balcony. There’s no laundry area. There’s a few AC EV chargers in the vicinity. You will need a transport/taxi to travel around. There’s a CU convenient store near the reception

I had a very good stay there. I dont know the rates for the rooms because it was paid for by my work. I liked the rooms but a few small things would be better. 1. More control over the lighting in the rooms. 2. Ability to turn off the fan in the batroom and shower - its quite noisy but comes on automatically with the light. 3. There are no clocks in the room. A clock would be nice.

Other than that everything else was good including the restaurant and meeting rooms.

This was by far the largest hotel room I had while traveling in South Korea. Room was a little dated, but very clean. Hotel is located kind of in the middle of nowhere, so a vehicle is definitely needed to stay here. Nothing is really walking distance, but it is a good central point for visiting landmarks on the western half of the island. It was also very quiet since it sits far back from the road. There is a convenience store located in the lobby which was nice for grabbing any snacks. A major perk that I think is overlooked is that this hotel is located in very close proximity to the Jeju Aerospace Mueum and Jeju Greem Cafe. The cafe is a 2D art cafe located on the top floor of the museum. You do not need a ticket to go to the cafe. It was practically empty when I was in there having breakfast.

Pleasant stay, highly recommended. Clean, spacious rooms (we had balcony overlooking the green tea fields) and very good location--if you like shopping, it is within a few mins walking distance from Innisfree museum! There's a convenience shop inside the hotel, and it's within a few mins drive/bus to a few attractions e.g. Jeju Aerospace Museum, Innisfree museum, Hello Kitty Island, etc. Staff are also wonderful. Overall a pleasant experience. 10/10 will book this hotel again when we visit West Jeju.

Seongsan Sunrise Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63643, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, Seongsan-eup, Seongsandeungyong-ro 17beon-gil, 35 KR
Seongsan Sunrise Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, Seongsan-eup, Seongsandeungyong-ro 17beon-gil, 35 KR
Seongsan Sunrise Hotel.name: Seongsan Sunrise Hotel

reviews.text: My friend's favorite hotel in Sungsan
must hike up and see the view of the canyon and sun rise. 20 to 40 minutes depends on ur fitness

The floor in the room is carpeted, which I personally dislike.
Considering that dust does not cause sneezing (rhinitis)

Nice Place to Stay.

The scenery is beautiful
But I don’t know why some places on the floor are sticky and uncomfortable.

First of all, the view was so crazy. very pretty..
It was an accommodation with a very beautiful and beautiful view whether it was early in the morning, at night, day or early in the morning.
Although the convenience store or restaurant was far away, you could walk there while chatting with friends, lovers, or couples.
It came out quickly so there was no inconvenience.
Eating breakfast in the morning, looking at the scenery, and getting some fresh air was so relaxing that I didn't want to leave the room.
ah! We recommend that you bring toothpaste with you. There was no toothpaste.

And if you look inside the accommodation, there is a notebook called The Joy of Doodling.
It was a lot of fun reading reviews of Jeju Island visits and other people's posts.
The boss has good sense~

This accommodation has everything you need to see the Seongsan Ilchulbong seen from the room. The view and breakfast are good for the price, but the facilities cannot be compared to hotels. The location of the outlet in room 204 was ambiguous, so it was inconvenient to dry or charge. It would be nice if they at least provided a connection cable. Haruki Wow, it's nice that Borges' books by Park Sang-ryung are on display. The coffee and music of the cafe run by the owner are also to my taste.

reviews.text:
This is my second visit and the room condition is amazing.
The view is fantastic when you wake up in the morning
Room condition is better than Lotte Hotel
The room atmosphere is also very good.
The meat restaurant right next door is also good for dinner.
Boss, I’ll go again next time.

A place I want to give more stars to!
It's a 2-year-old new building and well-built, so it's completely soundproofed and insect-proof, and the bedding is soft, so it's like home!
Plus, you can go fishing at night in front of the accommodation, and Panpo Port is just a stone's throw away!

It was a place where I stayed for 7 nights and 8 days and had an enjoyable trip thanks to the accommodations~^^
I am uploading photos around the accommodation~^^

It's clean and the house is nice, so I think the dehumidification is perfect even at the beach.
The living room and two bedrooms all have full-length or large windows, so the ocean view is beautiful day and night.
There are pavilions and restaurants close by, but there are few bars, so you can enjoy the quiet and tranquil sea.
Even though the surrounding area is famous for snorkeling, it is quiet and secluded.

The supermarket is far away and there is a convenience store nearby.

The kitchen is well-equipped for 4 people, and is equipped with a trendy induction stove, electric kettle, microwave, and refrigerator, making it ideal for long-term stays.

There was construction going on to open a cafe on the first floor, so maybe a cafe will be available in the future.

Non-face-to-face check-in and service suitable for the coronavirus situation were also good.

I stayed in a two-room bathtub room, and since there is a port nearby, it is quiet and not busy, and has a great ocean view. I highly recommend it to those who dislike hustle and bustle and enjoy quiet. Since it is a two-room type, there is a double bed in each room, and the bed is firm, resilient, and soft. In addition to the basic amenities, a hair dryer is provided, and I was grateful that they provided plenty of tableware, hangers, and towels. Cooking is possible, and I don't know if it was remodeled or just built, but it was very clean, and it also has a Bluetooth speaker, so the ocean view has an extra dose of entertainment. will be added. Each room has individual heating and cooling, and of course Wi-Fi. One thing that is disappointing is that when the sun goes down, it may be difficult to find the alley leading to the pension. ^^;; Other than that, everything was satisfactory. I had a nice stay~~~

The scenery is nice. The rooms are also clean.
The electrical outlets are a bit uneasy...
It's not like I'm going to buy it... I guess that's okay.

reviews.text:
The room was clean and spacious. Large bathroom with a hot tub!! The view was good looking over 성산일출봉 but the window was very dirty.
Staff was friendly and very helpful.
Location was great as well, lots of dining options around, great view, many amazing tourist spots are within walkable distance.
Has 5,000won breaky option, which has some basic stuff.

Hotel is near Sunrise Peak, a few mins drive/8mins walk.
Room is tidy but showing some wear and tear. Towels not put in toilet, had to go down to get. Only face towels provided. Not even full body towels...

Have to buy your own toiletries for less than 1usd but that's OK if they had informed ahead of time. I am all for the environmental cause for less waste.

No light switches next to bed. But there are international plugs which is nice.
Mattress is so-so and only 2 very thin pillows are provided....

There is a view but we never stayed to see it as we were there to climb Sunrise Peak.

Room ain't exactly cheap at $60usd for this delivery of standards. I feel it's not value for money.

Great location, easy check in. The restaurant was closed, I think for winter season. The second floor hallway had a bit of a mildew smell but the room was clean and smelled clean too.

The bed had a plastic/rubber protector under the fitted sheet that was not very comfortable to sleep on. If I were staying more than one night I would have removed it.
Room is spacious. Bed a bit hard and uncomfortable. No full body towel provided. Only face towels. No toothbrush and toothpaste provided. Overall is clean. Location in a quiet area.
The view and the room is good, also 50% of room is window, you can enjoy the nice at room, and it comes with jacuzzi. However they don't provide big bath towers.

reviews.text:
The view of Seongsan Ilchulbong from the room is a work of art.
Because it is Seongsan, it is a bit far from Jeju Airport, but it was good to plan a trip to Udo Island and travel to Udo Island.

I highly recommend the terrace room on the first floor:) It had a really nice view and the bedding was Goose, so it was very comfortable. The female owner seemed to be very clean and sensible. Overall, the interior, scents, and trees were well maintained. I went there for a prenatal education trip. I had a good night's sleep for 2 nights because they even provided me with a body pillow. I ate breakfast sandwiches on the outdoor terrace while looking at Seongsan Ilchungbong Peak, and the large window had a sea view, so I woke up to the sound of birds! If I come to Jeju, I will definitely stop by again. The Ojori Village trekking course recommended by the owner. It was so quiet and cute! Thank you.

The owner greets you directly and is friendly. There are many places to take pictures and the view is also nice.

However, if you are not here to take pictures and feel girly, you may be disappointed by the price.
It's slightly different from antique or vintage. There are details that look old and there's nothing special about them. Besides, other than that feeling, there's no killing point...
If you want to relax, it's not bad in many ways!

First of all, the view is nice, the owner is very friendly, and the interior is pretty. I recommend going to Gyorae Black Pork, which is nearby by foot in 5 to 8 minutes. It was nice to be able to have a drink of Udomakgeori as well as meat~

The view is good. However, it is inconvenient because there is no soundproofing, so everything you say in the hallway can be heard, and everything you say in your room can be heard outside.
There are many restrictions, and it is written that if you do not follow them, you will have to compensate for everything, so it is intimidating and not very pleasant.

reviews.text: I had a great stay there. There is a swimming pool on the rooftop. Unfortunately, during my visit, the swimming pool was closed because the weather was still chilly. I could see the Seongsan Ilchulbong from the hotel

Best Jeju Seongsan - Large hotel formerly Ramada Encore. Quiet location with great views toward Seongsan Ilchulbong and sunrise.

Soundproofing could be improved. Central controlled temperature with no adjustment. Rooms are too warm for sleeping and need to open the balcony doors. So you can hear every street noise.

Breakfast is a basic buffet and covers most diets. Clear your own table/dishes.

Reception pleasant and friendly. Good location to explore the area.
Very nice view of sun rise.

Good location for exploring the eastern end of the island. Mornings start with sunrises over the nearby crater. Rooms are adequate but the swimming pool is often dirty and there is a daily per person charge for using it! The pool showers are out of action and appear to have been for quite some time. Underground parking is limited and on a first come first served basis. Didn't use the restaurant so cannot comment.

Was very new building so was clean enough.  The 10,000 extra charge to use the pool is obsene. The extra charge for the breakfast buffet is not worth its price in my opinion. Room came with only very basic amenities, not even including lotion. Instead of having forgotten amenities such as razors and toothbrushes available at the front desk they must be purchased at the convinience store. Overall the experience at the hotel felt like someone was trying to pull all the money out of my pockets they possible could. Would not recommend.

reviews.text:
I stayed here for about 3 months last year and had fond memories of that time, so I came back.
The owner and manager changed and the price went up a bit, but I always want to come here when I'm in Moseulpo.
Being able to use the cooking utensils and washing machine provided in the room is a very nice advantage!

It was a hotel with a nice view.
The owner gave me a corner room, so I really enjoyed my stay with a panoramic view of Moseulpo Port.
Thanks to you, we extended it for another day.
I will definitely stay here again the next time I visit Moseulpo.
thank you

It says that washing machines and cooking facilities can be used, but they cannot be used.
When I asked directly, they said it was not possible for this price.
They say you have to charge at least 100,000 won for a pension type lol.
Then I don't know why you wrote on the homepage that you can use it.
There is a lot of dust. There is no discount for consecutive stays. They do not clean it properly.
They don't talk at all, so they just take out the trash.
Not much for 60,000 per night
Go to Moseulpo Hotel for 40,000-45,000 won per night.

For a hotel, it seems strange that there is a washing machine or induction cooker.
The fact that there is something like a court ruling posted on the room door makes me feel like I failed while trying to sell it.
The rooms are clean and there are restaurants and convenience stores nearby, so it would be okay to stay for a day.

I travel the world on a bicycle
I am a traveler.
I went to Moseulpo Dream Hotel in Jeju Island.
The owner is friendly and the hotel is large.
It's clean and very nice. I highly recommend it.

reviews.text: It is a must-stay guesthouse in Seongsan! Sunmi and her husband were so nice, they were so helpful and passionate. The room was very clean and comfortable. Besides that, they have a terrace to rest, and you could savor the beauty of the ocean from there! And for the male dorm, the ocean view is just outside from your window, every morning I woke up, my mood got uplifted due to the amazing view.

One of the best ghesthouse i had over a 15 days trip around jeju ! Owner is great and welcoming, the place is convenient and affordable. And the view !
We woke up around 4:50 am and climbed the little volcano (it took 20 min) to enjoy the sunrise. It was fantastic !

The owner is very friendly and genuinely cares for you as a person. Without a doubt I would have stayed one more day in this guesthouse if it weren’t for my travel plans. Cost per night is 19000 won (2019.8 standard)

This hostel was one of the nicest and friendliest I've ever been to. The host is absolutely lovely, and she is happy to chat to you about anything from your plans in Jeju, to life in general. She made me feel incredibly welcomed and I really enjoyed my stay. The rooms are clean, the hostel is conveniently located and had everything you need. It's close to the bus stop, only 5 minutes from Sunrise peak and close enough to the harbour to walk if you're going to udo island. Our host was so lovely, she even drove us to the harbour because she thought we would be tired after climbing seongsan ilchulbong to watch the sunrise.
고맙습니다!!

Standard bunk beds but clean enough with warmer in the room. Location were near to seongsan entrance. You can see seongsan ilchulbong during breakfast in the rooftop. The host was a nice lady who made us breakfast (egg with salad and sweet potatoes)

reviews.text:
The staff and the owner are super nice, friendly and extremely helpful. They will make you feel like home:)

The room was nice, really clean. Everything like it was expected. And big enough for 2 adults and 2 kids.

We booked it because of its location, we needed to be not far from the Dongliri Port. It is still far to walk with kids, but with taxi it was 3 mins (25 minutes to walk). Downstairs there is a 7-eleven shop and also a small cafe (a twosome place). Many restaurants and cafes are around.

We stayed here for 2 nights. The room is huge and clean. There is cleaning service every day, so we get our fresh towels and toiletries every day.  One of the bulbs wasn't working, but we could get a replacement bulb at the counter easily.

Everything we expected of a hotel is there. The nice extra is the seawater jacuzzi in the room. This is an extra bonus.  The seawater bath is so relaxing.

Ours on the 7th floor, not the highest 9th floor, but we have a good lookatf the surrounding area. We parked our car easily in the free car park lots available. There is also a charging point for electriccarsr here.

This location allows us to travel northwards and eastwards along the western and southern coastlines. We visited the windmill stretch while we stayed at this hotel.

There is a 7-11 convenient store and a Twosome Cafe downstairs. So we could get our coffee fix and tidbits all the time.

Nearby, there are plenty of cafe and eateries. We enjoyed toasts and coffee in a friendly cafe about 150m away.  I was looking for some western food but i was not able to locate any nearby.

Highly recommended. Quite, well equipped, and best value for money.
Rooms are spacious and clean. Paper cups for coffee, that is a no no for us. No spoons. No glasses
Clean, good price, helpful staff. Plenty of western food options within walking distance, great cafe downstairs with discount for guests. Staff speaks English.
Beautiful views, big room (with tub), and fantastic coffee downstairs. You’ll need a car to get to the tourist attractions from here.

reviews.text:
It was very good value for money and the interior was clean and nice. It was so exciting and nice to have a swimming pool.
The counter was nice and friendly too.
I will have to use it next time~^-^
It was clean and nice. The TV is big, there's a middle door, and the bathroom is very clean and nice, but there's a big mirror in front of the toilet, which really bothers me. Causes constipation

This place is really clean and friendly.
I don't know what to say, but it seems cleaner than my house.. haha
It was clean so it was great to take the baby around.
Clean, friendly, nice view
Nice atmosphere and comfortable

Stayed in one of these lovely chalet apartments for 2 night with 4 people in total. Apartments are a great size and standard.

The staff were also were helpful and arranged food deliveries and transport/reservation at a local BBQ restaurant.
Affordable, beautiful quiet pension. Quaint cottages great for couples/small families.
Very beautiful place. Clean and good accommodation.
The sea view is excellent and the delivery is possible.
Everything was provided and location was good for everything

reviews.text:
The location of the resort in terms of view is excellent. The sea and the light house, the wide road, it is all stunning. The rooms are big and spacious. The view from the room is also great. The staff is very friendly and helpful. They help you with booking of taxi, ordering food and also guide you with places to visit.
The only thing is they don't have a kitten of their own. And there are no vegetarian restaurants nearby, so it might be difficult to find vegetarian food nearby.
Overall an excellent place to relax and enjoy the beautiful view.

The room is great, service by the front desk is good. Atmosphere is nice as well. The service staff helped to carry the luggage to the room.
However, even though I have checked into the hotel, there was a miscommunication between Agoda and the hotel. Hotel informed Agoda that it's a no-show even though I have stayed for 3 nights. The Agoda agent could have asked for the paper work signed during check in. Lots of admin to settle due to the inefficiency of the Agoda platform to check the check in status of the customer. Perhaps to book from other platforms in future.

Stayed 3 nights. It is located at the southern side of Jeju island and was a short few km drive to the beautiful songaksan trail (do visit and do the complete return trail of around 2.5km! less than 2hrs with quite alot of steps but awesome cape views).

sumptious breakfast was served to room at around 8am. same menu everyday but so good. adequate parking at back of resort. i stayed at ground floor rooms with patio, perfect place for breakfast:)

all super friendly staff, especially the cute young lady on morning shift who gave us complimentary photoshoots before checkout:) They also provide a whatsapp contact for english support during the stay.

location wise, facing sea which was across the road! coastline was very suitable for walks/jogs. few eateries along the coast but a car would be better to bring you to livelier locations. nearest supermarket was about 10 to 15min drive away. there was a coin laundry place 5 to 10min walk away.

the only downside is the temperamental heater which gave me quite alot of cold baths. Also power sockets were limited at inconvenient locations but staff provided me with an extension which solved the issue. Notwithstanding i would love to visit sun and moon again:)
Nice hotel facing the sea with easy access to the sea front. Local eateries nearby to try. Hotel staff are pleasant & polite. Bf served to the room.

Good place if you are happy with the west side of the island. It's about 1hr drive to Seogwipo and 2hrs to Seongsan.
The serve a free hearty breakfast of sandwiches and drinks.

reviews.text: Great location, right in the middle of a nice tourist area, close to the beach, great restaurants within 1km. Nice lobby, just the rooms are quite ordinary. No problems, just not super nice. Breakfast was decent, enough to fill you up both nothing special. It got better when they brought out fresh scrambled eggs. The seaweed soup was seafood based and quite delicious. All in all, not a bad stay at all!
It was a nice stay and the staff was friendly. There is option of breakfast with extra payment which was pretty good. You can use the pool of the sister hotel beside it, although I didn’t try it.
If you want to sleep and breakfast only in a hotel at around Southern area of Jeju island, this Bloom Hotel is the best considering price. Very satisfactory.
Hotel was located in quite a quiet area. Rooms are clean but old. Cheap and good and I extended for a extra night

The bathrooms could do with some renovation.  The double grazed windows need a good clean.  The breakfast was minimal for europeans  not much choice. Some guests who had children let their kids bang on their doors in the corridors at 11 pm.  I guess this hotel is a hit for korean people but not european. It was all self service in the breakfast area including removing your own plates and cutlery. Apart from a shop in the building there was no other dining facilities except for a microwave.

reviews.text: Nice hotel, but the parking lot sucks.

I visited with my family and it was spacious and clean.
The staff is friendly and the location is good.
The parking lot is a bit narrow, but it wasn't a big problem.
It's a bit disappointing that there is only one bathroom in the 4-person room.
It's nice that there's a coffee machine and you can conveniently bring bottled water!

It was so nice and clean. I will use it again next time. What is disappointing is that there is no electric vehicle charging facility in the parking lot.
It was really nice because there were many Jeju Island black pork restaurants nearby.

It's not that luxurious, but you can stay there without worrying about the price at an affordable price.
It’s also convenient to use public transportation.

Friendly, affordable and clean
Room condition is excellent!
Plus, free breakfast service!!
The view is almost like that of a Southeast Asian hotel.
However, since it is at the entrance of Jungmun Tourist Complex, you have to walk about 1 kilometer to find places to play and enjoy.

Slightly misrepresented in advertising. It's more of a backpackers hostel bare minimum. Very nice place though for the price
Nice resort!
Relax time.

It was nice that the owner was kind and patient.
However, there was no room key and the cleaning condition was very poor.
The bathroom condition wasn't any better.
It's been a while since I used the shampoo, conditioner or shower gel, so it doesn't come out.

I think only the kind boss will be remembered.

reviews.text:
This was a very affordable stay.. coming from Seoul, we loved the spacious Ness. As we rented a car, the l9cation was actually very nice n peaceful by the harbour. Very short walk to the waterfall.

There is no breakfast though but overall a nice, friendly atmosphere.

The blue light from the aircon n bathroom is disturbing at night. We plastered a thick tissue over 😅
This is a budget friendly place. Don't expect fancy buildings and nice rooms. They do not offer breakfast but there is a Starbucks about 20mins away where you can park for free.

Great location near the Cheonjiyeon waterfall and walkable to lots of food options. Clean, spacious (2 king beds is probably too much even!), affordable, nice staff, even a decent view from the room. Double shower room is a little funny - one of the showers results in water leaking out so that's an oversight, and only mini towels to dry off with, but otherwise good showers. Soundproofing is poor, like many hotels in Korea. Breakfast was very sad, while we were there it was only 7:30-8:30 and consisted only of toast, cereal, milk, and juice, but it was free so we just ignored it.
Good hotel near harbour. Balcony rooms have pleasant outlook over inner harbour. In walking distance of waterfall. Restaurants and bars close by.
I liked it. Great location. Quiet place.

reviews.text: Very affordable lodging in Jeju. Rooms are small, but they have bathrooms, table, and dressing closet. If you are looking for a less expensive hotel, this is it. However, front desk clerks are young, and they do not wish to be bothered. The room was so hot ypu have yo turn the AC. They suggest you put your used toilet papers in the basket instead of flushing it, which I did not. Overall, I will use this place for affordable prices but not for services nor amenities.
The room is small. In the cheap room, the view outside the window is a building wall. It's okay for the price.

If you run a business like this and take money out of thin air, you have a rotten conscience.
It smells like mold and the inside of the air conditioner is rotten, so I can't stop coughing because of the smell, and I feel like I'm going to get pneumonia. This place is absolutely unusable.

This is a hotel with excellent value for money.
I stayed in the event room for 3 nights, and it was a bit difficult because it had a view of the Shinshin Hotel across the street, but I was a single man so it was a big deal.
It wasn't uncomfortable. The cleanliness of the room was also good.
I was also satisfied with the bathroom. I really liked that it had a bidet.
Parking is inconvenient. There is parking at the tower, and if you don't want to waste time at the tower, there is a private parking lot about 100 meters away, but it is an empty parking lot.
It is inconvenient to drag a suitcase. The staff was friendly and the two elevators were fast, so it was an excellent cost-effective hotel with no inconveniences other than the parking lot. There is also a 7-Eleven convenience store at Shinshin Hotel across the street.

There aren't many spacious rooms at the Shin Seogwi Hotel, but there's plenty of room even with a king bed and a double bed and a table. The current room is different from the one in the site photo because the furniture has been rearranged. There is no stand or desk.
The front manager is friendly.
Room condition is good and clean.
It is an all-in-one toilet. The water pressure in the toilet is too weak.

Tamara jeju.adr_address: 10-8 Gimjeongmunhwa-ro 41beon-gil, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63566, South Korea
