reviews.text: one of the best affordable hotel in jeju. the parking is quite difficult especially night time

A great value hotel in Seogwipo. 3 people, 40,000 won per night, 7/1 month.
The bed mattress is soft, the sink, toilet, and bathroom are separate, and the toilet has a bidet.
The outlet is only on the wall opposite the bed, which is a bit inconvenient.
There is only parking on the basement level, so I parked in the passage. It's not a crackdown area nearby, but it looks like parking on the street.
Microwave in the hallway lounge.
Self check-in & out. However, all rooms are set up for two people, so three people must get towels from the front desk. There is no such thing as room service.
I will most likely stay here when I come to Seogwipo.

They say they know reviews well unless it's a review event or something.
Some reviews say the view is bad, the service is bad, and they don't lend you a charger.
The dog's mind is seen as a few.

The breakfast is decent for the price and the overall condition of the room is clean.
The bedding and interior are also clean.

To those of you who left 1 star here, don't be rude.
Please think about the price range before taking action.

It costs 300,000 won per night, so why not go and sleep there?
Why on earth do you want so much for this price and this location lol?

Very satisfied for the price
Really great value for money!
The staff are also friendly

However, it is not cleaned thoroughly.

Dust and cookie crumbs ㅠㅠ

I booked through Agoda and it was the worst hotel with a perfect wall view and no phone charger available for rent. .
The service cannot be called a hotel.
There are no tables, no chairs, just nothing.
There is a smell in the room. It smells like petroleum and it hurts my eyes. The TV is too small.
I won't come back again... I stayed for 2 nights, but I'm seriously considering leaving for 1 night.

Areumdaun Resort.adr_address: South Korea, 63638, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, Seongsan-eup, Siheung-ri, 5 주특별자치도
Areumdaun Resort.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, Seongsan-eup, Siheung-ri, 5 주특별자치도
Areumdaun Resort.name: Areumdaun Resort

reviews.text: Very spacious room and close to a beach. There are 2 convenient stores within walking distance. Miss Regina Lee from the front desk has been very helpful! She helped us to call the car rental company and did the translation from Korean to English. We thank her for her help!

No resort at all. Small hotel.
It did not even appear in the navigator of my rented car.
They only speak korean.
They do not clean the room nor make the beds if your stay is shorter than 4 nights.

Good quality for the price. The location was nice as there are places to visit on the Eastern coast of Jeju Island. However, going there would be very complicated without a car. The bus system is complex. I personally often had to take a taxi to move around. The hotel staff was nice but did not speak proper English. Other than that, the room was very spacious and comfortable to move around. My room had a fully functional kitchen.

Clean and comfortable. Our room has a small kitchen for some light cooking but not allowed to grill. We were told no sea foods allowed. We have a sea view room and the view was nice and we can see Udo island at the balcony. Location is rather remote, but a convenient store is 1 minutes walking distance.

Nice price and neat / clean room. Only one problem is barbecue area and its kitchen. You cannot cook pork or beef at the indoor kitchen as it doesn't have a ventilator in the room. You should do cook outdoor but you will pay additional charge about 20k won and you will enounter lots of wild bugs amd flies lol And no pool there though a pool of another hotel is just right next to the hotel. You will feel very jealous of people staying the hotel next to this hotel. This hotel should get some renovated in my opinion. But, if you just stay in very cheap price, I recommend... view from the rooms is cool 😎

Kensington Resort Jeju Seogwipo.adr_address: 684 Ieodo-ro, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63564, South Korea
Kensington Resort Jeju Seogwipo.formatted_address: 684 Ieodo-ro, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Kensington Resort Jeju Seogwipo.name: Kensington Resort Jeju Seogwipo

reviews.text: I'm from Ireland and was there as part of a shore excursion from a cruise around Japan and Jeju Island, I was on. The food was magnificent. The quality, taste, variety was wow. This was the highlight of our day at Jeju. After visiting magnificent waterfalls and  jaw dropping cliffs. The Botanical gardens with Jungle/Desest/Korean/Japanese areas. After all the steps and stairs we had taken during the day this was a truly Korean welcome and feed!

The Kensington Resort Jeju Seogwipo offers numerous benefits, making it an attractive destination for visitors.

1. Scenic Location: Located in Seogwipo, the resort provides stunning views of Jeju Island's natural beauty, including ocean vistas, lush landscapes, and nearby attractions like waterfalls and volcanic formations.

2. Luxurious Accommodations: The resort features a variety of well-appointed rooms and suites, designed to provide comfort and luxury. Guests can enjoy modern amenities and tasteful decor that enhance the overall experience.

3. Comprehensive Facilities: Kensington Resort offers a range of facilities such as swimming pools, fitness centers, spas, and recreational activities. These amenities cater to both relaxation and active pursuits, ensuring a well-rounded stay.

4. Culinary Delights:
The resort boasts multiple dining options, including restaurants that serve local Jeju delicacies as well as international cuisine. Guests can enjoy diverse culinary experiences without leaving the premises.

5. **Family-Friendly Environment:
- With dedicated kids’ clubs, playgrounds, and family-oriented activities, the resort is an ideal choice for families traveling with children. These amenities ensure that guests of all ages have an enjoyable stay.

6. **Proximity to Attractions**:
The resort’s location provides easy access to many of Jeju’s famous attractions, such as the Seongsan Ilchulbong Peak, Hallasan National Park, and various beaches. This makes it convenient for guests to explore the island.

7. **Event and Conference Facilities**:
- Equipped with modern meeting rooms and event spaces, Kensington Resort is suitable for business conferences, weddings, and other gatherings. Professional event planning services are also available to assist with organizing successful events.

8. **Cultural Experiences**:
The resort often arranges cultural activities and events that allow guests to experience local traditions and crafts, adding an educational and enriching aspect to their stay.

9. **Exceptional Service**:
The staff at Kensington Resort are known for their hospitality and attention to detail, ensuring that guests receive excellent service throughout their stay.

10. **Relaxing Atmosphere:
Surrounded by nature, the resort offers a tranquil and serene environment, perfect for those looking to unwind and escape the hustle and bustle of daily life.
It was a good stay. Rooms are a bit old and faculty left to age.

Very disappointing. We got a family room. Everything feels old and outdated. No microwave in the kitchen. One of the room has absolutely nothing except a closet. No bed, no AC and no bathroom. The bathroom is also very small. You also have to pay for pool usage in a resort! (KRW 18000) The only positive is lobby was clean, has a fancy buffet and view is pretty nice. My previous resort had 2 bathrooms and 2 rooms with a bed and AC in each room. The pool was bit small but obviously free.

My family and I absolutely loved staying at Kensington resort.  We had a beautiful view from our room and were located right by the beach, looking out onto the water.  It was very cool to see the navy boat at sea and so close.  Along with the stunning view, the staff were so  sophisticated and friendly.  They went above and beyond to help me and assisted me in so many ways that even had nothing to do with them and/or the hotel.   I really can’t thank the staff for providing us such a wonderful stay.  I felt so welcomed, comfortable and safe.  Even the Manager was making rounds and providing any assistance we needed to ensure we are having a great stay.  Also, not to mention the kids arcade and koi fish pond that my kids absolutely loved.  When we come back to Jeju, we most definitely will be returning to Kensington Resort!

Matheson and H S Kim

Palm Valley Resort.adr_address: 193 Jungsanganseo-ro, Gangjeong-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63558, South Korea
Palm Valley Resort.formatted_address: 193 Jungsanganseo-ro, Gangjeong-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea

reviews.text:
- The rooms are simply unclean and disgusting - There are thick build ups of dust throughout the accommodation, mould in the bathrooms and a fowl oder in each room throughout the establishment.

- The pool will work for a few 'instagram' pictures, however the grounds surrounding the accommodation are horrible unkept and attract small animals throughout the day and night as it is simply not clean

- The Pool is small, cold water (warm water costs approx $100)

- The accommodation is infested with bugs, roaches and spiders. My partner suffered a bite on the foot whilst in the room (without any open windows/doors) causing us to need to leave the accommodation to seek medical care. No refund nor credit was provided by the hotel as we didn't visit the management office prior. It needs to be mentioned that the management office was left unattended for 3 hours prior to us needed to seek medical care due to the pain.

This is not a safe place to bring children, with no staff available when needed given a medical situation (including an unattended communal pool) this 'resort' poses a serious health and safety risk

What a peaceful place. Of course, I did visit in winter and not tourist season. Hahaha

Great staff.  Comfortable room.  Beautiful walking paths around the grounds!!
I will be back when it is warmer to enjoy a room with a pool and the main pool.

The resort was certainly nice and good many years ago, but now it is getting old and no longer worth its price.

The interior is partly broken (e.g. the mosquito protection in front of the windows had holes and couldn't be opened/closed properly; the blinds sometimes didn't go down/up; the whirlpool in the room leaked and couldn't be used; the air conditioning in the bathroom didn't work ) or too old (e.g. there are mold spots everywhere on the wooden ceiling in the bathroom; the TV in the bathroom was very dirty). At the same time, the entire area is filled with music from early in the morning until late in the evening (i.e. loudspeakers are set up everywhere in the area), which is annoying at times.

The rooms are very spacious. The large shared pool is quite nice - but the small pools in the "Camelville Pool Villa Suite" rooms are not worth the money: far too small and too cold.

The impression in the pictures is quite nice at first glance, but upon closer inspection there are too many defects. A pity. We wouldn't book it again.

I went there a little skeptical.
It seemed a bit old since it was built.
Thank you for taking good care of the building, keeping it clean and kind so that I didn't feel like that at all.

very kind
There are a lot of mosquitoes in the mountains

Kensington Resort Jeju Jungmun.adr_address: 29-29 Jungmungwangwang-ro 72beon-gil, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 697-130, South Korea

reviews.text: Clean room with a small kitchen. Great location with a nice view. Not elderly-friendly (many steps). Small selection for breakfast buffet. 사과빵 was good (must pre-order a day ahead).

Good location if you want to go to the beach, but a bit far away from other touristic attractions in the island. Friendly staff and breakfast changes from day to day so you get to try a variety of local food (there is also typical western style breakfast). Big apartment style rooms with nice view, however the bathroom could use some renovations. Make sure you state clearly if you would like a room with a Western bed or futon beds.

recommended if you have kids.
The space is big, add mattress with free.
There is a kitchen, so you can cook.
7-11 is nearby, you can buy supper easily. There is a station to wait for town bus, about 15-20 minutes one time.

It's a pity the younger people at front desk did not do their jobs proactively. I suggest that they could upgrade their services by having translations of their (limited) information ready for inquiries.
Good location and spacious room but it was August and there was no water in the swimming pool.

Jungmun Family Resort.adr_address: 83 Soboridang-ro 164beon-gil, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63534, South Korea
Jungmun Family Resort.name: Jungmun Family Resort

reviews.text:
Comfortable beds and the best location.
The room is big and the two queen size beds are spacious. The lady from the Front desk is from Germany, she speaks English well.
It is middle of Jung Moon area, so i can visit anywhere within 30mins. Cool.
The hotel is a little old but they will let you barbecue and it has a great meeting hall.
Good o e

Since there are no entertainment areas nearby, it is quiet and you can rest comfortably. (It could be both an advantage and a disadvantage). The room bedding and facilities are clean. It has its own store, but it's only open until 10 p.m., which is okay because there's a 24-hour convenience store nearby. And the boiled pork at Neungi Baeksuk Restaurant in the resort is delicious and plentiful.

It's clean and has air conditioning in every room... I think I come here every year. The first place that comes to mind when I come to Jeju Island. The surrounding facilities and tourist attractions are good, and I like clean accommodations best ;)

Sanbangsan Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63520, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도 Daejeong-eup, Iljuseo-ro, 2093 산방산호텔
Sanbangsan Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도 Daejeong-eup, Iljuseo-ro, 2093 산방산호텔
Sanbangsan Hotel.name: Sanbangsan Hotel

reviews.text:
If you want a view of Sanbangsan Mountain, you should mention it when making a reservation.
Some of the private rooms are not visible at all, but the bat-shaped mountain is clearly visible from the front.
If you don’t particularly want Sanbangsan Mountain, it doesn’t matter.
Rooms are clean, staff are friendly, and there is a convenience store in the lobby.
Paid breakfast in the basement, Pocha on the rooftop, good places to go nearby.

The owner of the rooftop pocha is very friendly and the simple hops taste good.

Be sure to visit Sanbangsan Carbonated Hot Springs right near the hotel.
go twice

The rooms are clean and the breakfast is very delicious.
The staff are also friendly
The walking path behind the hotel is also good to explore in the morning.
High cost-effectiveness
It is better to make a reservation directly on the hotel website rather than through an app.
I recommend it
There is also a dog playground.
Comfortable stay and good breakfast. Very, very good value for money. Definitely coming back again.

I stayed for 5 nights and 6 days with my 11 month old baby.

Although you can swim right next to the beach or have an ocean view that will make your heart beat just by looking at it, waking up every morning looking at Sanbangsan Mountain was healing.
When I returned to the hotel after a day's trip, it felt like a comfortable home, leaning on the shoulder of Sanbangsan Mountain with the setting sun in the background and welcoming me as if to welcome me to rest in peace.

I was so thankful that the staff was considerate in many ways, perhaps because of the baby.

I think I've used a lot of accommodations, including hotels, motels, resorts, and pensions, and the cleanliness was the best.
Even the areas I was usually careful with, such as the corner of the bathroom, the terrace, and the corner next to the bed, were kept clean, so I wasn't anxious about putting the crawling baby down.

Shampoo, conditioner, body wash, toothpaste, and hand wash were provided in the bathroom, but there was no toner, lotion, razor, toothbrush, or soap.   Personally, I was a little disappointed because I am a type of loser who carries disposable items in his travel bag and makes memories whenever he sees them.
Why is it that when the hotel lotion I stayed at before appears in the corner of my bag, I think, 'That was fun back then~' Am I the only one?

There was a kitchen and laundry room on each floor, so we were able to minimize luggage. I wore three sets of summer clothes in rotation, so I really didn't have any luggage. Traveling is more comfortable when you don't have any luggage.

Rooftop pub on the roof? There was a jacuzzi that seemed like it could be used instead of a swimming pool, but I couldn't even think of it because of the heat wave of over 37 degrees.  All I could think about was the air conditioner (my baby gets irritated when it gets a little hot, so most of my travel itinerary was indoors or on driving courses haha)

There was also an abf breakfast buffet.  There was a good selection of Korean food such as rice, soup, side dishes, soup, ham, cheese, bacon, etc., fruit, juice, coffee, milk, etc., but if you think of the standard hotel breakfast you would normally expect, you might be a little disappointed.
Personally, I was very happy because it was my first time in a hotel that used coffee beans for espresso in a fully automatic machine.

It's too long to write.
I came here thinking it would be cost-effective, but unexpectedly found a really nice hotel and was excited.
Accommodation is important when traveling. Isn't it hard to leave home where you came to relax?
It's not fancy, but it's a comfortable hotel that feels like home. I just found out that it was really nice.

I chose it because the reviews said it was generally clean, and it was still good. It's quiet and the staff is friendly... but the room is small so it's a bit frustrating. The view of Sanbangsan Mountain in the distance is good, but it feels desolate because there are greenhouses and fields right in front. Sanbangsan Mountain’s carbonated hot springs are nearby, so it’s a good idea to use them.

Ocean Palace Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63595, Jeju-do, do, KR 서귀포시 14, Jungang-ro

editorial_summary.overview: Streamlined studios with kitchenettes, in a cosmopolitan hotel offering a restaurant & sea views.

Ocean Palace Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, do, KR 서귀포시 14, Jungang-ro
Ocean Palace Hotel.name: Ocean Palace Hotel

reviews.text:
(Solo Traveler/ Family suite 7th floor) I truly do not understand how this is a 4-star hotel. Let me list the "Good" first:
1. Within walking distance (.5 miles+) of several tourist attractions and Starbucks.
2. Large room with an excessive amount of closet space.
3. Extremely nice and helpful staff.
4. Washing machine, refrigerator and dining area the Family room.
I choose this location mainly for the breakfast option and it's close proximity to many tourist sites without having a "touristy" feel. I read the reviews and was confident that this was the best place for the price. WRONG! When I first arrived at check on, it was apparent that they were doing some type of construction (this was not mentioned in any of the descriptions or reviews. It looked like the subway station! Dirty and loud. The 7-11 is very small and is the only way that you can warm up any food. I was willing to forgive the lack of decor, the cabbage smell in my room, the mystery stains on the couch and the overall lack of upkeep on this hotel, but I can not forgive the NO BREAKFAST! Not only do they still advertise breakfast on all booking sites, but they don't say anything about the restaurant being closed when you check in AND it's still being advertised on the elevator. I'll just make a list of issues so that you can decide for yourself:
1. No breakfast or on site restaurant as advertised.
2. Construction going on inside and outside of the hotel (at all times of the night)
3. The staff speaks very little English
4. The Family Suite did not have a stove or a microwave
5. The photos online are at least 15 years old.
6. Walls were cracked and chipped and badly repaired.
7. The furniture was stained and dusty.
I can go on, but I think you get the point. Spend a little more and enjoy your stay somewhere else.

This place is listed as a Airbnb. Not a hotel. There is no breakfast provided. The building and rooms are not well maintained. We booked a double bed room for 4 pax. The only thing that impressed me was the door bell and auto door lock. The room is full of defects and the mattresses for the single beds are soft as bean curd. You have to place a 10k won for renting a dryer. The only waste bin in the room is very very small. The air con ducts have not been cleaned for ages. You have to throw the rubbish yourself and the cleaners will not throw them for you. See pictures. The chair is broken and noone knows. Overall, we will not recommend to stay as the service is poor.

Very spacious apartment-hotel, with kitchens area, dining area, bedroom etc. Love the washing machine option, just need to buy washing powder from the convenience store downstairs to wash our clothes.

Bed is comfortable and though the room is not luxurious, it feels like a home and the location is good in town. Walkable to markets etc

Service from front desk is good. No breakfast but there are options around.

We are able to park our car for free here but there's limited parking spaces so if you come back late you might not be able to get a lot.

The pictures on the web site are amazing , unfortunately it is nothing like that. Sometimes they clean your room but not sweep or wipe down anything. We were left with no towels o e day and another day they did even come in and make up the beds. Needs updating and a deep clean and drain would block in the shower.

It's close to the local market and restaurants. The service was friendly. Having a washing machine in our room was very convenient. We found that our clothes were dry within a day. There is a tiny bin in the living area so we recommend you bring a spare medium to large plastic bag to act as a catch all. There are minimal bathroom amenities.

Marine Port Resort.adr_address: 744 Ieodo-ro, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63564, South Korea

reviews.text: Amazing room and amazing sunrise view. We cooked food as we are vegetarian, as no vegterian options around. There is GS25 near this place if needed. Overall VFM place.

The kind and cheerful proprietress who works hard in business~
Give me a small gift and stay on the fifth floor to enjoy the beautiful sea view ~
great!
The room is clean and the bathroom is bright~

It was the best accommodation
friendly boss
agreement
Nearby amenities
nice view
The grandchildren loved it so much

The price is cheap and the rooms are kept very clean. It's not flashy, but if cost-effectiveness and cleanliness are important to you, I highly recommend it. Seogwipo-side, good accessibility, breakfast available for a separate fee. 2 electric vehicle charging stations
It seems like a husband and wife business owner, but the male boss is a manly man...haha. The female boss is kind. Convenient room kitchen utensils, refrigerator, etc.

Pine Hill Hotel.formatted_address: 44 Budu-ro, Seogwi-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Pine Hill Hotel.name: Pine Hill Hotel

reviews.text:
This is my ghost town experience
My stay for 3 nights
1. No one there for check-in and no self check-in ~  devastated
2. No Room service , No one at reception, No lights at lobby ~ scary as hell
3. Hotel are dirty , looks like no one there to maintain the quality
4. If you want to experience ghost town you might probably like this ~ Spooky
5. Plugs and wires in the room are exposed dangerously

Think twice before you book

My wife and I had a great experience at Pine Hill Hotel. We have been traveling all over Asia and this might be the best value and friendliest hotel we have stayed at. Great location and comfortable room. We were given great restaurant recommendation. The front desk even went out of his way to drive us and help us order at a couple great spots.

Great clean room, new towels and water every day. The staff is helpful and friendly. Location could not be better, no loud traffic and you walk easily to all the attractions around: waterfalls, the nice bridge etc. 10/10 stay! Greetings from holland and france!
Devil's place. This place takes your soul. Don't ever think about reservation on this.
The room was small, but clean. The bathroom quite spacious. It's close to the bus stop to Jeju City, only 5 minutes walking. It's walking distance to the quay.

The Grand Sumorum.adr_address: 118 Maksukpo-ro, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63573, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Sleek quarters, some with sea views, in a modern hotel offering a restaurant & an outdoor pool.

The Grand Sumorum.name: The Grand Sumorum

reviews.text:
We've booked this hotel as an alternative, as our originally booked hotel in Jeju was partially closed for maintenance.
Was a bit concerned prior to arrival, but it turned out to be an amazing place to stay, which is way, way better than it presents on the pictures.
It's rather small, boutique hotel, but has facilities more than expected. There is a high quality restaurant downstairs, with lovely views at the pool and sea. Plenty of parking space and pool loungers. Spacious rooms and bathrooms with quality cosmetics, comfortable beds.
Plenty of restaurants in a walking distance, couple of convenience stores as well (including a small one in the hotel itself)
All that in extremely affordable prices compared to it's high quality. Consider to pay extra for the panoramic sea views for an unforgettable stay.

We stayed here for 2 nights as part of the Jeju leg of our honeymoon.

Pros:
- Large resort style hotel. The new Annex building is very fresh and modern (make sure to stay here)
- Buffet breakfast was quality
- Well equipped gym although lacks ventilation
- Rooms are large and ours had a view overlooking the outdoor pool and the ocean + rock

Cons:
- Staff could've been a little better to match the hotel level
- In room air conditioner was loud and only auto heating function was allowed, which meant it kept turning on and off intermittently
- Dragging of furniture from upstairs rooms was constant and irritating

The room rate was off peak and was great value. Although our stay in Jeju was rained out, we really loved this hotel and the relaxing vibes. Highly recommended if you don't mind the location

Was there for two nights. The room was nice and clean. There are three swimming areas. If you actually want to swim without people, I would recommend using the indoor one (if the weather is good). They have different depths of pools for different ages. The food was apparently good, except the bacon because it wasn't crispy enough for my daughter.
Very spacious room, for the main building. In annex the rooms are relatively small. Walkabale from eateries and right on beach

Staff is very helpful with information and very hospitable. Breakfast spread wonderful. Good mix of restaurants nearby. Seaview fantastic both day and night. Looking forward to hanyeo divers show coming up nearby!

Jeju Hotel the M.adr_address: 14 Taepyeong-ro 353beon-gil, Seogwi-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do 63595, South Korea
Jeju Hotel the M.formatted_address: 14 Taepyeong-ro 353beon-gil, Seogwi-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Jeju Hotel the M.name: Jeju Hotel the M

reviews.text:
This is a hotel that was top class. The location, the view and the service were worth the price. I am glad i opted for the sea view room.
Highly recommended!
It was amazing experience! Great location: close to beaches, markets, and landmarks. Very clean room. Very nice people in the hotel and an affordable price! I am very satisfied.

It is located in downtown Seogwipo, so it has the advantage of being able to travel to major tourist attractions in the city. Olle Market, Cheonjiyeon Falls, Lee Jung-seop Street, Jeongbang Falls, etc.
Although the rooms are not very old, they are clean and well-maintained. The sea view of Munseom Island and Seyeongyo Bridge is also good.
The soundproofing is the worst. You can hear conversations very well from the room next door, and you can clearly hear the sound of the bathroom sliding door.
I had a hard time meeting crappy neighbors.
Parking is mechanical within the building, and there is a separate external parking lot a little down from the hotel.

Hotel located right in front of Seogwipo Olle Market.
It's really cheap and clean, so I always stay here when I come to Seogwipo.
Parking is also good.
A room with two double beds costs around 30,000 won.

Staff does not understand English, difficult to communicate, modern room, nice view, toilet has a modern, automatic toilet, the family really likes it. Parking in the basement with automatic storage system with controller.

editorial_summary.overview: Spare, TV-free rooms & haute suites in an inspired hotel with 9 dining options & yoga classes.

Playce Camp Jeju.name: Playce Camp Jeju

reviews.text:
Room was compact 11m Sq.
Ok for my 1 night stay to catch the sunrise tomorrow.

Staff were friendly and helpful.

Limited space for luggage. No TV in Room lol
Spring mattress is basic. Not suitable if you need firm and padded.

Free parking, laundry (coin operated), convenience store below. Gs 25

Takes 8 min to drive to the main attraction
Really fun place to stay. I stayed here while cycling round Jeju, they have bike storage and a place to eat on site which is helpful. Ransome location, but not far to get to sunset island.

As some other people have stated, the rooms are pretty small.

That being said, the staffs were incredibly friendly, my room was very clean and had everything I needed. I paid $7 more for the “Standard Plus” and I was so satisfied that I stayed for one more night.

The coffee shop “Dorrell” was also worth visiting. Their signature drink (nutty something) was delicious and was something that I’ve never tasted before. Definitely recommend!

There is also a convenience store on the first floor, but it’s really small and carries probably half of what you’d expect from other convenience store.

Overall, I’m a happy customer and I’d definitely revisit the hotel!

Clean and modern room! Stayed for just one night but had an extremely good rest.

There's also a laundromat, bar and convenience store on site! And charging for electric cars :-)

Highly recommend and wish I had booked this hotel for my entire time in jeju instead

I will be honest. This hotel room is quiet possibly the smallest hotel room I have ever stayed in. I literally started laughing when I opened the door. HOWEVER, it was impeccably designed and very clean. If you are a solo traveler who wants to be close to Seongsan Ilchulbong, definitely stay here. It was a quick drive to the sunrise peak in the morning. Feeling lazy? You can see the peak from your balcony and could probably catch sunrise there if you are not a morning person.

The hotel honestly reminds me of a college dorm. Small rooms, but lots of activities on "campus." There is a bar, restaurant, convenience store, laundry, and lifestyle shop all located in the courtyard.

Do not stay here if you are trying to fit more than 1 body in this hotel room, unless you are SUPER close with the person you're staying with. The bathroom is separated from the room by just a clear glass wall. You will be able to watch your travel companion in all their bathroom activites, as the only place to really sit is on the bed that is located across from this glass wall. Also, I hope you don't have a lot of luggage. There was space to open my carry on suitcase in the room and that was about it. Could be a good option if traveling with a group, if everyone gets their own room as there is plenty of communal space to hang out.

reviews.text: We didn’t stay here but we got lost and found our way here. We asked the reception and she very kindly arranged for a buggy to bring us back to our parking compound. The exceptional service makes me want to return to experience the full hospitality at this hotel on my next trip.

Excellent location, nice view.
Don't bring down your luggage at check in center, the room is not there.
Room is like north Korea.
Nothing to eat after 9pm.
The location is quite nice and the staff was helpful. However I  expected a better maintained room and amenities.

I have somewhat mixed feelings about this hotel.
Pros:
- amazing location, you can go for sunrise and sunset hikes with stunning views
- kids club, my daughter loved it
- plenty of parking space
- big CU in the hotel lobby
- huge rooms that could accommodate big families
Cons:
- the rooms are pretty outdated
- hotel corridors are so run down, they look scary
Overall this is a great stop over point for 1-2 nights but for the price charged I think the condition of rooms and the hotel common areas should be improved.

Jeju Island's hospitality scene is a kaleidoscope of offerings, and Phoenix Jeju stands out for its sheer scale and architectural intrigue. Nestled beside a cluster of weathered buildings, remnants of the devastating ravage of COVID, the initial drive-pass did inspire a touch of apprehension. However, stepping inside revealed a meticulously maintained haven, albeit one hinting at the hotel's age.

The true star of our stay was the breakfast spread. A symphony of culinary delights, it rivaled, and perhaps even surpassed, the offerings we'd encountered at other Jeju establishments. This bounty was undeniably worthy of a five-star designation.

The vastness of the Phoenix Jeju complex hinted at a glorious past, possibly predating the recent travel slump. While the current atmosphere lacked a certain buzz, one could easily imagine the property teeming with life in its heyday. The surrounding area, too, seemed primed to offer breathtaking views, a fact sadly obscured by the gloomy weather that plagued our visit. A glimpse of sunshine, however, revealed the undeniable potential for scenic splendor.

A single frustration marred our experience: the elusive Mint Restaurant at the Glass House. Nestled beachside and accessible only via buggy or shuttle, this eatery beckoned with the promise of a unique dining experience. Alas, despite the presence of empty tables, our attempts to gain entry were met with a firm "fully booked" response. Reservations, it seemed, were a prerequisite. This, combined with the knowledge of the breathtaking ocean vista the Glass House offered on a sunny winter's day, left us with a pang of disappointment.

Despite this setback, Phoenix Jeju remains an intriguing proposition. Its architectural heritage, coupled with the phenomenal breakfast spread, makes it a contender for those seeking a unique Jeju experience. Just be sure to plan ahead for that coveted spot at the Glass House.

reviews.text:
Very well priced hotel, very friendly service. The receptionist was very welcoming and patient with finding our booking (Booking.com) and offered to help us navigate the local area, checked weather for Hallasan peak, and even kindly offered to take us to the ferry for the nearby island the next morning.

The room was clean and had a nice view of Sunrise Peak and included a good modern bathroom. Everything was perfect for our stay, thank you.
Friendly and very helpful staff, amazing location,  "mountain view" room had a great view of sunrise peak, very clean and nice modern bathroom.

There were some hiccups with the hotel - such as the fact that floor towels are being provided as body towels and the rooms not having a safe. The room toilet can also get a bit cold while showering as there is a vent blowing cold air. However, the owner was always very friendly and accommodating throughout. He can also speak English so this is a suitable place for foreigners to stay. The lounge is also a great place to admire the mountain view and have lunch / dinner.

Good location for hiking before the sunrise. The building is old and a bit run down however very clean and the lady is really nice. Would recommend if you are not bothered with fancy hotels. (The town itself is dead quiet in the evening tho.)

The room is very clean through out 7days of our stay.The owner and staff of the hotel are very nice and helpful.The boss lady speak fluent chinese.The location is very convenient both for food and public transport.Highly recommend.

reviews.text:
Jeju Green Narae Pension offers very homely, warm and spacious room that's well designed with an interior that's classy. Last check in time is 10pm.

The moment you reach, you will be welcomed with many little flowers and little figurines that's colourful and pretty. The car park is spacious.

Lobby is always on with relaxing music. There's coffee powder that you can take at the lobby.

Bed is comfortable and nice to sleep. There are also quite a number of pillows for us to hug. Table is nice.

They provide combs, hair dryer, toothpaste and kettle.

I love their huge mat on the floor in front of the bed which we can use to do yoga on. They also have straw pad which comes in useful.

There's some smell at the sink area but not too bad. Kettle has some coffee stains which are not washed entirely.

Air conditioner controller is not given in the room and does not work when we want to adjust the temperature. However, there's natural wind that's cooling which we get from opening the doors to get ventilation.

Noted that host/person in charge of the pension does not know how to speak English.

Really enjoyed our stay here. The view, bed, breakfast was all good and met our expectations when booking through Airbnb. Great for sunrise and sunset as well. Just note that its rather far from some main tourist attraction so definitely need to travel with a car. The roads are really dark at night as well! Will come back!
we have 21pax staying here for 3nights, very nice environment & comfortable rooms!
Beautiful place. Nice and quite. The couple who took care of the place are nice.
Friendly owner

reviews.text: After a busy day exploring Jeju, we checked into Ocean Square Resort and were excited to see the great view of the ocean and pool. The staff was very helpful and friendly, showing us to our room. The beds were comfy and rooms were clean but we had trouble keeping the room at a comfortable temperature - we woke up hot in the middle of the night. overall, this is a great hotel.

We had a good time staying at this place even though it was raining the whole time during our vacation but we still enjoy the place was quiet and peaceful. Glad the place has convenient store plus they serves breakfast.

Easily the best place we have stayed so far in Jeju. This place is excellent in all senses: location, hospitality, cleanliness, breakfast, just name it. The hosts / management conversing in English was a big plus point in Jeju. Breakfast was awesome, with cereals, bread, toast, porridge, milk, coffee etc. Just that the timing should be longer (it's from 8am-9am). There is a 7-Eleven store attached to the hotel so its extra convenient to get food. Overall, highly recommended to stay here!
Reserved BBQ. But they didnt prepare anything and made us wait for 30 min. Didnt even apologize. The rooms were clean. Location isnt good but very close to the coast.
Price was very reasonable, in a remote relaxing location, and very clean with a built in convience store. Enjoyed here more then a 4 star hotel in downtown jeju!

reviews.text:
It was my first time staying at a guesthouse.
It wasn't uncomfortable and it was great.
The owner and staff were friendly and gave us information on restaurants and good travel destinations, making it a more memorable trip🤍 The room was clean and they seemed to care about cleanliness more than anything, so it felt like home and was comfortable! A place I would stay longer if it weren’t for work! I will use it often from now on. Thank you❤️

I visit this place every time,
A bedroom and blanket that always feels warm
We chat in a quiet atmosphere.

I like nearby tourist attractions such as Seongsan Ilchulbong, Gonggigi, and Seopji.
And there are so many restaurants with good value for money.

I had a good rest today too.

The facilities are very good for the price.
There are dormitories for 2 people, 4 people for men, and 4 people for women.
I was looking for a quiet guesthouse to avoid party guesthouses, and it was nice because it had nice facilities and was quiet.
They also rent bicycles and electric kickboards!
Every evening at 8pm, you can attend tea time (not a party) and have fun chatting, and on even-numbered days, you go to see the sea or the stars at night!

The staff are all friendly and it feels like a guesthouse.
It was nice talking to each other.
Except that the cleaning standards are a bit strict.
It was so good. Comfortable. The boss is also very nice. I had a pleasant and comfortable stay thanks to the good guidance around the area. Your dog is also very pretty. I really like it~~

not bad

Good location, no parking issues. Judging by the overall serving sense, it feels like the lady boss is in charge. The room condition is good for a quiet one-day stay. However, the cleaning condition is somewhat uneven.

I had a good rest during the March 1st holiday with a low lodging fee. It's near Seongsan Ilchulbong. It's convenient and good when traveling to the east of Jeju.
The accommodation fee is cheap, the facilities are clean, and the nearby restaurants also have good food, so I had dinner at Lee Dong's and rested right at the accommodation.
If you're tired, there's a Suhyup public bathhouse right in front.

It should be called a motel rather than a hotel.
The room condition is good, but the soundproofing is not good.
I could hear the footsteps and words of everyone passing in the hallway.
The accommodation price on December 31st was very reasonable.
Same price as weekdays

reviews.text: A family of 9 people of all ages and genders was traveling to Jeju together. We planned a schedule focusing on Jeju Seongsan and Bijarim Forest and decided to stay at an accommodation near the sea. We made a reservation at Kuji, which prepares breakfast. We were impressed by the clean and thoughtful breakfast. They made a simple home-cooked side dish and boiled hangover soup, and it was very delicious. The accommodation is much cleaner than it looks on the search screen, the building is well maintained, and most of all, shampoo, conditioner, sea wash, toothpaste, foam cleansing, and even men's shaving foam are provided in each bathroom. These days, it was inconvenient because there are many cases where only the main bathroom is used and the rest are not. You can feel the sincerity of the owner and his wife everywhere. Uniquely, the dining room was a party room, separate from the bedroom, so we played karaoke, sang, talked, and had fun all night long. For those who are preparing to travel with family or friends, I think it would be great to choose Kuji Holiday. It wasn't in front of the sea, but from the second floor, you could see the sunrise rising on the distant horizon. You will be able to experience the comfort that can only be enjoyed in a private house, which is different from a resort. If you are staying at Coogee, be sure to take advantage of the breakfast service and chef's dinner (reservation required). Your trip will be more leisurely, delicious, and enriching.

The owner and wife are so kind.
The accommodation was clean and very well maintained.
It was quiet and had nice scenery.
The experience in Cheonhyehyang’s field was very enjoyable.
They are generous people.
The trip was enjoyable.

The owner and his wife are very friendly.
Breakfast is also great
The interior of the room was also great!
I highly recommend it. I highly recommend it~!!!

I had a great time taking my mother in her 70s for 4 nights and 5 days.
Conditions above that of a 5-star hotel and friendly owner and wife.
The best breakfast service I had in Jeju
I've had a very happy week.
As seen in other reviews
This is a treasure-like private pension that I came across by chance.

The price was cheap, the owner was friendly, and they provided Korean breakfast, so I had a really happy day for 2 days and 1 night.
Best for family and friend gatherings.
I would like to give it 10 stars.

Abientot.formatted_address: 1611 Ojo-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea

reviews.text:
I found out about it through Instagram and had it on my list for a long time, but I finally got to go there. It was clean and cozy, so the whole family was satisfied. I could feel how much thought was put into constructing the interior and props.

Every restaurant I went to in Seongsan didn't taste good, but I couldn't tell you how grateful I was for the simple but hearty breakfast prepared by Aviantto. Thanks to you, I was able to start my daily journey with confidence.

Please note that the road leading into the accommodation is very dark at night, so it is a great place for couples or a family of four.
Where my parents' friends live. There is Avianto right next to the villa. Difficult to find your way in the evening. However, there are delicious restaurants and tourist attractions 15 minutes away.

The accommodation is generally clean. The breakfast served in the morning is of a high standard. However, the bathroom shower booth is not separate, so it is narrow and uncomfortable. The refrigerator motor makes a lot of noise... The boiler room is not separate and is located on the path leading to the terrace, so the noise from the boiler operation is very loud. So it's okay in the summer, but not good in the winter.

Breakfast is also provided. Since it was recently built, it is clean. Generally satisfied.

The service just seems friendly. It is not unvarnished kindness. When I asked for two more towels, his impression changed. And we had a barbecue here, but the charcoal fire was below expectations.

Although it was a bit remote, it was good accommodation at a reasonable price.

The owner is friendly and kind.
Breakfast is also provided, which is nice.
Villa? Resort? Rent it? Haha
The building was clean and the interior was also neat and nice.
Those who use Instagram seem to like taking pictures..

Air conditioning and heating facilities are good.

Smokers outside... haha
Cleaning is required when using the interior, so those who are lazy should take note!

reviews.text: I loved my stay here - thank you for teaching me the art of tea ceremonies and providing such a nice atmosphere to relax to. The natural surroundings were a joy to wake up to and I cannot wait to visit again! Thank you to all the kind staff for your beautiful work and energy.

Quiet and relaxing stay. The building itself is well maintained and rooms are spacious. The staff was very friendly and helpful, some do speak good English. The location is good I think, not too close and not too far from other places. Easy walks to convenience stores and coffeeshops. Breakfast is provided at restaurant just in front of resort. They have tea, mediation hours free to guests. There's also a giftshop in the resort. Hope to come back some day.

This is the best hotel style resort I have ever stayed at and definitely an amazing place for a relaxing stay in Jeju island. They focus on tea and meditation, so you should keep in mind that peace and quiet is appreciated in this place! If you stay the night, tea ceremony, morning meditation and yoga class are free of charge. Not suitable for parties, but perfect for wellness travel. If you want to forget your life worries, you should definitely stay in this place #추천웰니스관광지 #wellnesskorea #wellnesstourismsupporters #한국관광공사
#취다선
Lovely wellness spot to stay in Jeju. This is definitely a place for tea lovers and yoga and meditation lovers. Right on an Olle trail and on the beach.
Accommodation for an Acroyoga event and  that was the perfect hotel for this with a big hall doing yoga and nice rooms with an amazing view.

hotel environment clean and scenery is attractive. price is reasonable.counter receptionist is hospitality to assist to solve my transportation problem. There's a small restaurant beside the hotel u can find a cheapest Buffet in Jeju.
Disappointed by the room which was not perfectly clean. Very convenient if you want to get up early and see sunrise at Inchulbong.
So so. There is other good hotel or pension
Just beside bus stop , 5 mins walk.

B&Sun pension.formatted_address: 592 Goseong-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
B&Sun pension.name: B&Sun pension

reviews.text: We enjoyed our stay here for 3 days. The location is very strategic and close to many good restaurants. We drove here and there’s plenty of parking. The room itself is well equipped with washing machine, refrigerator, microwave, kettle, and so on. There’s also a shared dryer on the second floor. We can self changed for clean towels everyday at the first floor and borrowed some electrical equipment (such as iron, steamer, hair curler, and so on). I highly recommend staying here.

It was great because it was in front of the beach and the place to use the fireplace was on the rooftop.
We bought and grilled our own food.
It's been a while since I ate deliciously and leisurely.
The room is very clean. The view of the sea was nice, and when I opened the window in the morning, I could hear the beautiful sounds of birds. It seems better than most hotels...

You can see the sunrise very clearly from inside the room.
The room is clean and there is a good parking lot.
The soundproofing is a bit lacking, and the accommodation is located a bit further down a narrow road.

The view is nice, the accommodation is newly built, so it's clean and overall very good value for money!
I didn't eat it, but you can have a barbecue on the rooftop, and they have all the seasonings you can think of.
However, at night, there are limited places to go on foot nearby.

Sea Dragon Guesthouse.formatted_address: 285-1 Seongsan-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea

reviews.text:
We love this place.
It is a family run pension. They have a restaurant downstairs. Recommend the ribs!! The place just has such a good location, and we find it charming. It might not suit people who are expecting luxury 5 star treatment, but we find it perfect.

No lift up. No views. The futon and blanket is very very comfortable. Quite a few restaurants nearby. A bbq restaurant at lvl one but not a cause for concern. Seongsan Ilchulbong is near but would recommend driving cuz it's not thaaaat near.

Amazing location! Close to sunrise peak and the harbour! The owners are so friendly and helpful...they offered us a ride to the harbour and stored our luggage after check out! Big, comfortable rooms. Really recommended!

Very simple yet adequate room, with all the necessary toiletries available. Check in was easy and the host was friendly. Best feature of the guest house was its location. Not only were there many cafes, restaurants and convenience stores, Seongsan Illchubong was literally just behind. Great for those looking to hike up to watch the sunrise.

I could see the sun rise in my room if the weather is good.  The room is basically clean and tidy.  The host could not speak English, but she post all the useful information on the wall, e.g. the restaurants nearby and the bus routes.  However, there is no elevator, so it requires to go upstairs with the luggages.

Thira Hotel.adr_address: South Korea, 63641, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, Seongsan-eup, Goseong-ri, 제주특별자치도
Thira Hotel.formatted_address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, Seongsan-eup, Goseong-ri, 제주특별자치도

reviews.text: Sunrise was beautiful 😍 Hotel seems brand new & super clean.

I think it's the best except for the location.
Still, it's not far from Seongsan Ilchulbong, so you can go back and forth in a few minutes by car, and there's a convenience store a 2-minute drive away.
The room was clean and the price was cheap and good.

The location is good, there are a lot of parking spaces, the room is quite clean (but I found that the sheets are not changed every day haha), the bathroom only has a shower curtain so water may accidentally spray outside, so be careful
The self-service cafe on the top floor has a great environment~
The front desk staff was very nice. They even called and sent text messages to let me know if something was left in the room~
Overall very good, the price is very reasonable, worth recommending

Thira Hotel is located near Sunrise Peak, next to a secluded road. There is a large parking lot in front of the hotel and two charging parking spaces, which is great.
The guy at the counter was friendly. My first impression of staying was that it was comfortable. The double room was medium-sized and had heating and floor heating. I didn't feel cold even without a quilt.
There is a free coffee buffet on the 4th floor on the top floor. You can also overlook Sunrise Peak and enjoy the beautiful scenery while drinking coffee. It is really pleasant.
It's a good hotel for the price. Seongsan Ilchulbong is right in front. It's good. I'll come again when I come to Jeju next time. It's even better because I can drink coffee.

Paradise Hill.adr_address: South Korea, 63640, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, Seongsan-eup, Iljudong-ro 4120beon-gil, 103 제주특별자치도

Paradise Hill.name: Paradise Hill

reviews.text:
Do yourself a favor and DON‘T book here. The owner‘s attitude is a joke - he isn‘t friendly and enters the space you book without asking. Using the (dirty) pool is advertised free, but costs 30k and the owner even dared to get angry at a guest and his wife for using facilities they paid for. There was no apology for anything, which is not acceptable. Haven’t had something like this before.
It was also quite noisy at night.
European style accommodation in jeju

The owner is very kind!!! The rooms are also pretty and nice. Each room and living room have air conditioning and all utensils, so it's great to cook, drink, and hang out in the room!
Perhaps because I was in room 201 and had the floor to myself, I had a good time without worrying about soundproofing.
The bed was very comfortable, so everyone in my group had the best sleep we had during our trip to Jeju Island, so we were able to travel in good condition.
The location is a bit remote and there is no convenience store, so you have to prepare well, thinking that once you go in, you won't be able to come out.

The owner is kind.
The door is shaking so much because of the wind that I can't feel at peace;;  No hot water in the shower booth.
One room only has mood lighting;;;

Recommended if you have about 6 friends coming and just want to have fun and not worry about any of this.
Isn’t it good value for money for 6 people?

First of all, the interior is very pretty. The building is pretty, the interior is pretty, and the swimming pool has a nice feel. The view of Seongsan Ilchulbong from the room is truly the best. Above all, the 5-star reviews were really friendly, so I had a pleasant rest.

reviews.text: The room is clean and spacious and everything you need is there.

The exterior looks like a really abandoned building. It seems like there is no management at all. Still, the rooms are clean and the facilities are good for the price. There are many scenic places nearby for a walk, such as Seopjikoji, Glass House, and Phoenix Island, so if you just want to sleep, this is a cost-effective accommodation.

Seongsan Ilchulbong is visible at a glance. The owners are friendly and the facilities are neatly maintained. The parking lot is a bit disappointing, but considering the price and view, it is a reasonable accommodation. The food nearby is average. Udo Pier is also located nearby. It is located near the end point of Olle Course 1 and the starting point of Course 2, so it is also recommended for Olle hikers of two or more people.

Clean.. better than the exterior of the building
I liked it because it was much cleaner than I expected.
I want to come again next time
It's so neat. The wife was very kind and it was convenient and nice because it was close to Ilchulbong.

reviews.text: Parking space is okay and the accommodation is very clean and well-maintained. The sound of birds that can be heard in the accommodation really heals you. However, it was very disappointing that the insect screen was torn.

Perhaps because it is a newly built pension, it has a clean and modern feel.
The room is also clean and spacious. It had everything I needed so I had a good rest. The kindness of the owner is a bonus.

Accommodation with a youthful feel
It was a quiet and clean accommodation. I loved the friendly hospitality of the owner, who spoke with a savory Gyeongsang-do dialect, and the young owner (son). I like the newly built, clean and simple interior design. Seongsan Ilchulbong is 10 minutes away, so it is easily accessible, and a small barbecue party will become a great memory. I had a nice stay. Thanks~

I had a comfortable stay at Damor Pension for 2 days and 1 night in Jeju. The pension was clean, perhaps because it was built not long ago, and the kitchen facilities and bathroom were perfect, without any fault, but I went on a picnic because the terrace was so spacious and connected directly to the outdoors. I felt like I was having a meal. It was so nice. I want to go to Damor Pension next time.

It's okay if you want to tour Seongsan Ilchulbong. Restaurants and supermarkets are all within 10 minutes. Udo Street also takes you to Seongsan Port in 5 minutes. The facilities are clean, and I like the bedding and towels the best.

Haeilri Pool & Spa Hotel.formatted_address: 269-37 Hando-ro, 성산읍 Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea

reviews.text:
This is such a beautiful sea view resort, but unfortunately the weather wasn’t obliging and we could only see a storm instead of a sunrise (!) That said, the staff were exceedingly kind, spoke great English, and offered us discount coupons to be used at their cafe which is a stone throw away from the resort. They had the largest tv I have ever seen in a resort, and watching Netflix in hd on this gigantic screen is really an experience by itself.

Superb place, and I hope to revisit when the weather is better again!

Best seaview hotel at Jeju east coast!
👍🏻All rooms are with seaview
👍🏻Can see sunrise in your room
👍🏻Hotel is new & clean
👍🏻Vouchers for you to enjoy coffee/breakfast at their cafe
👎🏻Check-in time only until 20:00

Rooms at 1/F are equipped with private swimming pool, but I think the seaview angle from 2/F is better

Great location with nice view but not worth to spend money for the room.. smelly toilet.. hard to find staffs for the help..
There is no staffs for check in after 7pm..
Fun place with great snacks & drinks 😘

This should be the most luxurious resort hotel (or more appropriately called a villa) on this leisurely peninsula. You can see Seongsan Ilchulbong Peak and Udo Island at any time.
The rooms are spacious enough, and all have sea views with balconies and open-air bathtubs. Each room on the first floor also has a private pool.
The overall hygiene and cleanliness are not particularly good, but if you don't judge it by the standards of a five-star hotel in the city, there is no big problem to be picky about. If the guest room needs to be cleaned every morning, remember to light the service light at the door.
I recommend all travelers who live here to get up early to watch the sunrise if the weather is fine. The sunrise here isn’t the most spectacular, but it’s quiet and comfortable.
I really like this peninsula and everything about the small villages on this peninsula. I will definitely come back!

reviews.text: I stayed here for two night in January. It felt like home, very comfortable. The room was clean and smells really good 😍
The owner was so sweet and the rooms were delightfully clean. The location is also perfect for visiting that area of JEJU and all that for a remarkably low price

My wife and I stayed at this beautiful place for one week. The owners were very hospitable and helpful. The room was cozy, well appointed and clean. The hotel is located not far from Sunrise peak. It is only a couple minutes from the bus stop to the hotel. Nearby there is everything you need - cafes, restaurants, souvenir stores.

Thank you very much!

Great location. Few metres from the bus stop and few minutes walk to the seongsang illchubong peak starting point. We went for the sunrise and this was a very convenient place to start.
The host is very helpful and rooms are cosy & clean

Super nice people, who even helped me for ferry reservation.
Super cleans and well equipped rooms. Coffee on free service.
Super good location for going on the sunrise of Seongsan Ichulbong

reviews.text:
This is a quiet guest house in Jongdal-ri.
I went there while looking for an accommodation on Olle Trail, but it is a bit far from the starting point of Olle Trail.

It's nice because it's quiet and secluded.
What's disappointing is that I wish there was coffee beans rather than mixed coffee.
It was a pity that there was no breakfast.
(It would be nice to provide eggs, bread, and cup noodles.
This is my personal opinion haha)

It is a good place to go to Udo Olle Trail.
I will visit again next time I go to Udo.

2023.3.4.
It seems like the owners have put in the know-how they gained from staying at many guesthouses.
I was surprised by the power outlet right next to the bed pillow, I was even surprised by the USB port for charging, and I was surprised by the fact that I could mount my glasses right on the bed.
I was impressed that there was a stand for clothes in the bathroom and washroom as well.
Most of the rooms seemed to be small private rooms, but even the locks and locks were nice.
There are not many restaurants or eateries near Jongdal-ri, but there are some shops right nearby that are open for reasonable hours. There was also a good space nearby where you could reflect on yourself.
Being close to Jimibong is also an advantage.
However, please note that there are only 3 parking spaces and you must pass through a narrow alley to enter.
It's my first time seeing a guesthouse that's so well-maintained... It's amazing. Highly recommended for couples as they can walk through brightly lit streets at night. This condition for this price.

A cozy, quiet guesthouse with delicious coffee. Jongdal-ri Village is very pretty, and Udo Port is also close by, which is nice. Oh, and you can also rent and ride a bicycle. Feel the nature of Jeju~~

Recommended for cyclists, but also for casual visitors. The rooms and bathrooms are clean, and there are surprisingly good restaurants and bars in the neighborhood, so be sure to take a look around the neighborhood!

\uc131\uc0b0\ud50c\ub85c\uc6b0.name: 성산플로우

reviews.text: The hotel is really nice and the price worth it. Each room has ocean view and you can see Seongsan Ilchulbong. The rooms are great equipped and very new and clean. There is no reception but the communication for checkin and checkout worked well. What could be improved are bigger towels and a small wardrobe.

This pension is run by a friendly and impressive young couple.
There is no indoor cooking or barbecue, but the rooms and bathrooms are very clean and disposable items are well-stocked.
When you open the window facing the sea, you are a little concerned because it is a private home, but it is not enough to be a concern.
If you are coming to Seongsan, this pension is recommended.

I felt so happy to be greeted so warmly and kindly! Since I was going with a child, I was late, so I went in around 8 o'clock, but the owner and his wife were so kind and helped me carry my luggage, so I was very sorry!!
Actually, I didn't know it was a no-kids zone because my husband made the reservation..ㅠㅠ
I think they were considerate by not telling me if it would be inconvenient! I found out after reading the rules in the accommodation. That made me even more sorry.. But they welcomed me warmly and there was no inconvenience at all in staying one night with my child~!!  Fortunately, my child didn't take a nap, so I washed up right away and fell asleep. The next day, they recommended an abalone porridge restaurant right in front, so my mother and child had a perfect schedule of packing up their bags and leaving while eating breakfast and taking a walk, so I felt a little lighter because I didn't make a fuss.
And it really fit my standards (a little short) and was really neat! In particular, the mattress and bedding were perfect and I slept very comfortably!! And not to mention the view! The location is really great!! Next time I come to Seongsan, I definitely want to stay!! I am grateful that I was able to spend a night on a very nice trip with my mother and child, and thank you for being so kind~^^ I was not able to go to the Jongdal-ri pasta restaurant you recommended due to time constraints, but I will definitely stop by next time.

The location is so good
The view from the room was also very nice.
The pension owners are also very friendly.
It was also easy to get there by bus.

You can see the ocean view as soon as you enter the room. We really recommend this place! A super warm-hearted hosts and great service...!!

1. This is a clean accommodation.   Both inside and outside of the accommodation were clean and tidy.

2. Parking is available on the first floor of the building and in front of the building. There is a parking space for 6 cars.  Seongsan Ilchulbong is within a 5-minute walk, so there is no need to travel by car.  The Seongsan Ilchulbong parking lot is large and free of charge.

3. There are two convenience stores within 100 meters to the left and right of the accommodation.

4. The tourist attraction near the accommodation is Seongsan Ilchulbong. Jimmy Bong. Sehwa 5-day market. Sehwa Beach. Ojo Port. Gwangchigi Beach. Kim Young-gap Gallery Dumoak, etc.

5. If you sit in front of the window in your room and look out, you can see the beautiful scenery of the Jeju sea, Seongsan Ilchulbong, and Seopjikoji.  It's a great place to just chill out and spend time in Jeju.

6. In memory of the friendly and warm host couple, I think I will choose this place as my accommodation next time I visit Jeju.

reviews.text: Above all, the owner is very kind. The rooms are clean and if you come to relax, Coogee Holiday (Island Santa) is the place to be. I think I will always come here when I come to Jeju. 100% intention to visit again.

I can say that it is the best pension I have ever been to. It's clean, the rooms are nice, bottled water and coffee are provided, and the swimming pool is fully equipped with life jackets, tubes, parasols, etc. A place I want to go again!

I really like it. I like that the surroundings are quiet and spacious.
It's perfect for gazing at the stars at night.
What a beautiful place! It's comfortable for family vacation. A great pension to stay in when traveling with a large family
The owner is very kind. You can stay comfortably

reviews.text:
Everything is wonderful, but the hostess, besides Korean, does not know any other languages.
The audibility is awesome, you can hear all your neighbors, I think you could hear us just fine too.
On the last day of our stay we saw a huge cockroach in the kitchen and we were really scared.
Very small towels.

It's nice to have new wallpaper, but the smell still remains.
It's clean because they installed a system air conditioner.
The bedding and blankets are all clean, but there are no sofas, dining chairs, etc.

There was a mistake and the room I reserved was given to someone else.
I was upgraded to a better room.
The bathroom was so small that it was very difficult to shower. The bathroom door wasn't locked.

It's close to Seongsan Ilchulbong and it's a studio apartment, so it feels like home.
Cooking is possible and there is a microwave coffee pot so I used it well.
New building. Clean and good facilities. If I leave the door open and talk in the room next door, my room rings.

reviews.text:
Personally, I am very satisfied with this accommodation. The owner personally prepares breakfast and even greets us at the beginning. I think it would be suitable for people who want to relax in a quiet place while looking at a great view. I stayed on the 3rd floor, and it was romantic to be able to see the sunrise peak from the bathroom bathtub. The bed and bedding were also very comfortable!

There are no restaurants or entertainment places to walk to nearby, the rooms are very clean and like new, and although it does not provide hotel-like services to customers, I recommend it if you are looking for a quiet and comfortable place to enjoy nature and chat with people.

Feels like a well-maintained old mountain cabin.

*disadvantage
The cleaning condition was excellent, but there was a strong smell from the bathroom drain. The diffuser in the bathroom looked odd.

There was no soundproofing, so the sound of the children next door screaming late at night felt as if they were screaming into my ears.

I made a reservation through Airbnb, and obviously there was a TV in the list of amenities, but when I checked in, they asked, “Did you know there was no TV?” and I was so embarrassed that I couldn’t say anything. Since you said this without even asking, I guess you've received quite a few complaints.

There is no outlet next to the bed, which is a bit inconvenient. I wish they would provide a multi-tap

*merit
The surroundings are quiet and there is an outdoor garden, so it would be nice to sit outside on a nice day.

The bedding is pretty good. It's been a long time since I fell asleep

Parking is convenient

The owner is unfriendly.
So, I think both the breakfast and the room are not that good.
Of course, I liked that the bedding was clean and quiet.

Be sure to adhere to the 11 a.m. check-out time.
I checked in at night, and in the morning, I took my luggage off and tried to take pictures of the accommodation, but the owner came and said, "Please leave." I think we really made a mistake because we were a little late.
We stayed for consecutive nights, but it was very disappointing that you said that.

To be honest, I only paid for one view, but I think I should have taken pictures a little earlier.

Anyway, I hope everyone else is on time and enjoys their trip.

It's clean and the owner is friendly. The bed is great too! You can see Seongsan Ilchulbong from the garden. However, it is a bit far from the busy restaurant district! Still, I had a really good rest~~

You can enjoy the sunrise peak while lying in bed. A very great view~
The owner was very kind, and the night in Demont's bed was perfect. I had a good night's sleep. They also gave me two breakfast menus, so I shared them with my husband.

reviews.text: Rooms were dated, the hotel want to leech money any way they can. Everything is charged for, even to use the swimming pool, never seen this anywhere in the world especially at a hotel with these room rates. Incredible. Location was good but that's where it stops.
Lovely staff, great hotel, bed and bit too soft and if you have small children mind the windows, they open a bit too wide

This is certainly not a 5-star hotel. This hotel can afford many guests. That must be the reason why they can promote themselve as a 5-star. However, Cleaniess, Room condition, Facilities, Staff, Service, and in every other aspects, this is simply not a 5-star hotel at all. It's an okay hotel if you pay less than 50$ per night. I would recommend you to reconsider if the room cost is higher than 55$ per night. I personally will pay more than 40$ to stay here.

Tips: The hotel is located near the Chinese area. The parking lot is narrow and often fully occupied. Use the outdoor parking lot, if the weather is okay. Extra charge applies for the pool, spa, and gym.

For a 5 star hotel
Amenities was charged including toothbrush !
Air con/heater doesn’t function ( they said they switch it off during winter) but it was spring n it was warm during the day-
No ventilation
So they gave us a fan ! - a fan ????
Walls were super thin. You can hear doors shutting and people talking

Overall this was not a 5 star hotel. I HAVE BEEEN to 5 star hotel. N this isn’t one of them.
Location is passable.
Pay no more than 50$ max. Not worth it. Not a 5 star hotel at all. Blood stains, holes, molds… Don’t be fooled by the commercial reviews.

reviews.text: I really like the pool villa. I can take my kids swimming in a private space, take warm water and relax at the spa. There is no need to travel abroad. I liked the swimming pool in the center as there weren't many people there. The room condition was good and the bedding was nice and fluffy. Since I said I had a child, they put two beds together^^

Cancellation requested 3 hours after reservation with 10 days remaining. And I'm not receiving any contact right now on purpose. I receive one message every 4 hours, and they tell me to send proof of a situation where I need to cancel, but they don't cancel. Phone, Naver inquiry, KakaoTalk Ssakda Jamsubam

The spa is good... I was lucky enough to get an ocean view accommodation with a clean, spacious interior and a quiet atmosphere. I don't want to recommend this accommodation where you can spend quality time with your lover. If you go too many, it will be difficult to make a reservation.
Boss, have a good rest without any inconvenience~!😊
It's a bit confusing because there are several buildings together with pensions. The building is not new, but it's clean. It was a shame that I didn't have any slippers to wear at home.

This is a pension with a luxurious atmosphere and a view of Seongsan Ilchulbong.
There is a private jacuzzi, so you can use the heated spa even in winter. If there is a public pool, the last order at the eat kitchen is 8 o'clock.
It is conveniently accessible for traveling east of Jeju.
Host calls are very prompt.

reviews.text: It's a little far from Hyeopjae Beach, but it's a quick drive away. The facilities are clean and it's nice to have a swimming pool.

It has been newly remodeled and all facilities, including the rooms, are very clean.
It's quiet so it's perfect~
You can see Biyangdo Island from the rooftop and it’s great to drink morning coffee~

I like that the accommodation is clean and the parking lot is spacious.
There are also places to charge electric vehicles.
I booked a 3-person room, but I liked it more because it was spacious enough to accommodate 4 people.
You have to travel 3 to 4 minutes by car to get to Hyeopjae Beach.
It is a good value for money accommodation for traveling to Jeju with family. It would be a good idea to specify whether or not you can cook at the accommodation when making a reservation.

reviews.text:
The hotel is terribly dirty!! Don’t be faked by the images online!!

The lobby is super small and filled with greasy smell coming from the fried chicken store next to it and the decoration aside are all wrapped with spider web!!

The bedroom still look ok to me but the mirror facing it has quite a few unknown swipe on it that cannot be clean!! The hygiene in the bathroom is unacceptable that there’s mould around the grouting and a stain in the shower, I don’t dare to shower with bare foot that we have to buy a slipper in the convenience store before we have shower

The view of the hotel is nice facing the beach but the hygiene is a big NO

Most disturbing and despicable gross hotel I’ve ever been too.  Photos are all out of date.  Everything was dirty! Chocolate all over bedsheets,  tiles ripped off bath and all around room. Bugs inside the bath living inside tiles.  Never never cleaned!!! No one works there! It’s a fake hotel and just grossssss!  So depressed I had to walk down the street to find another hotel!

Modern hotel straight in front of the beach. Views can be pretty amazing from the room. Rooms are modern and clean. The beds were a bit hard but nothing too bad. They don't offer any breakfast but there is a coffee bar at the reception. Also plenty of other nice places just around the corner.
I'll give 0 start if I can. Rubbish dirty toilet. Old hairdryer, hair and snack in bed sheet, like they do not clean before we checked in, do not expect that with expensive price.. sad experience

The ocean view rooms are amazing BC the view is the entire wall facing the ocean. The mountain view is great too but we also see restaurants within that view. Beds are hard. Staff are friendly. No airport shuttle service. Location is a bit far from other places but right nearby Hallim Park and the beach.

reviews.text:
It's only after 8 months that I write a Google review about Haru in Hallimsok. We got married 8 months ago in the aftermath of the coronavirus pandemic.

We wondered if we could even go to Jeju Island, let alone travel abroad, and we wanted to find Jeju Island, which we had never experienced before, so we made a reservation at 'Hallimsok Day'.

I have visited Jeju Island more than 10 times so far, but this was my first time staying at an accommodation where I could feel the quiet and leisurely life of Jeju Island.

The healing I had while looking at the rabbits and the conversations I had while drinking coffee with the owner were so fun and great.

The owner's husband is a film camera photographer, so we were able to create memories by decorating the final photo with the film camera he brought with him.

‘A Day in Hallim’, an accommodation where I was able to make so many good memories.
I want to visit again.

The accommodation was cozy, quiet, warm, comfortable, and very nice!   The breakfast was prepared beautifully and deliciously with great care, and it was very helpful by giving recommendations and tips on good places to travel. It was also very healing to see Hanrim, a local puppy, running around in the yard.

The accommodation was really clean, the owner and his wife were very friendly, and the accommodation was so pretty that it was a shame to just sleep there!!
