we like it

It's great if your vacation is just to relax quietly. The sea right next to it is beautiful morning, afternoon, and evening. When I opened the window, I could see the sea (not the entire sea, but over the wall), so it was good to check the weather of the day, and I was satisfied because the neighborhood was very quiet. And the owner seems to be taking good care of the garden! It feels good to return to the accommodation with the flowers and trees well-organized. There is also a swing, and chairs and tables where you can sit and relax are placed to suit your sensibility. It's nice that there's a low stone wall, so the inside is somewhat hidden, and it's easy to get around because there's parking right after you get over the stone wall(?). At night, the lights come on cutely, so you can tell it's our house from afar.
The hot water comes out well and the heating works great. And the bed is hot, but I don't know if this means that when you turn on the heating, the bed automatically becomes hot as well. Anyway, I stayed at a time when it was really windy and a typhoon was coming, but I was tired and had a good rest. I asked for a replacement towel and they gave it to me right away. It looks like they live in the accommodation! If you are someone like me who gets cold a lot and likes quiet, this is the perfect place. Are you disappointed that the wallpaper and tiles are a bit worn out? A few TVs aren't working? Other than that it's good. There is also a convenience store nearby, so it is easy to buy water and snacks when returning to the accommodation. In each room, I had my own little space haha, so I laid out my clothes and put my wet shoes out.
It is equipped with everything such as a small refrigerator, sink, coffee pot, cutlery and cups, so it is convenient to bring food to eat. I drank coffee every morning. There are also shampoo, rinse, soap, toothpaste, and dryers. But there was no body wash! If you wake up early, take a walk along the seaside every morning!

This is a cozy house with a very pretty garden and exterior. There is a port in front of the pension, but if you walk 30 seconds to the back, there is a great sea view of Geungneung. The small room is perfect for a couple. The bedding and towels are soft and fluffy. A car is essential to eat. If you want to play in the water, wear a life jacket along the sea road to Geungneung. I swam there haha. There are ants, so as long as you're careful not to leave food on the floor, the price is good and good! I recommend it.

This is a very cost-effective condo for people who only sleep at night like me. Since it is located on the west side of Jeju, it takes about an hour to get to the airport, so plan your itinerary well.

Really beautiful place to stay in Jeju. You can relax with own jacuzzi at room.
Really recommended
Nice hotel with great spa

I came alone and went to the healing zone.
The bath ball(?) foam that the lady boss gave me is no joke.
Natural soap is good, and the coffee machine and ice maker are free.
The whirlpool was so good that I only took three baths in two days.
The owner is friendly, the room is nice, the view is good, the parking lot is good (electric car charger provided), and if you come in the summer, it would be nice to have a swimming pool...
I'll come back when I find a lover. Have a nice rest, boss^^

Overall I was really satisfied. The exterior was pretty, and the rooms were also clean and simple, which was nice. Handmade soap and bath salts were provided, and the owner's friendly explanation before entering the room was nice. I was satisfied with the spa and had a good rest.

The staff was friendly and there was plenty of parking space.
The spa facilities are clean and bathing products are provided as standard when you go.
There is absolutely no need to buy it because it is given away. Nice clean place.

reviews.text: Hello, first of all thanks a lot for your hospitality, we arrived with my family at the hotel around 9 am, check-in from 3 p.m., we were allowed to enter the room at 9 a.m. without any problem, no extra charge. Hotel clean, friendly service, highly recommended

Kai Hotel situated a few streets back from the main beach road.

Suite Twin - top floor (5th). Views are good looking down the street toward the beach. The balcony never sees the sun and is chilly to sit on. The bathroom is cold and remains wet most of the time. The toilet had a wiring short or some weird massage as tiny electric shocks stung your left bum cheek.

Once again no AC control to cool the room down for sleeping. I guess hoteliers know whats best for us guests and what temperature we should swelter in.

Us humans are not all the same hence the reason for temperature controls on AC units. Heating is via the floor. Cooling not allowed apart from opening windows.

Late evenings can be noisy as drunking hotel guests make their way back yelling and screaming like children throughout the morning .

My first impression of the hotel was that it felt very chinese. It doesn't look that nice from the outside. Once inside the room i wasn't disappointed though. The rooms are reasonably large, fairly modern and clean. They also have kitchen. Location is a 5 minute walk from the beach or coffee shops.
I guess it's a pretty good location for families, especially for the price.
Close to the beach, reasonable price. Rooms are nice and clean. View isnt that great from the lower floors. Staff are helpful. The pool was drained when we went so couldnt use it

the unit we have was like a small apartment with 2 rooms, bath room and a fully functional kitchen. the space is large and we enjoy the balcony a lot. there are 2 convenient shops just about 100 m away which we walked to every night to pick up snacks and drinks. the are many restaurants near the beach and also around this hotel. the location is nice as the famous Hyeopjae just near by. Halim park is also just nearby. not bad a choice if you have many members in your trip and want to explore the west side of Jeju for few days.

reviews.text: This is more for the families,  the rooms are ok,  you sleep on the floor,  the hot water was limited,  breakfast free but poor.

It's clean and the owner is friendly.
The swimming pool is good too

Satisfied with the abundance of towels...
Regarding facility use, the swimming pool cannot be used before check-in, and the swimming pool is not open in the morning....
After checking in, I only use it after 3pm until dinner....
Compared to other pensions, usage time restrictions are greater..... When using the beach, it is only used as accommodation and there is no intention of revisiting...
There are few swimming room facilities, but the slides are not safe... It seems dangerous for children to fall out when using them.

Recommended for parents of children
Hyeopjae Beach is also a good location for walking back and forth.
When the beach water drains
Playing in the pension swimming pool.
Even though they are not big, children can play safely.
The inside of the pension is like a large master bedroom in an ordinary home.
There is a veranda
On the 1st floor, return the wet laundry to Jjalsuni.
I dried on the veranda and packed my bags.
There is no smell and it is good.
I had a good rest.

Where have all these photos gone?
There are no photos of the beach.
It's a pity that I can only take nice pictures of the swimming pool because it's so pretty on the way in after dinner at night.

It was great value for money. We stayed here for one night and at a private guest house for two nights, but the kids said they wanted to come here again and stay for a few days because of the swimming pool.
I rented the largest room, and both the two bedrooms and the living room and bathroom were very clean. The floor was cleaner than any place I've ever been to, the room was spacious, and the owner was very friendly and I enjoyed the breakfast. I want to go again. And I think it's quicker to get to Hyeopjae Beach if you walk towards Donatos. It's about 5 minutes away.
The photos come out really pretty too.

reviews.text:
Advantages
1. Free food (breakfast)
2. The food (breakfast) is so delicious
3. Master, you are so callous
disadvantage
1. I don’t have an older partner.
2. There is no praise
3. It’s a little small (room)
Other than that, everything is okay
A little bit recommended

The beach is right around the corner, so it's nice to see the Biyangdo sunset. At first, I wanted to see it while having dinner at Hyeopjae Beach, but it's also nice in front of the accommodation. The room is clean (remodeled). The exterior is a bit old, but the owner is friendly. When I stayed on the first day, I thought there was no one other than us, but in the morning, I saw quite a few people eating.  Before breakfast, I listened to the birds singing behind the accommodation for about 10 minutes because I loved it so much.

It's quiet. If you go to the facility, you can see from the exterior that it looks old, but the interior and facilities are definitely older. However, the owner's grandmother seems to have kept it clean. It may have been used as a condo in the past, but there is a simple kitchen in the room, but I never used it, so I'll pass on this part. ah! The bathroom had shampoo, soap, toothpaste (shared), and towels, and they informed us that if there weren't enough towels, we could get more from the first floor. Of course, there is a hair dryer, mini refrigerator, and IPTV. It was winter and it was very drafty because it was near the sea, but there was an electric blanket on the bed so it was warm. All rooms have ocean views and are on the 4th floor, but there is no elevator... ㅠ. There is a water purifier in the center of the hallway on each floor except the 4th floor. Breakfast is served from 7 am to 9 am? (Probably yes) Yes. It's rice, soup, small grilled fish, seaweed, kimchi, and a small salad. Still, it was delicious. I ate 2 bowls each~ (You eat your own rice from the rice cooker.) However, the location is ambiguous, so it takes time and a lot of walking to get from the airport by public transportation like me. If possible, go by car. Cost is 22.02. I think you can expect to pay around 50,000 won for two people (off-peak season).
Although it was a slightly older accommodation, it was very nice to have breakfast service. Well served Korean food. It's also great for a walk to Hyeopjae Beach. Access to amenities is also good.

Good transportation in HallimㆍAndeok area, 202 and
Hallym High School. The stop is a short walk away and there are many beach restaurants within walking distance.

Go to the guest room by car

And the structure of the route is convenient.

It's expensive here

There's a strange smell throughout the hotel.
I had a hard time during my stay. I still feel like throwing up.

I think there are other good options....
I've lived in the countryside for a long time, but I never thought the smell of fertilizer would be this bad...
Breakfast is all frozen food and made in China!! The bed and blanket are very, very uncomfortable...

Inexpensive and cost-effective hotel
It's inconvenient without a rental.

reviews.text: Watch out, if you are booking a room for the bunk beds, they charge you per bed, not the room.  I paid $75 but ended up paying $150 instead.  I couldn't even cancel due the the penalty.  With $150, I could've stayed at 5 star hotel.

Expensive mistake!
Sadly, our flight to Jeju was cancelled due to weather and there were no flights available the next day, so we had to abandon our plans of going there. We would have stayed at Shemungnolmung guesthouse 3 days later and at $105/night it was the most expensive place we booked. Even given the extreme circumstances and 3 days notice, they never responded to the two emails my wife sent them requesting a refund.

It is within walking distance to Hyeopjae Beach and there are many restaurants nearby.
The owner is very kind. Breakfast is served a little late.

The double room stay is clean.
Hyeopjae Beach is a 3-minute walk away.
It's quiet and nice.
This is a view of staying on the 4th floor.

It's quiet inside the neighborhood across from Hyeopjae Beach, and there's a forest behind it, so the sound of birds is so cozy and nice. It is a newly built building with clean rooms and good value for money for families. The owner is friendly and there is a toast service for breakfast. The beach is also a 5-minute walk away, making it a great place to visit again.

reviews.text:
It is a clean and neat guesthouse.
It is a charming and stylish place in spring, summer and fall, but in winter it can be cold as there is only one door.
Since it's right outside, there's not enough privacy, and depending on who the guests are, it's quiet...
Breakfast is delicious

On the timeline of Google Maps....
It says ‘Injeju Guesthouse’...
Wrong.
🔹️Address: 137-11 Myeongwolseong-ro, Hallim-eup, Jeju-si

Actually, the place I stayed was ‘Rural B&B’...
An acquaintance from the mainland searched on the internet and decided to stay here...
As it turns out, the old house was renovated into a rural and fishing village bed and breakfast, and the angeori (Jeju word for main house) is used as lodging, and the grandmother is currently living in the outgeori (Jeju word for outhouse).

In the middle of walking through Olle to enter the accommodation, there is a large hackberry tree (it seems to be several hundred years old... it is very large).

The location is close to Hallym Myeongwoljinseong Fortress, Myeongwol Hackberry Road, and Myeongwol Elementary School (cafe), making it a great and peaceful place for a morning walk.

The interior consists of 1 large room, 1 small room, living room & kitchen.
The ceiling height in the living room is high, which is nice because it doesn't feel stuffy.
The warehouse is fully equipped with electronics such as washing machines and dryers, and the bedding set is very nice.
The feel and the cozy feeling of being slightly hugged against the body are good.
I tried to buy it by taking a picture of the product name.
Haven't purchased it yet.
If anyone knows, please leave a comment... haha

The morning of the last day after a comfortable rest for 3 days and 2 nights.
As I was about to check out, construction began using heavy equipment as if new construction was being carried out on the empty land right next to the accommodation.

It's cozy and the owner is kind.
Breakfast is also delicious. It was disappointing that the bathroom door was made of translucent glass and had no lock.

It is a quiet guesthouse with good breakfast.
There is no TV.
There is one large dog (black dog), one dachshund, and although it is not kept in the guesthouse, there is also one tuxedo cat.
For breakfast, toast, omelet rice, salad, and drinks are provided by the outside host.
It's quiet and perfect for me! It was the Jeju-style accommodation I wanted!! The owner and his wife were very kind and very considerate of the little baby!! Even the breakfast was the best!!!

reviews.text:
A resort located in Hanlim area. The famous HyeopJae Beach is 5 minutes away by car.
There is a outdoor pool in the resort. The pool was not small, but they should consider putting some shades near the pool.
Facility is overall clean and nicely maintained. My room was also clean, but some of the furnitures were broken. And also, they should clean the balcony as well.
Just budget resort and good for a simply night itself. However, KRW 19,000 per night even with breakfast is sort of magic price.
Amazing quiet place.
good

I went there during summer vacation and am leaving a late review.

Pros - Low accommodation costs even during the peak summer vacation season.
There is a children's pool. Soundproofing is good. Room is spacious.
You can go to Hyeopjae Beach and Geumneung Beach in about 5 minutes by car.
There is a balcony, so it's great for drying wet clothes after swimming in the sea.

Cons - Much older than the picture. Old tea pakpaknam.
Especially if you are sensitive to the air conditioner noise, it is not recommended.
There is a strong smell of manure from the back of the building.
There are few amenities nearby, so you have to take a car.

Well, that's about it, but overall I give it 5 stars.
First of all, the price and location are great.
I had a great time during my summer vacation.
If swimming is not your goal, I recommend another hotel.

reviews.text:
Nice view :) I stayed in room 402, duplex.
4 people stayed and it was spacious and well-used.

The air conditioning in the shared kitchen isn't working well and it's too hot.
I had to cook in the kitchen and eat in the room. I wish there was some improvement in this area.

The sea view is very nice.
The room structure and facilities are also good.
It would be a shame to have a small table in the room.
Still, it is a recommended pension ^^* Fog lights

I like the floor and the room, which is clean and has a great sea view. Bedding and bathroom towels are clean. It is located slightly inside Geumneung Beach. It was also nice that there was an air conditioner in each room and on the floor.

This is an amazing Geumneung Beach view pension. As soon as I entered the pension, I was so surprised by the view outside the window... I was shocked...!!! You can see the emerald sea and Biyangdo at a glance!! I was once again shocked that a place like this costs 100,000 won..!!! The accommodation itself is a spacious one-room accommodation, so it's not particularly good, but the view is great. Really... How nice would it be to take a walk from the accommodation to Hyeopjae Beach? ㅠㅠ The atmosphere of the neighborhood was quiet, calm, peaceful, and really nice compared to Hyeopjae next door. Oh, one thing that was disappointing was that there seemed to be a lack of guidance on how to check in. Also, the common kitchen was very messy;;; I couldn't even figure out if I could use it or not. So I just didn't use it. There were some disappointing points, but even taking all that into consideration, it is excellent value for money. Be sure to go!

There were few restaurants near the accommodation, but the sea view from the accommodation was nice.

The accommodation is good for multiple people to stay.

The price is like a hotel

The 270-degree ocean view from the restaurant on the fourth floor makes you forget about the price.

The sea view was 120%

reviews.text: I loved staying here because its away from all the hectic city life. The place has an awesome landscaping. It feels like you are in Thailand. Each room has its own unique ambiance. The staff was exceptional and tended to all my needs. They were always trying to do more. I would definitely come back and recommend it for everyone.

From the hotel entrance to the counter, it's really nice.
Everything is good, from the pleasant scent that lingers as soon as you enter the room, the clean room at a glance, the heated Ondol (floor heating system), the nice bathroom with a bathtub, and the easy-to-eat breakfast. But the soundproofing is really bad.
It seems like the house is divided into two, but I can hear everything they are talking about. I thought you were talking to me.
If you're lucky, you won't be envious of a 5-star hotel.

The scent was good and the room condition was perfect... The atmosphere was so nice that you could come in and burn the intense stick. Water and disposable drip coffee are also good. The sound of birdsong from the accommodation was really nice... The hinoki soup was a bit small haha... Other than that, everything was good. Breakfast was also delicious~♡

It looks well decorated with a Thai concept, but it's uncomfortable to stay in.
First of all, there are no windows in the room, so ventilation is difficult. There is a bathtub next to the bed, so it gets very humid when you use the bathtub. And since the entire floor of the room is tile, the entire room echoes like a bathroom, so it has a built-in echo effect, making it great for singing.
The problem was that while we were sleeping, around 12 o'clock, a large centipede that was over 10 centimeters bit my husband and I on our feet in bed. We were startled and in pain, so we woke up and caught it. We were really surprised at how big it was.
I called the owner, but he said he had never been bitten by a centipede and had no emergency medicine such as antihistamine ointment or emergency medicine to deal with centipede bites, and I was shocked that there was no solution.
I felt like I couldn't sleep any longer in this room, so I checked out early in the morning. They gave me a refund, but the owner told me to contact the reservation site to cancel and not contact the pension, so he had no response to accidents like this or any consideration for the safety of guests. This accommodation seemed very disappointing.

I like the pension because it is exotic and cozy. I had a good rest in a quiet and quiet place. They kindly prepared a barbecue, and the spa was really nice :)
I also enjoyed the breakfast.

reviews.text: The enitre place is interesting and cozy. The staff is two old couple. They are super cute and helpful! As we cant speak korean, they tried their best to help us in any way they could!
It is one of best hotel with a beautiful garden with very reasonably price. I would highly recommend it.

This resort is located on the road from Seongeup Folk Village to Pyoseon and has European-style buildings and caravans.
For gatherings of multiple families, you can choose a room with three duplex rooms.
Although the location is remote, the resort garden is very pretty and well maintained.
The owner was friendly and gave good explanations about the garden while taking a walk.
We recommend this accommodation for gatherings or vacations.

There was nothing around, but it was quiet so it was better. And the garden is so pretty! It’s nice to just take pictures and have fun inside the resort. It feels like every detail of the exterior building, interior, and cafe was taken care of, and the rooms are clean. Next time I go to Jeju Island, I want to visit again! Also, the owner is very kind and the dog is a bit tough but cute. One downside was that when I used hot water in the room bathroom, there was a slight ammonia smell, which was disappointing.

The owner welcomed me first.
We were greeted by a puppy named Palo.
Thank you for welcoming me so warmly with a smiling face.
I liked Gibuni even before I came in haha.

When I entered the dorm, my family made a wow noise...
The bedding on the duplex is clean and the bathroom is very stylish and clean.

Landscaping so you can easily take a walk outside
It's so well done.

Next time I come to Jeju, I want to come again!
Highly recommended!

reviews.text:
One of the BEST stay experiences I’ve had.
The design of the building, interior and exterior was outstanding. They explained how this place was designed which was in traditional Jeju house format. Interior was super unique, leveled into 3, bed area, living room and kitchen. This was my first time staying in a Jeju style house and it was very traditional yet very elegant at the same time. The place was super clean and floor heating was so warm it was definitely a place to relax and heal.
When you wake up in the morning, you can directly see the buckwheat fields through the window and there’s only the fields and blue sky.
The breakfast was served with Jeju black pork pie(must try), some salads, juice and yogurt bowl.
This was legit a hidden gem in Jeju and I would love to visit again with my family in the near future.
For me the best hotel in the world.

I had a really good rest with the peace of feeling like I was lying down on the ground. The supplies, amenities, and bedding provided in the room felt like a lot of care was put into it and it was neat and clean. I tend to go to Jeju often, and this is the #1 place in Jeju where you can get a feel of nature. It was so comfortable. The swimming pool at night was really nice, and the stars in the night sky were so pretty that I took a picture, but it's a shame that they weren't all included in the picture. I highly recommend you go to see the natural beauty of Jeju's nature that you can feel here.

The hot water and heating system worked well so I could use it comfortably. It was nice that the swimming pool was warm in the winter! The view is so nice when you open the curtains in the morning... I requested breakfast and had it, and it was very delicious. The restaurant is also nice~

We recommend that you experience time in a sophisticated space that embraces nature. In addition, it was 3 days and 2 nights where my heart was filled with thoughtful touches and hospitality :)
From check-in to check-out, everything was pleasant and well-prepared, so I definitely plan to visit again.

All-you-can-eat restaurant level, medium to low level

reviews.text: We are CYaRon! I love CYaRon!

The owner is kind. Room conditions are generally acceptable for rooms and living rooms (however, there are a lot of cockroaches, money bugs, etc.). Inconvenient as there is no key for the door. The location is not bad near Seongsan.

Actually, I want to write a good review...
The bathroom is so dirty...
I hope you make sure to clean the swarm.
The manager is kind...
There was no inconvenience for a large family to rest, but the toilet was really watery...

Sharon's House Pension
I went to this accommodation for the first time on my trip to Jeju Island.
The location is very quiet.
I love the sound of birds chirping in the morning.
There is Susanhanmot Lake nearby.

I was worried that it might be too remote.
When I went there, it was really cozy and pretty.
It's not too far from the city,
I was especially worried that it would be cold, but the room felt hot every time I stepped foot in it~~~♡
The boiler is being reduced and cut down.
I was very worried because it might be my last trip with Haru.
I'm very satisfied.
Ps. The owner also reduced the additional fee for the dog.
Thank you so much.

reviews.text: I like the smell of wood

There is nothing basic.
First of all, there is no microwave.
There is no excess either.
The refrigerator was broken
There is no conditioner or body cleanser.
It's very cold in the evening due to the smell of flowers, so I called twice in advance to ask for heating, but when I checked in, the room was cold.
There is a strong smell in the bathroom
This is my first time seeing something like this.
I'm embarrassed that an important part of my trip to Jeju Island was filled with this experience.

The water pressure is weak and the boiler keeps turning off.
But the rest, including the structure of the house and bedding, was good.
The boiler needs some improvement for winter travelers.

The owner is really kind~
The food is also very delicious.

The pension is also very pretty.
I would like to come again next time.
Highly recommended.

I loved it so much. The owner was so kind and nice. I 100% intend to visit again. There were some things that were not available, but when I told the owner, he gave me everything and was very kind. It felt like a home~~~

Batdol Guesthouse.formatted_address: 2 Songdangseo 2-gil, Gujwa-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea

reviews.text:
I chose Baddol Guest House because I like Songdang, and it has a neatly organized yard and rooms! I have been so happy and peaceful. In addition, the owner himself drove us to the secret forest and we enjoyed the beautiful scenery. I regret not being able to climb the nearby mountain.
It is a duplex with two spacious and comfortable beds on the second floor, and on the lower floor you can cook and eat while looking out at the palm trees. While baking bread and making coffee for the morning, I suddenly looked outside and thought, ah, this is happiness.
This is a highly recommended accommodation if you want to experience the quiet and peaceful countryside of Jeju with its palm trees and stone walls.

1. Excellent building: Joints, furniture, and outlets are plentiful. There is a skylight on the duplex bed, so when it rains you can see the rain, and when it is clear you can see the stars.
2. Cleaning: The owner and his wife do the cleaning themselves, and despite the high ceiling, there is no dust and the dishes are clean, with the cleaning skills of a first-class hotel.
3. Location: It is a quiet and secluded location, but it is in front of the bus stop and a 10-minute walk to the center of Songdang.
4. Details: Free early morning ascending tour, beautifully manicured garden, and lights on until 23:00

It was very easy to find as it was right in front of the bus stop, and it was a clean and comfortable accommodation. They helped me check in early and even contacted me to pick me up if I was going to be late when I went out.
He carefully checked the transportation and route and took me to Yongoreum to see the sunrise at 5 a.m. He also showed me some good things nearby. It was a fun trip as there were many small and pretty shops and restaurants in Songdang. It's a place I want to go next time!!
I was most satisfied in every way. It was clean in every way, there was a swing chair in the yard and a trampoline that children would love, and the interior was nice and warm.
Convenient place in Kyoto with quiet scenery and Seongsan port nearby

Hotel With Jeju.adr_address: 34 Noyeon-ro, 특별자치도 Cheju, Jeju-do 63082, South Korea

editorial_summary.overview: Understated rooms in a modern high-rise hotel featuring a restaurant, a rooftop garden & sea views.

reviews.text: Horrendous service but decent, clean rooms. Staff will not help you and are not interested in helping you. They will not book a taxi for you or anything like that. The rooms are good and clean but be aware that twin and triple room bathrooms don't have doors. So the shower room is completely open. This may make things a little uncomfortable, depending on your travel group.

**Location is good, front desk staff not helpful**

Room rate is reasonable. Breakfast (w 12000) can walk in and quite yummy.
The front desk staffs are not helpful to self-travel visitors. They were not take initiation to help. I had problems to download Kakao Taxi app to mobile, the staff was not willing to call taxi for me and ask me just go out to catch the taxi...at midnight 5AM, they even don't know if there are many taxi pass buy. I was quite shocked for this service ;(

I'll choose other hotel around this area next time.

If you are driving in Jeju, avoid booking this hotel as parking is restricted. We were directed to park at an open car park, which is approximately a 10-minute walk away and not very convenient if you have a lot of luggage. The room is clean and spacious. Counter staff are unfriendly.
No bath towels, they gave face towels only. They came thru the room although putting the do not disturb up. Will not return.

This hotel does not provide taxi call service. When I checked out at 6am for early flight, they told me to hail a cab from the street. After 15mins, I gave up and walked to the next hotel down the street, where the receptionist readily helped me to call a cab.

Do not understand why taxi call service is not provided for guests, when other hotels can do it easily (even for me who did not stay with them)

Excellent. A little farther away from the main town, but for the price it was a great place to stay
Nice resort.. value for money. Friendly and helpful staff.
Beautiful resort, excellent service from the resort.
Good and xlean reaort

reviews.text:
Rooms are nice, central warmer and clean.
With attached toilet and kitchen that is easy to prep any meals. There is laundry facility. Owner is friendly and responsive.
Location is near all the attractions located on Seogwipo side.
Near the pension has a few nice eating places within 10 mins walk or 20 mins drive. From 7-11, nice cafes, BBQ porks, porridge, beef bones soup and fried chickens. Will stay here again.

Check in was quick and easy. Owner was very welcoming although he speak very little English. Excellent service and good hospitality. Location is a bit far but quiet and peaceful if that's what you’re looking for. Room come with equipped kitchenette. A little arm chair and small dining table. The surrounding smell a little but it is not bothersome and it is no fault of the place. Would come back again if I am in jeju.

I made a reservation on Boo*.com on the same day and stayed for 2 nights at a low price. The room was very clean and the bathroom was also very clean. Everything I needed was provided and there was no electric rice cooker so I asked and they brought one for me. I stayed on the 2nd floor and the view from the terrace was great. Sea view~
I forgot to bring bottled water, so I asked and the owner just gave me 2 liters. He was so kind~~
If you drive from the pension for about 2 minutes and turn left on the road, there is a 1000 won salt bread event at the bakery restaurant. (Delicious)
I wasn't able to see the area around Andeok due to my schedule, but I want to come back next time.

It is comfortably located amidst the scenery of Yerae Beach in front and Gunsan Oreum in the back, so the scenery was great and the air was clean. (Can be seen separately)
I usually stayed in Seongsan or Seogwipo City, but this time I stayed in Andeok and it was quiet and very nice.
Above all, the owner here was very kind and I was able to create many happy and enjoyable memories during the 10 days.
I was satisfied that both the room and bathroom were clean, and it was nice to be able to relax with a cup of coffee/beer in the morning/dinner in the cafe space on the first floor.
I think it’s a really good environment for people working from home!
The pension provided charcoal and a grill, so I had barbecue three times. It was a burden to wait in line at a good black pork restaurant to buy it, but it was easier and more delicious!
Thank you for taking good care of me and being so considerate.

The best cottage ever in Jeju!
Located in a beautiful spot having mountain at the back and coast/beaches in front.
The room and washroom are very clean! And the room size was spacious and just perfect for me & my wife. We stayed here for 9 days and it was a truly joyful and peaceful holiday.
Charcoal & grill were always ready every night so we had bbq party for 3 nights for during the week. We will definitely come back and stay here again for our Christmas holiday:)
Thanks for treating us so well, Mr. Kim, the owner of the cottage. We really had a great time here in Soo cottage!

A surprisingly good place
You can think of it as an upgraded version of Yam Motel.
It's not a motel, but it has large windows, a veranda, and even an ocean view.
It seems to be good value for money, the price is reasonable and the water comes out well.
The bathroom is small, but it's well-structured as if it were large, and it's a cozy place with heating, full of sunlight, and not much wind.
The bedding is clean and the bed doesn't turn off, so you can sleep comfortably.
The Jeju-style manager is also friendly and nice.

☞Neo Belt Level delivers only honest and honest reviews☜

reviews.text: SOOO EXPENSIVE

The owner came to mow the lawn. It was clean, spacious, and quiet. I woke up in the morning to the sound of birds and raindrops. It was so nice. I want to come again next time. The convenience store is a 7-minute drive away, so it would be a good idea to come prepared in advance when coming to the pension.

It wasn't bad. I was traveling with a large family and it was suitable for sleeping. The room was warm, which was nice. I thought it would be noisy because there was a wind turbine right nearby, but when I entered the room, I could barely hear the noise. I recommend this place to those who go out with large families.

1. It’s really clean and the room design is pretty😊
2. I stayed here with my dog, but there is enough space for the dogs to run around and a dog bowl is provided as standard. Please note!
3. The view behind the barbecue is really 👍
4. The bathroom was spacious and there were plenty of towels provided, so it was comfortable.
5. It's easy to use the washing machine haha. It's in the room so you can use it freely. (+Additional: There's also fabric softener and detergent~)

The owner is friendly, the rooms are in excellent condition, and this is an accommodation with no inconveniences. This is an accommodation I definitely want to come back to again.
Meticulous kitchen utensils, washing machine, spacious bathroom, bathroom condition is also excellent.

reviews.text: Booked the pool villa for a family of 4 with added bbq set and added more meat because it was so delicious. A very relaxing place to end our holiday, the place is not crowded, it felt like a private resort. We did not use much of the private pool as it was summer and there were a lot of flies in the pool despite the staffs did one round of cleaning upon our check in. Due to the season, our rooms have a lot of fruit flies and houseflies too. It was still manageable as we just walked around killing these flies with the electrical racket they gave. Overall, the place is extremely well maintained, somewhere we would like to head back again if we visit Jeju.

I would like to thank the crew onsite, we went on a family holiday with my parents. And my mum had a fall, the staff were helpful with first aid and helped to locate clinic facilities nearby. Special thanks to Carl for his care & kind assistance during our stay there. Amidst the situation, we had a pleasant stay there. Thank you!

The ambience and set up of the entire place was very relaxed, nordic style. Just the right place to chill and take a break. Book the caravans with bbq pit, facilities were adequate and clean. Will be back again next next time.
We booked the Airstream 31+ and topped up for the grill & meat set for outdoor bbq. It was a lovely experience!

Have a really good time here. The campus is neat and well organized. The twin room is an adorable lodge with full furniture and kitchen accessories. With pre-request of grill, one can even enjoy a BBQ night here.

reviews.text: Located close to the 800 busses and 15 min walk uphill from the main road, bus station and e-mart. It's a nice hotel with a 7-eleven just a few steps next to it. Hotel rooms are nice, there's a washing machine and microwave plus refrigerator. Only thing I'm missing is cutlery and some plates to actually eat what you can make. At the Lobby & Cafe, I couldn't find a cafe? Only a microwave and some chopsticks and a seating area. The rooms are quite modern, loved the view over the sea and the stadium and a big tv with options to log into your own Netflix. Would def recommend if you travel here (by bus and car).
Amazing
It was good quality accommodation at a relatively low price. The photo shows the mountain view and rooftop view.

Some rooms have a foul smell of sewage mold. If you have a room that smells upon entering, you must request a change immediately.
This hotel was closed during the coronavirus pandemic. It appears that the drain pipes were not cleaned while the building was being reused after being vacant for several years. The staff's answer is that it is random as not all rooms are like that.
I understood the situation because I used to frequent the hotel even before Corona, but it was not removed even with ventilation or fans, and it was to the point where I couldn't sleep even while lying in bed.
I contacted the front desk at 10:30 pm and they changed my room. The employee left work at 11 o'clock, so if I had made a mistake, I would have stayed up all night by opening the door (the ventilation wasn't limited to the window, so I had to open the hallway door as well).
I don't understand why a room like this wasn't checked during cleaning.
The hotel's attitude of accepting guests without cleaning the entire drain just because all the rooms are like that is absurd.
You should consider that the hotel may not have been cleaned as it has not been used in a washing machine or air conditioner for a long time. The washing machine in my room had black stains so I only spun it.
1. View - The ocean view is not good because there are buildings in front, other than a few high rises and the west line. In fact, the view of Hallasan Mountain is better on a clear day.
2. Room size - small.  Other than a few twin rooms, the rooms are said to be the same size. However, on the Agoda site, the ocean view double is listed as the same size (26m3) as the twin, so it is the same price as the twin.
3. This hotel is good value for money, but does not provide breakfast. (There used to be a meal box, but I don’t think there is one anymore.)

This hotel maintains 5-star level of cleanliness.
The room is small, but if you move the bed and put it against the wall, it can function as a twin room.
The interior of the room is not the best, but it is upper to upper middle class and suitable for a comfortable stay.
When staying overnight, room service came and changed not only hand towels, but also large bath towels and floor towels.
The staff are polite and very professional.

The location isn't bad either.
It has a nice view of Hallasan Mountain and the neighborhood is quiet and clean, located within Seogwipo Innovation City. Just down the road, there is a restaurant area with many good restaurants next to the Seogwipo Fire Station. There aren't many restaurants, but they're all good. Although they may not be gourmet restaurants, they seem to be great value for money.

The price of 55,000 won is not cheap, but it is a business-class hotel with almost 5-star cleanliness and service, so if you can get a discount if you stay for consecutive nights or more than 3 days, this is a hotel you would want to stay at again.

reviews.text:
I stayed here to go to Bijarim Forest and Darangshi Oreum, and thanks to you, I had a good rest!!
It was nice and warm because it was a hanok, and the interior was very clean. Above all, the owner was very friendly, so I was able to rest 100 times better!
When I asked about the location, they kindly informed me. I asked if I could leave my luggage after checking out, and they gladly allowed it, so I was able to travel without worry!
Bijarim Forest can be reached in 5 minutes on foot, and it is also close to Darangshi Oreum, so it was easily accessible.
Next time I come to the east, this is an accommodation I definitely want to stop by.

This is a bed and breakfast, and you can only reserve rooms for 7 days or more. I don't recommend it.
Because there is nothing near the accommodation. It takes 10 to 15 minutes by car to get to downtown Sehwa.
I think it will be very inconvenient for people without a car. The only place nearby that can be reached on foot is Bijarim Forest.
It's okay and quiet for the first two days. But after 2 days, it became very uncomfortable.
If you are just staying at home without thinking, eating all three meals a day, and going for a walk in Bijarim Forest, or if you are taking your own car, please try staying here.
The owner is quick to respond (he runs a restaurant out front), but since he only rents the room for a long period of time, the bathroom is a bit messy.
I recommend it to those who just want to spend their time without thinking about anything.
However, if you are planning to heal and travel in Jeju Island, I recommend spending a little more money and choosing another accommodation.
If you don't have your own car or rental car, look elsewhere.
It's so uncomfortable.
The owner is friendly and the room is a red clay room, so it’s really nice.

I love it because it’s a red clay room.
It is an accommodation that matches well with Bijarim Forest.

I'm so satisfied!!
It is a two-story red clay ondol room. There are 3 rooms, 1 kitchen and 1 bathroom each.

reviews.text:
I visited this place after seeing Airbnb reviews, but I was quite disappointed. Rather than looking like the interior had been renovated, it felt a bit like the building was demolished and decorated at a low cost.

There was quite a bit of dust, and most of all, it was disappointing that the room was very cold and the bed was not good.

This is very great Traveling
Good Stay in Place!
It is similar to a B&B next to a provincial highway. The surrounding area is also very quiet and not too noisy. Although it is a bit far from the seaside, I stayed there for 4 days and three nights and felt it was pretty good. However, the sound insulation is a bit poor, and because there are plants next to it, the smell is a bit... Heavy, try not to open the windows next to it. Everything else feels fine

The obvious advantage is that the accommodation costs are low and the cost-effectiveness is good. Also, it feels like the landlord put a lot of thought into the interior decoration of the accommodation. They say you have emotions, right? However, there were many difficulties as I stayed for several days.
- I decided on a place to stay after understanding that it was a dry bathroom, so I had to be careful every time I showered. However, there is no way that such features can properly clean bathroom scales. For that reason, I had to endure a musty smell when the water dried after showering, and there was mold on the silicone part of the bathroom. Also, due to the nature of the bathroom, I had to leave the door open to reduce the smell, but as a result, the room was filled with moisture and my clothes got wet.
- It is located right next to the road, so there is bound to be noise. Because it is a country road, there are few cars, but the sound of cars passing by in the early morning was annoying.
- The part that was so difficult for me in collaboration with the second point was the bed. It was so hard that I would wake up every morning and twist my back. However, once I woke up, I couldn't sleep because of the occasional sound of a passing car. Because of this, I had to travel with a swollen face and tired throughout the entire trip. I really thought it would be more comfortable to sleep on the floor with a blanket.
- The heating is a heater-air conditioner type, so it gets very dry when turned on in cold weather.

I chose this accommodation because of its cost-effectiveness, but after the trip was over, my thoughts were that from now on, it would be better to go to an accommodation where I feel comfortable, even if it means spending more money.
It seems like a good place to stay for couples or friends in their early to mid-20s with light budget but full of energy.
A great place for healing camp, drive carefully when entering the car.
I liked that it was so clean and the host was so friendly. I want to come again next time

Tashidelek.formatted_address: 612-6 Gasi-ro, Pyoseon-myeon, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
Tashidelek.name: Tashidelek

reviews.text:
A cozy, highly unique guesthouse that made me feel like part of the family. The owner has handmade many of the furnishings and rooms giving a Tibetan Buddhist feel to the place.

The best part is all the nature. There is a small tangerine orchard on the property and a small hill to hike, walking distance from the place.

If you like an earthy type place, that is completely different than the typical ones in Korean, this is it.
Very peaceful lovely natural comfortable friendly place in the nature with good vibes. A wonderful place to decharge/ recharge from the stress of daily life.

It's hard to get to, but I think people who come here will come for the tranquility. The talented owner, Beam, is the best part about this place. It's a pity that it has changed to a long-term stay, but it still retains its charm as a haven of its own for over a dozen years.

A space built by the owner, an amazing Jeju woman who makes everything herself. Before the coronavirus, it was a famous and crowded guesthouse, but due to the COVID-19 pandemic and many other hardships, they said they changed it to long-term stays of 2 weeks to 1 month or more. The entire large grounds are works of art and nature. It's a really wonderful place where you can spend your time camping in nature. However, there are bugs and snakes, and the bathroom can be a bit uncomfortable.
A place with a unique charm, it is said that it has now become focused on long-term stays.

The host it's super friendly man Soo Woun I hope I wrote it right,

But the place kinda remotely, however it's super nice in horse farm also with great views to wind turbines and Halassan mt.

This resort has an exotic atmosphere. As soon as we arrived, we said it had a Southeast Asian feel.  It's not very sophisticated or anything like that, but the owner is kind. And the surrounding scenery is very nice. Large lawn yard. It is said that the dog greets you warmly and that he also raises his own horse.
It was a great place to relax as a family.

A quiet rural village. It doesn't feel like a condo hotel. It felt like I was at a country house. It was nice because there was no TV, but it was hot in the summer because there was only one air conditioner in the living room. Well-equipped bed and breakfast. Serenity.
This is the best accommodation for those who want to find peace of mind in nature. The surrounding scenery is really nice, and it's great for a walk.

Highly recommended if you want quiet healing!
Delicious coffee and simple breakfast.
A place where dogs are warmly welcomed~

reviews.text: The accommodation is clean and the host is friendly.

I was so thankful that the owner welcomed me so warmly.
I was a little cautious because it was a Kosi country, but the accommodation was very clean and the bedding had a soft laundry smell, so I slept comfortably. I was disappointed that the hydrangeas weren't blooming yet because it wasn't the season, but I can't forget the feeling of healing with the bath bombs prepared in the bathroom. The bathroom is really the biggest advantage of this accommodation, but other than that, I had a pleasant stay thanks to the owner's careful consideration. Next time I come to Jeju, I want to stay again.

I was really satisfied with my choice of accommodation.
It feels like every detail was taken care of throughout the accommodation.
The accommodation is also very pretty, but since it is a private house, I can have all the pictures of the pretty hydrangea garden to myself.
It’s so frustrating because it’s a much prettier place in real life ㅜㅜㅜ
This time I came as a sister trip, but I think it would be better as a couple trip.

Accommodation on the first day of summer vacation in Jeju Island. I wondered if there was a place like this haha. It looks pretty by itself, but I highly recommend visiting during hydrangea season! The bathroom is another highlight. The owner was very friendly and recommended good restaurants nearby, so I enjoyed my stay.

I think it would be the best atmosphere even for a honeymoon.
I can feel the owner's kindness and consideration in making sure the guests have a comfortable rest throughout the place.

Go To Bed Resort.name: Go To Bed Resort

reviews.text:
I was very, very satisfied!
The interior was neat, but it was structured so that I could see nature, and although it was close to nature, there weren't many bugs (that's why it's so clean, right?), so I was very satisfied😃 This place is really nice, but there aren't as many customers as I thought, so I'm promoting it to my acquaintances.
If I had to point out a downside, it would be that the location isn't very close to the city center and the bed wasn't very soft, but it didn't feel like a spring or was a stone bed!
The blanket feels so good too! First of all, I liked the view because it was so green haha.
The owner and his wife were also very kind. I would definitely visit again^^

The price was cheap, and overall the facilities were clean and nice. I stayed in a duplex on the 3rd floor, and the views from front to back were great. (Picture taken in the morning) Hallasan Mountain and Udo Island are spread out... I almost regretted not waking up earlier in the morning.
I went to Udo Island and stayed there for the evening. The location was not inconvenient, but it was a quiet village, so it was good for a quiet rest.

Perhaps because it was built not long ago, it is clean overall and breakfast is free! There is also a karaoke room and barbecue area in the basement, which is nice.
One thing that is disappointing is that the light in the room is yellow. When I asked, it was almost like that. They're kind and very nice, but if they just fix this, it's the best value for money.
I was impressed by how quiet the accommodation was, the bedding was soft, and the overall cleanliness. The facilities are not fancy but are clean. I'm satisfied with the price~~

I stayed for 4 days and 3 nights until yesterday. I had an 18-month-old baby, so I deliberately stayed in an ondol room, but I was more satisfied because both the room and bathroom were clean. Moreover, they provided a separate baby pillow and lent me a baby bathtub for showering, so I stayed without any inconvenience. ^^
